title: cream cheese cookies
directions: Mix together and bake at 350 degrees for 8- 10 minutes.

title: oven stew
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients together; add meat, mushrooms, onions, carrots, celery and potatoes.
Put in 2-quart casserole dish and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Stir and then cook for another 30 minutes to 1 hour or until potatoes and carrots are tender.

title: linda's peanut butter mousse
directions: Soften cream cheese at room temperature for about 2 hours. Beat softened cream cheese and sugar; mix in peanut butter.
Whip cream until very stiff and fold into other ingredients carefully, a little at a time.
Chill.
Spoon into individual graham cracker crusts and top with Reddi-Wip at serving time.
Garnish with shaved chocolate or chocolate sprinkles, if desired.
This recipe does 6 individual crusts nicely.

title: wilma's squash croquettes
directions: Combine all ingredients; mix well.
Drop by spoonfuls into 1/2-inch hot oil until done.
Sure good!

title: pork and beans to can
directions: Soak beans overnight.
Cook beans until soft.
Mix the rest of the ingredients together.
Cook a few minutes, then add to soft beans and mix well.
Put in jars and seal.
Cold pack 1 1/2 hours.

title: slow cooker swiss steak
directions: Assemble all ingredients in slow cooker.
Cook on low heat for 7 hours or until meat and vegetables are tender.

title: cooking wild game
directions: Clean, wash and cut meat in serving size pieces.
Place meat in heavy saucepan, covering with cold water and 1/2 teaspoon salt. Soak for 30 minutes.
After soaking, place saucepan and its contents on medium-high heat and boil for 30 minutes.
After boiling, drain liquid from meat.
Return to burner and cover the meat with water again, adding 1 to 2 bay leaves and 2 tablespoons of lard or a small piece of salt pork.
Cook until tender.
Remove meat from cooker and place in baking dish.
Sprinkle with salt and black pepper and bake at 400° until brown.

title: hot potato salad
directions: Boil potatoes with skins on; peel and thinly slice.
Boil eggs; chop coarsely.
Fry bacon slices and drain.
In bacon fat, saute onion and celery until golden brown.
Blend in flour, sugar, salt, dry mustard, celery salt and pepper; cook over low heat, stir until smooth and bubbly.
Remove from heat and stir in water and vinegar.
Bring to a boil, stirring constantly.
Boil for 1 minute; crumble up strips of bacon and pour mixture over eggs and potatoes.
Mix gently.
Let stand until ready to serve.
Sprinkle with parsley, if desired.
Serves 4.

title: chicken breasts diane
directions: Pound breasts slightly between sheets of waxed paper. Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Heat 1 tablespoon each of oil and butter in a large skillet.
Cook chicken over high heat for 4 minutes on each side.
Transfer to warm serving platter.
Add remaining ingredients to pan and cook for 15 seconds, whisking constantly.
Whisk in broth and stir until sauce is smooth.
Whisk in remaining butter and oil.
Pour sauce over chicken.
Serve immediately.

title: cornstarch paint(non-eatable)
directions: Mix the water, cornstarch and several drops of food coloring together in a saucepan.
Heat and stir the mixture until it thickens, about 5 minutes.
Let it cool.
Store in a covered container.

title: corned beef and cabbage
directions: Put meat in large saucepan with all ingredients, except the cabbage.
Cover with cold water and bring to a boil, then skim off any scum.
Cover and simmer for 3/4 hour.
Put in cabbage, trimmed and quartered.
Cook for 30 minutes to the pound and serve.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix all ingredients and knead.
Make into balls about a quarter size.
Bake at 300° for 25 minutes.
May be served with or without dipping sauces.

title: hot butterscotch sauce
directions: Melt butterscotch morsels over hot water.
Stir in canned milk until smooth.
Great over ice cream.

title: swedish apple pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together and set aside, except for 1 tablespoon sugar and 1 teaspoon cinnamon.
Fill pie plate 2/3 full with apples. Mix together 1 tablespoon of sugar and 1 teaspoon of cinnamon and sprinkle mixture over apples; spread evenly.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes

title: orange salad
directions: Stir real good, Jell-O, cheese and Cool Whip.
Drain pineapple and oranges; stir in.

title: les tuna dip
directions: Mix together.
Serve with crackers or vegetables.

title: four layer dessert
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pat into a 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: fried pies
directions: Crust:
Cut margarine into flour.
Combine egg yolk, milk and salt; add to flour.
Knead well to make a smooth dough.
Roll 1/8-inch thick and cut into rounds or squares.

title: monkey bread
directions: Cut biscuits in quarters and roll in sugar and cinnamon. Place biscuit quarters in Bundt pan. Boil sugar, butter and cinnamon for 1 minute. Pour over biscuits and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: stuffed baked potatoes
directions: Scrub the potatoes and prick with fork several times. Microwave on High for 12 to 15 minutes.
Rearrange them halfway through cooking.
Let potatoes stand 5 to 10 minutes.
In small microwavable bowl, heat chili until bubbly hot.
Place a potato on individual serving plate.
Cut an X in each potato.
Squeeze to push pulp out.
Top potatoes with chili, cheese, lettuce and salsa or tomato sauce.

title: crispy chewy cornflake cookies
directions: Mix all dry ingredients thoroughly.
Add eggs, vanilla and oil.
Stir well and drop by teaspoon onto cookie sheets.
Bake at 375° for 6 to 8 minutes.

title: french chocolate cake
directions: In a bowl, beat eggs and sugar until light and fluffy.
In another bowl, combine flour, cornstarch and baking powder.
Add to egg mix.
Line a 9-inch round baking pan with wax paper; do not grease sides of pan.
Pour batter into pan.
Bake at 375° for about 30 minutes.
Let cake cool in pan.
Loosen around edges with a knife; carefully turn cake out onto rack and peel off paper.

title: hot mexican dip
directions: Brown and drain fat from 2 meats.
Melt cheese in microwave. Crush tomatoes and chilies in blender to a fine liquid.
Combine all ingredients over heat.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: cheese loaf
directions: Combine meat loaf mix and hot water; let stand 15 minutes to re-hydrate.
Combine all ingredients and pour into a well-oiled flat loaf pan.
Bake in a 350° oven for 45 minutes.
Serve with creamed vegetables, mushrooms, tomato or brown gravy.

title: deviled ham ball
directions: Mix all of the ingredients.
Chill in the refrigerator for 2 hours.
Roll in a ball and then roll in pecan pieces until completely coated.
Serve with party crackers.

title: chocolate truffles
directions: Melt butter; stir in cocoa.
Cool.
In large mixer bowl combine cocoa mixture with sugar; gradually add cream, vanilla and almond extract, if desired, blending well.
Chill until firm. Shape small amount of mixture around almond; form into 1-inch balls.
Roll in coating until covered.
Cover and chill until firm or freeze up to 4 weeks.
Re-roll in coating before serving. Makes about 3 1/2 dozen.

title: lentil pate
directions: Bring water to boil.
Add dry lentils and cover.
Simmer 45 minutes until lentils are tender.
Remove from heat and drain.

title: meat balls(for spaghetti dinner or meat ball sandwich)
directions: Wet bread thoroughly.
Squeeze out water and crumble fine; should equal 2 cups of bread.
Mix remaining ingredients, including bread, in large bowl.
When thoroughly mixed, make meat balls.
Fry in oil.
Brown on 1 side, turn and brown on the other side.
After spaghetti sauce has cooked, add cooked meat balls and cook for an added 15 to 20 minutes.

title: strawberry jello salad
directions: Drain the strawberries and pineapple.
Use the juice for liquid in preparing the Jell-O.
Let the Jell-O partially set up, so you can whip it.
(Watch closely so it doesn't set to a firm stage.)
Whip Jell-O and fold in the pineapple and strawberries. Then add the heavy whipped cream last.
Refrigerate.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli and drain.
Add cheese, soup, onion and cheese. Bake at 350° for about 1 hour and 10 minutes before completing cooking process.
Crumble crackers on top and finish bake time.

title: hamburger stroganoff
directions: In skillet, cook meat and onion in butter until brown.
Stir in flour, garlic, salt and pepper stirring constantly.
Reduce heat; simmer 10 minutes.
Stir in sour cream and heat through. Serve over noodles.

title: barbecue beef sandwiches
directions: Mix all together and simmer 45 minutes.

title: meatballs
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients and roll into 1-inch balls.
Brown in a small amount of oil.
Mix beef consomme and mushroom soup together. Drain meatballs and add to soup mixture.
Cover and simmer for 20 to 30 minutes.
Serve over rice.

title: blueberry buckle
directions: Cut batter in as for pie crust.
Bake for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: christmas cutout cookies
directions: Add sugar to shortening and cream well.
Add salt, vanilla and unbeaten eggs; beat well.
Add sour cream alternately with the sifted dry ingredients.
Chill dough.
Roll and cut with floured cookie cutters.
Place on cookie sheets.
Bake until light brown, 10 minutes at 400°.

title: salsa
directions: Mix ingredients in large stock pot.
Bring to a boil.
Simmer 20 minutes.
Process in water bath canner for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: candy turtles
directions: Melt caramels and milk.
Add pecans.
Drop by teaspoon onto buttered cookie sheets.
Put in freezer 15 to 20 minutes.

title: green tomato pie
directions: Cook all together; add 1/2 teaspoon cinnamon and 1/4 teaspoon cloves.
Divide into 2 (9-inch) pie shells and bake at 425° for 20 minutes and then reduce heat to 375° and bake until brown.

title: apple pie
directions: Arrange apples in pie crust.
Mix 1/2 cup sugar and cinnamon; sprinkle over apples.
Mix 1/3 cup sugar with flour.
Cut in butter until crumbly.
Sprinkle over apples.
Top with sprinkles of cinnamon.
Bake at 400°
for 35 to 40 minutes or until brown.

title: sausage cheese muffins
directions: Cook sausage and drain.
In bowl, combine soup, milk, sage, and sausage.
Stir in biscuit mix just until moistened.
Fill greased muffin cups 2/3 full.
Bake at 400° for 15-20 minutes. Makes 2 dozen.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Place all ingredients in mixing bowl.
Mix well.
Put in 2 loaf pans that have been floured and greased.
Bake 1 hour at 350° or until done.
While still hot, butter top.
Cool.
Turn out on rack. Freezes well.

title: cheesy manicotti
directions: Combine 1/3 cup Parmesan cheese and the next 6 items in a bowl.
Stir well; set aside.
Stuff each shell with 1/4 cup cheese mixture.
Arrange in dish.
Pour sauce over shells.
Cover; bake at 375° for 25 minutes.
Uncover; sprinkle remaining Parmesan cheese and bake for 5 more minutes.
Serves 6.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Mix the mayonnaise, sugar and vinegar together.
Add the remaining ingredients, mix and refrigerate.

title: southern sweet potato pie
directions: Boil sweet potatoes until done.
Peel and set aside.
Mash well.
Add milk, flavoring, sugar, butter, flour and brown sugar. Mix well.
Add potatoes and lastly, add eggs; hand beat eggs. Pour in ready to bake pie shells.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: jellied fruit salad
directions: Note:
Pineapple (if used) must be cooked or canned.

title: cherry cobbler(diabetic)
directions: Combine flour, baking powder and salt in a large mixing bowl. Cut in shortening until consistency of cornmeal.
Combine milk, 1 teaspoon of the Fasweet and the beaten egg.
Add to the dry ingredients, stirring only until dampened.
Meanwhile, sweeten cherries with remaining Fasweet.
Place in a 1-quart casserole and sprinkle with tapioca.
Spoon batter over cherries.
Bake in a moderate oven (350°) 30 to 40 minutes or until top is golden brown. Serves 8.

title: easy enchiladas
directions: Mix together chili, onions and 1 1/2 cups of cheese.
Spread about 2 heaping tablespoons of mixture down center of tortilla and roll up.
Place in a greased 8 x 8-inch pan as you go.
Spread remaining mixture (should be about half of it) over the top, completely covering rolls.
Sprinkle with remaining cheese.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: jalapeno cheese bread
directions: In a large bowl, proof the yeast in 1/4 cup lukewarm water with the sugar for 15 minutes, or until it is foamy; add 1 3/4 cups water, the vinegar and the salt and combine the mixture well. Stir in 5 cups of the flour and combine the dough well.
Knead the dough on a well floured surface, incorporating more of the flour as necessary to keep it from sticking, for 10 minutes, or until it is smooth and elastic and form it into a ball.
Put the dough in a buttered bowl; turn it to coat it with the butter and let it rise, covered with a plastic wrap, in a warm place for 1 hour, or until it is double in bulk.

Punch down the dough; divide it into 3 pieces and roll each piece into a 16-inch rope. Transfer the ropes to a buttered baking sheet; let them rise for 15 to 20 minutes, or until they have almost doubled in bulk and with a sharp knife, make a slash down the center of each one to within 1/2-inch of the bottom.
In a small bowl, combine well the mild chilies and the jalapeno chilies and spoon the mixture down the center of the loaves.
Cover the chili mixture with the Mozzarella; bake the loaves in a preheated 375° oven for 25 to 35 minutes or until the Mozzarella and the bottom of the loaves are golden and let them cool on a rack.
Makes 3 loaves.

title: pie crust
directions: Beat flour, Crisco and salt.
Add water and wine, mixing well. Flour rolling surface.
Form dough into ball and roll out to an 1/8-inch thickness.
Take pie pan and hold over dough to get correct measurement.
(The key to pie crust is rolling dough one time only.)
May need to use spatula to loosen crust from surface.

title: rigatoni al prosciutto
directions: Cook rigatoni in boiling water; drain.
Mix together half and half, ham, butter and Parmigiano.
Put in a Pyrex casserole dish (13 x 9 x 2-inch).
Scald milk.
Melt butter in another pot.
Add flour, salt, pepper and nutmeg.
Mix well.
Add scalded milk. Stir continuously over low heat until it boils.
Stir continuously for 5 minutes.
Pour over rigatoni.
Dot with butter and Parmigiano.
Place in the 325° oven for 25 minutes.
Serve hot.

title: missionary church soup
directions: Combine can soups with milk.
Add cheese and warm until cheese is melted.
Add cooked broccoli last.
Great for a large number of people.

title: breakfast burritos
directions: Brown sausage in medium frying pan; drain well.
Set aside. Saute onions in butter in large frying pan.
Add chili flakes and Tater Tots.
Mash Tater Tots, add sausage and mix well until hot. Crack all eggs on top of mixture and scramble until cooked well done.
Do not burn eggs.
Serve in heated bowl with warmed tortillas on side with salsa, shredded Cheddar cheese and jalapeno peppers.

title: fruit salad
directions: Drain fruit; save pineapple juice.
Mix pudding with pineapple juice to make a thin dressing.
Add fruit and chill.

title: italian bean soup
directions: Drain and rinse the white kidney beans.
Remove 1 1/2 cups beans to medium bowl.
With potato masher or fork, mash beans until smooth.
In 5-quart Dutch oven or saucepot over medium high heat, in hot oil, cook ham, celery, carrots, onion, zucchini, basil and pepper until vegetables are tender and begin to brown, about 15 minutes.
Stir in stewed tomatoes, chicken broth, spinach, mashed beans and 2 cups water.
Over high heat, heat to boiling.
Reduce heat to low, cover and simmer 15 minutes.
Stir in remaining beans; heat through.
When serving, sprinkle each serving with grated Parmesan cheese, if desired.

title: microwave glazed carrots
directions: Combine carrots, butter and brown sugar in a 1 or 2-quart casserole.
Cover with plastic wrap and microwave on High for 9 to 10 minutes.
Stir after 5 minutes.
Combine mustard, orange juice and cornstarch.
Pour over carrots.
Microwave on High 2 to 3 minutes or until thickened.

title: chicken-n-rice
directions: Cook rice; set aside.
Saute onion and celery in butter.
In large mixing bowl, combine all ingredients.
Bake in 13 x 9-inch baking dish at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: "philly" velvet cream pie
directions: Combine finely crushed chocolate wafers with margarine.
Press into bottom of 9-inch pie pan.
Bake at 325° for 10 minutes. Cool.

title: okra with corn and tomatoes
directions: In 10-inch skillet, combine corn, okra, tomatoes, onions, celery and ham.
Add water, oregano, salt and red peppers; bring to boil.
Lower heat and simmer for 10 minutes or until vegetables are tender.
Stir occasionally.
Simmer, uncovered, for 5 minutes more.

title: asparagus casserole
directions: Cook noodles according to directions on package.
Place in the bottom of a casserole dish.
Slice cheese and place on top of macaroni.
Cut asparagus in half and cover cheese.
Top with cream of mushroom soup.
Spoon asparagus liquid over soup.
Bake at 350° until cheese bubbles to top.

title: texas-style deviled eggs
directions: Slice eggs lengthwise.
Mix egg yolks with remaining ingredients.
Fill 20 egg whites.

title: blueberry cream cheese pie
directions: Melt butter in oven at 350°; add flour.
Press into the bottom of the cake pan and top with nuts.
Bake for 30 minutes; let cool.

title: mbsf cheese dip
directions: Melt margarine.
Add flour, spices and small amount of milk to dissolve spices.
Add rest of milk.
Add cheese.
Cook until thick.

title: cajun-spiced shrimp with pasta
directions: Combine spices and garlic in small bowl.
Cook pasta according to package directions.
When there is about 3 minutes left, melt 1/2 stick butter in frypan; add spices and peeled shrimp and saute until pink, about 2 to 2 1/2 minutes.
Drain pasta.
Melt 3 tablespoons butter in pasta pot; return pasta to pot and stir in shrimp mixture.
Keep warm.
Add last 1 tablespoon butter to frypan.
Cook zucchini and green onions for 1 minute.
Add tomatoes and parsley and cook a few seconds.
Add to pasta and mix well.
Serve with Parmesan cheese and a salad.

title: cream puffs
directions: Add shortening to water and bring to boil.
Add flour all at once and stir vigorously until ball forms in center of pan.
Cool slightly.
Add unbeaten eggs, one at a time, beating after adding each egg.
Mixture should be very stiff.
Shape on oiled cookie sheet by dropping from spoon or using pastry bag and tube.
Bake at 450° for 15 minutes.
Reduce temperature to moderate 350° and continue baking for 30 minutes or until done.
(Test one.)
Cool. Fill with whipped cream, custard pudding.
Makes 2 dozen small puffs.

title: chess bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees.
Combine cake mix, 1 egg and butter.
Mix well.
Pour batter in the bottom of a large greased baking pan.
Spread evenly.
In a medium mixing bowl combine softened cream cheese powdered sugar and 3 eggs.
Mix well.
Pour mixture over cake mix batter.
Bake for 40 minutes.
Remove from oven and cool.
Cut into bars.
Serve cooled.

title: strawberry congealed salad
directions: Beat cream cheese until smooth and creamy.
Mix Jell-O with 1/2 cup boiling water; mix slowly with cream cheese.
Fold in fruit and refrigerate 1 hour or more and serve.

title: fried rice
directions: Brown rice in cooking oil.
Add finely chopped onions.
Mash garlic and cumin seed.
Add dry ingredients.
Stir in tomato sauce and stir.
Add water or chicken broth.
Bring to boil 5 to 10 minutes.
Lower heat and simmer, covered, until done.

title: rainbow popcorn balls
directions: Combine syrup and sugar and bring to boil.
Remove from heat. Add gelatin and stir until dissolved and add peanuts if desired and pour over popcorn, mixing well.
Shape into 1 1/2-inch balls. Makes 4 dozen.

title: taco salad
directions: Cook hamburger; drain.
Add taco mix and onion.
In a bowl, put lettuce, tomatoes, cheese and chips.
Put hamburger mixture right in center.
Add sour cream and salsa.
Serves 8 people.

title: ann's old fashioned chocolate pie
directions: Mix flour, sugar and cocoa in saucepan; add 1/2 of milk.
Mix well.
Add egg yolks; mix well.
Add rest of ingredients.
Cook over low heat; stir continuously until spoon is coated.
Pour in baked shell.
Put egg white over top and bake at 350° until brown.

title: lemonade
directions: Wash the lemons.
Cut the slices from the center.
Remove the seeds.
Squeeze and strain.
Add the sugar and water.

title: racquet club chicken salad
directions: Cook chicken until tender, cool and cut into chunks.
In food processor chop celery and pickles, adding eggs last for chopping. Mix all ingredients together with mayonnaise and Italian dressing. Salt and pepper to taste.
May add 1 tablespoon sugar.

title: meat loaf by aunt mary lee
directions: Mix well and shape into loaf.
Bake for 1 hour at 300°.

title: cracked wheat pilaf
directions: Wash cracked wheat with cold water.
Drain and set aside. Place 2 tablespoons butter in a heavy saucepan; add onion and saute until golden brown.
Add tomato sauce and cook another 5 minutes. Add broth, the rest of the butter, salt and pepper and bring to a boil.
Add cracked wheat; stir once, cover and boil for 5 minutes on high.
Reduce heat and cook until cracked wheat absorbs all the broth, about 25 minutes.
Remove from heat, remove cover and place a napkin over pan.
Replace cover.
Leave in a warm place for 40 minutes.
Should be flaky.
Serves 6.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Place cooked ground chuck in the bottom of 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Drain can of your favorite vegetable; put on top of ground chuck.
Pour cream of celery soup on top.
Top with a layer of "Tater Tots".
Bake in a 350° oven for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: russian pie(from mom campanelli's friend, linda)
directions: Cream together
butter,
sugar,
egg
yolks
and
lemon extract.
Add flour and mix together and spread in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Spread apricot preserves on top of dough.

title: spanish squash
directions: Cook squash with 1/2 onion and salt until tender, don't overcook.
Drain,
reserving
liquid.
Add soup and 1/2 can of liquid
from cooked squash.
Simmer remaining onion and pepper in oleo
until
limp,
but
not
brown.
Add
onion
mixture, pimientos,
crackers, egg and cheese to squash mixture.
Place in greased Pyrex casserole dish and bake at 350° for 1/2 hour. Toast some
cracker
crumbs
in
oleo
and
put on top before baking, if desired.

title: tomato surprise salad
directions: Pour tomatoes in saucepan; bring to a boil.
Add jello and salt; stir until dissolved.
Add lemon juice; stir and pour into Pam sprayed mold.
Makes 4 cups.
Use as a salad or relish.
Serve with mayonnaise on a bed of greens.

title: potato soup
directions: Add sour cream and Velveeta to cooked potatoes.
Can add fried bacon or bacon bits and green onions when serving in individual bowls.

title: chili pepper spread
directions: Advance preparation:
Bring Cheddar cheese to room temperature.
Heat milk to boiling; pour over cheese in mixing bowl.
Beat with electric mixer until nearly smooth.
Add butter and garlic; beat well.
Stir in chopped chili peppers.
(Mixture will be thin.)
Chill well.
Serve with crackers.
Makes 1 1/2 cups spread.

title: new potato medley
directions: Melt margarine	in
a
large saucepan over medium heat. Add potatoes
and remaining ingredients.
Toss gently.	Cover and reduce heat and cook 20 minutes.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Cream butter, peanut butter, sugar, egg and vanilla. Sift together dry ingredients; blend into creamed mixture. Shape in 1-inch balls. Roll in granulated sugar. Place 2-inches apart on ungreased cookie sheet. Crisscross with fork. Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes. Cool slightly. Makes 4 dozen.

title: corn flake candy
directions: Boil Karo and brown sugar 1 minute; remove from heat. Then add peanut butter, vanilla, butter and corn flakes. Mix together and drop on wax paper.

title: caramel apple walnut squares
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
In large bowl, combine flour, oats, sugar, baking soda and salt.
Cut in margarine until crumbly. Reserving 1 1/2 cups crumb mixture, press remainder on bottom of 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Bake 15 minutes.
Add walnuts to reserved crumb mixture.
In heavy saucepan, over low heat, melt caramels with sweetened condensed milk, stirring, until smooth.
Spoon apple filling over prepared crust.
Top with caramel mixture, then reserved crumb mixture.
Bake 20 minutes or until set.
Cool.
tags: Thank You brand apple pie filling

title: pasta salad
directions: Cook spaghetti until tender; drain, then rinse with cold water.
Cut tomato, cucumber and green onions into small pieces. Combine spaghetti, vegetables and olives.
Pour Italian dressing over mixture; stir.
Refrigerate 6 hours.
Mix well and serve.

title: quick banana bread
directions: Grease bottoms of two loaf pans.
Mix all ingredients and beat 30 seconds.
Pour into pans and bake 55 to 60 minutes (inserted toothpick will come out clean when done).
Cool 5 minutes.
Loosen sides with knife and remove from pans.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Combine vanilla wafers, pecans, sugar and butter and pat in bottom of pan.
Let cool.

title: sausage casserole
directions: Crumble sausage in skillet and fry.
Drain well.
Mix all ingredients well. Pour into 10 x 8 x 2-inch pan.

title: pea picking cake
directions: Beat all ingredients together about 3 minutes with mixer. Pour into 2 or 3 oiled and floured cake pans.
Bake at 325° until done.
Cool before icing.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Mix together broccoli, Cheddar cheese, onion and bacon bits. Mix mayonnaise, sugar and vinegar.
Pour over broccoli.
Mix before serving.
Refrigerate.

title: cheese coins
directions: Thoroughly combine first
ingredients.
Add
flour a little at a time.
Knead until
smooth.
Form into a long roll about 1-inch in diameter.
Cut
into 1/4-inch slices.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Use ungreased cookie sheet.

title: cherry supreme
directions: Put fruit, juice and all, into large mixing bowl.
Add marshmallows; stir.
Add dry Jell-O; stir.
Place, covered, in refrigerator overnight. Stir well before mixing the other ingredients.

title: spaghetti red
directions: Cook linguini according to package instructions; drain and keep warm.
Heat chili and 1/2 cup water together.
Pour over linguini noodles and sprinkle with Parmesan.
Serve sliced dill pickles and onion slices on the side.
Serves 3.

title: strawberry bread
directions: Combine dry ingredients; set aside.
Combine the rest of the ingredients and add to dry ingredients; add pecans.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Makes one large loaf or 3 small loaves.

title: cavatini
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In large pan, cook pasta until tender; drain.
Combine remaining ingredients except cheese in large bowl and mix well.
Add cooked pasta; mix well.
Place in large baking dish.
Bake, covered, with foil for 30 minutes or until bubbly. Remove from oven.
Sprinkle with Mozzarella cheese.
Return to oven until cheese melts.
Serves 8.

title: split pea soup
directions: Wash peas; look for floating things and pebbles.
Fill a pot with 6 cups of water; add 2 cups of peas.
Boil for 2 minutes. Cover and let stand for 1 hour; drain.
Add ham bone, onions and 4 cups water.
Bring to a boil and simmer 1 1/2 to 2 hours.
Remove bone; cut off ham and add some additional pieces.
Return to soup and add carrots and celery; season to taste.
Cook, uncovered, for 30 to 40 minutes.
Cool soup and remove fat.
Reheat and serve.

title: oriental slaw
directions: Mix oil, cider and brown sugar; set overnight.
Next day, add onions, noodles, slaw mix and sunflower seeds.
Toss lightly just before serving.

title: fried cabbage
directions: Combine all ingredients in an electric skillet.
Cook 25 minutes at 325°.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Cream together the cream cheese and powdered sugar.
Whip the whipping cream and fold into the cream cheese mixture until smooth.
Spread in baked pie shell.
Place whole, perfect strawberries into pie shell - points up and as close together as possible.
Melt the red currant jelly and pour over strawberries to form a glaze.
Refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: granny's fried chicken
directions: Cut up fryers.
Wash and drain well.
Mix milk and 1 teaspoon salt in a large container and place the chicken in the mixture. Refrigerate 2 to 3 hours.
Place flour and seasoning into a large plastic bag.
Shake to blend.
When ready to cook, shake several pieces of chicken in the bag at a time.
Heat oil until hot and place 4 to 5 pieces of chicken in the pan at a time.
Cook on high for a short time to brown, then turn heat to medium.
Cover pan and cook 5 to 7 minutes.
Turn chicken over and cook 5 to 7 minutes on the other side, covered.
Then turn heat up to complete browning other side.
Remove and drain well on paper towels. Serves 6.

title: apple bars
directions: Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Saut zucchini and onion in large pan.
Remove from heat. Add soup, sour cream and Stove Top.
Mix well.
Put casserole in baking dish.
Cut butter and put on top.
Bake at 350° until butter melts.

title: five cup salad
directions: Drain fruits; add coconut and sour cream. Mix, then chill 24 hours before serving.

title: tomato cream sauce
directions: In 3-quart saucepan cut up tomatoes to fill 1/2 to 3/4 full. Add one medium to large onion, sliced.
Add salt to taste.
Do not add water.
Cook, covered, or partially covered, over medium heat to render juice.
When thoroughly cooked, press through strainer to extract juice.
(Discard tomato and onion pulp.)
Brown 3 to 4 rounded to heaping tablespoonfuls of flour in small amount of bacon drippings.
Add this to tomato juice and stir over low heat to thicken.
Add sugar to taste.
Then add 1/2 cup of whipping cream and cook over low heat, stirring until smooth.

title: pumpkin spice cake
directions: Cream the shortening and sugar until fluffy. Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each. Combine the pumpkin and buttermilk or sour milk. Sift together the remaining ingredients. Add to the creamed mixture alternately with pumpkin mixture, beating well after each addition.
Bake in greased and floured 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes. Cool and frost.

title: light 'n fruity pie
directions: Dissolve gelatin completely in boiling water, stirring about 3 min. Add ice cubes, stir constantly until gelatin is thickened, about 2 to 3 min. Remove and unmelted ice cubes. Using wire whip, blend in whipped topping; then whip until smooth. Fold in strawberries and chill, until mixture will mound. Spoon into pie crust. Chill 2 hours. Garnish as desired. Any flavor Jello and fruit can be used. Also try Orange Jello with Mandarin Oranges.

title: nutter butter cake
directions: Put half crackers (crushed) in long dish.
Mix pudding with 3 cups milk.
Pour on top of crackers.
Top with Cool Whip.
Put remainder of crackers on top of Cool Whip.

title: ham salad
directions: Put on bun.
Heat in oven at 300° until cheese melts.

title: sour cream and garlic potato
directions: Boil and mash potatoes (don't add milk).
Add cream cheese and sour cream.
Sprinkle garlic to taste (lots of garlic).
Put in casserole dish and sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Refrigerate for 12 hours.
Bake with a pat of butter on 350° for 40 minutes.

title: lemon pepper corn-on-the-cob
directions: Melt butter; stir in mustard and horseradish, Worcestershire and lemon pepper.
Place each ear of corn on a 12 x 9-inch piece of foil; drizzle butter mixture over corn.
Fold edges of foil to seal pouch securely, leaving space for expansion of steam.
Grill over medium hot coals, turning occasionally, about every 15 minutes.

title: raw apple cake
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Spread in two 8-inch pans that have been greased and well floured.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: beans and cracked corn soup
directions: Pick corn and wash.
Soak overnight to soften.
Cook until soft.
Wash ham and boil until almost tender.
Pick beans and wash; let come to boil.
Drain water.
Cut ham into small pieces. Add ham, corn and ingredients in large pot with corn.
Add enough water to cover.
Cook on medium heat until beans are done and soup thickens, stirring constantly to avoid sticking to pot.
Before serving, add stick of margarine to pot.

title: butter apple squares
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Lightly spoon flour into cup; level off.
In large bowl, combine flour, sugar and oleo and stir in nuts.
Press 2 3/4 mixture into ungreased 13 x 9-inch pan.
To the remaining mix, add other ingredients; spoon evenly over base. Bake 25 to 30 minutes.
Cut into squares; serve with whipped cream.

title: chocolate pie no. 1
directions: Mix all ingredients except egg yolks in boiler on medium heat. Cook until mixture gets hot.
Take a little mixture and put it in a bowl; add egg yolks and mix well.
Pour back into the boiler and stir constantly until thick.
Pour into baked pie crust, then top with Cool Whip.
Add cherry in the center of the pie, then serve.

title: beef dip
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients in mixer; blend. Add olives and dried beef. Refrigerate and serve.

title: iceberg salad
directions: Start with lettuce and layer ingredients.
Refrigerate 24 hours.
Mix just before serving.

title: layered parmesan loaf
directions: Dip biscuits in melted butter or margarine and then in cheese. Arrange biscuits, overlapping in 2 rows on baking sheet.
Bake at 475° for 10 minutes or until a golden brown.

title: stay night potatoes
directions: Any vegetable tastes so much better if it is steamed slightly and not boiled to death.
Broccoli, cauliflower, carrots, yellow squash, green beans and asparagus are excellent.
May be served with melted cheese or Hollandaise Sauce, if you are allowed; however just plain or
a little lemon pepper is so good and so good for you.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Cook first eight ingredients with onion and butter for 20 minutes; add Worcestershire sauce and catsup.
Bring to a boil and simmer about 10 minutes.
Makes a very good barbecue sauce.

title: chicken asparagus casserole
directions: Cut chicken in bite size; sprinkle with Accent and pepper. Mix soup, mayonnaise, lemon juice and curry powder.
Layer asparagus, then chicken.
Spoon creamed mixture over asparagus and chicken.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Cover with lid or foil.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serve with Town House crackers.

title: pineapple supreme(club member: kristi mayfield)
directions: Grease a 9 x 9-inch dish. Pour in pineapple. Sprinkle box of cake mix. Pour butter on top. Cook for about 35 minutes at 350°.

title: buttermilk pancakes
directions: Mix together buttermilk and flour.
Add egg, salt, soda and butter.
Fry until desired brown on each side.

title: squash casserole
directions: Saute onions in margarine until tender.
In a baking dish, put a layer of cracker crumbs, a layer of squash, then pour half the onions and margarine over top.
Repeat layers.
Top with cracker crumbs.
Bake at 350° until crackers start to brown.

title: orange slice cookies
directions: Mix well. Drop by teaspoonful on greased cookie sheet. Bake 8 to 10 minutes at 350°.

title: dump salad
directions: Drain pineapple.
Place in large serving bowl.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well.

title: codfish cakes
directions: Make sure you boil fish thoroughly.
Then strip fine in a bowl. Cut up onions, pepper, scallion and hot pepper.
Then add all together in bowl with flour.
Mix in a batter.
Then put on a deep pot with oil to deep fry (medium fire).
When the pot is hot, take a pot spoon and drop in oil, must be brown to cook.
Then drain. After you taste, make sure it has the hot pepper taste.

title: zucchini parmesan
directions: Put zucchini, butter and seasonings in skillet.
Cover; cook slowly 5 minutes.
Uncover; cook, turning until tender (about 5 minutes more).
Sprinkle with cheese; toss.
(For added flavor, add 1 can tomato wedges and serve over rice.)

title: stuffed peppers
directions: Cut steak into cubes or fine strips.
Place in a skillet with about 1/4 c. water; salt and pepper, then cover.
Let simmer until done.
Meanwhile, cut tops of green pepper off and clean out each pepper.
Place some cheese in the bottom of each pepper.
When steak is done put about 1/4 c. steak into each pepper and top with cheese.
Keep layering pressing down on the cheese each time.
Once full, place each filled pepper onto a baking sheet or a deep pan which ever is preferred.
Place tops on peppers and cook on 300° until peppers begin to soften and cheese is melted.

title: hot apple cider eggnog
directions: Combine first 7 ingredients in a Dutch oven.
Cook over medium heat 10 minutes or until mixture reaches 160°.
Pour into mugs and top each serving with whipped cream.
Yields 2 quarts.

title: beans 'n wiener biscuit casserole
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
In medium saucepan combine wieners, pork and beans, ketchup, chopped onion and brown sugar.
Bring to a boil and simmer for 5 minutes.
Spoon hot bean mixture into ungreased 8 or 9-inch square pan.

title: pina colada cake
directions: Bake cake mix according to package directions in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Let cool and poke holes in top, then pour crushed pineapple over top including juice.
Prepare pudding according to package directions.
Spread over pineapple.
Let stand in refrigerator for 1 hour.
Spread Cool Whip on top of pudding.
Sprinkle coconut over Cool Whip.
May be topped with maraschino cherries.
Cover and refrigerate for 8 hours.
Keep refrigerated.

title: spaghetti corn
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350° in a covered casserole dish.
Uncover, stir and bake for another 30 minutes, uncovered.

title: easy rice pudding
directions: Prepare pudding according to package directions using the 1 1/2 cups of milk.
Fold in the whipped topping, rice, raisins and nutmeg.
Spoon into serving dishes.
Chill 1 hour or until serving time.
Makes 6 small servings.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Mix by hand, cheese, sugar and peanut butter.
Add Cool Whip last.
Pour
into two graham cracker pie shells and place in refrigerator.

title: sour cream pound cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar until light.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating thoroughly after each egg.
Sift dry ingredients; add to wet ingredients alternately with sour cream.
Bake in tube pan for 1 hour and 20 minutes at 350°.

title: wild rice and pecan dressing
directions: Wash wild rice in 3 changes of hot tap water.
Place in a medium-sized saucepan with water.
Simmer, covered, 45 minutes or until water is absorbed.

title: chocolate rebel bars
directions: Cream butter and sugar until light and fluffy.
Mix eggs and vanilla.
Sift together flour, soda and salt.
Stir in oatmeal, add dry ingredients to creamed mixture.
Set aside and make filling.

title: carrot apple cake
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients in a large bowl; blend thoroughly. Sift together dry ingredients.
Add to first mixture and mix well.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Grease and flour rectangular pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes until center of cake is firm.
Cool in pan.
(If two 9-inch layer pans are used, grease and wax paper line them.
Cool 10 minutes, then invert.)
When cool, frost with Pecan Cream Cheese Frosting.

title: good salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together and chill.

title: peach jello salad
directions: Dissolve jello as directed on package.
When partially chilled, add peaches.
Chill until firm.
When jello is firm, mix sour cream, softened cream cheese and sugar.
Cream until smooth and spread over salad.

title: macaroni salad
directions: Mix all ingredients; chill.

title: tortilla soup
directions: Brown hamburger and drain.
In large kettle, combine meat, tomatoes, chopped green chilies, broth and spices.
Simmer for 1 hour.
In serving bowl, break chips (approximately 1/4 cup per serving).
Ladle soup onto chips.
Sprinkle with shredded Mozzarella.
Serve with garlic toast.

title: soft gingerbread
directions: Mix the first 4 ingredients together and add soda and flour. Then add eggs.
Bake in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan at 350° for 30 minutes or until springs back like a cake.

title: lemon chicken
directions: Combine lemon juice and butter.
Salt chicken and place skin down in baking pan.
Pour 1/3 lemon juice and butter over chicken. Bake in a 375° oven for 20 minutes.
Turn chicken over.
Pour remainder of juice over chicken and bake 40 minutes longer. Baste occasionally.
Serve with rice or potatoes.

title: heavenly cake
directions: Mix all ingredients in a large bowl.
Stir all ingredients until creamy.
Add chocolate chips.
Pour into a 10-inch tube pan. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: oatmeal raisin cookies
directions: Simmer raisins in water for 20 to 30 minutes.
Cream shortening, sugar, eggs and vanilla together.
Add
1/2 cup water and raisin juice.
Blend in flour, baking powder, cinnamon, baking soda and cloves.
Add raisins, oats and chopped nuts.
Drop by rounded teaspoonful onto ungreased pan.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes until lightly brown. Bake at 400°.
Makes about 6 to 7 dozen.

title: fire and ice tomatoes
directions: Place all ingredients, except cucumbers, in bowl.
Prepare dressing by combining all other ingredients in saucepan and boiling for 1 minute.
While hot, pour over vegetables in bowl. Let stand until cool.
Just before serving, add the cucumbers. Serves 6.

title: special french dressing
directions: If you prefer, you can use an electric mixer.
In bowl, combine ingredients and beat until well blended and fairly thick. Store in quart jar in refrigerator.
Makes 1 quart.

title: breakfast souffle
directions: Brown crumbled meat; drain.
Mix eggs, milk, mustard and salt. Stir in bread cubes, sausage and cheese.
Pour into greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Refrigerate, covered, overnight.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 1 hour.

title: poppy seed bread
directions: Bake at 350° for 1 hour in greased tube tins.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour into an unbaked pie crust.
Bake at 450° for 10 minutes, then lower heat to 350° until firm and done.

title: southern biscuits
directions: Mix the first 4 ingredients.
Cut in shortening; rub by hand until crumbly.
Pour buttermilk into flour mixture and knead 3 to 4 times.
Roll dough to 1/4 to 1/2-inch thick.
Fold over and cut into 2 to 3-inch biscuits.
Bake in a 400° oven until very lightly browned.

title: dill weed dip
directions: Mix (stir well) all ingredients.
Refrigerate for at least two hours (overnight works well).
Serve with raw vegetables: celery, carrots, cauliflower, cucumber, tomatoes, etc.

title: grape-nuts bread
directions: Combine Grape-Nuts and milk and let stand 15 minutes.
Beat egg and sugar; add Grape-Nuts and shortening and mix well.
Sift together baking powder, soda and salt.
Add to Grape-Nuts mixture and beat.
Will be very stiff.
Turn out onto 2 greased loaf pans. Let stand 45 minutes, then bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: million dollar fudge
directions: Thoroughly mix the sugar, milk and butter.
Bring to a boil and boil 5 minutes, no longer, stirring constantly.
Have Hershey bars broken up and everything ready to put in.
Put chocolate chips in first, then stir in Hershey and then Marshmallow Creme. Add nuts last.
Pour batter into buttered pan.

title: apple crisp
directions: In a 9 x 13-inch ungreased pan, arrange peeled apples on bottom of pan with 2 tablespoons of water.
Sprinkle small amounts of sugar and cinnamon.

title: hush puppies *
directions: Mix all dry ingredients together.
Add onions, then milk, water and egg.
(Beat egg, then add milk and water.)
Roll into balls about 3/4-inch thick.
Cook in deep fat for about 5 to 7 minutes.
This batter may be stored in the refrigerator overnight. This makes 8 to 10 nice servings.

title: jack hudson's oxtail soup
directions: In pot cook oxtail with only enough water to cover meat at medium heat.
Dice potatoes.
Cut cabbage in quarters and slice thinly.
Dice tomatoes; cut off ends of okra and slice.
When oxtail is almost done, add potatoes, cabbage, tomatoes and cream-style corn.
Season to taste and cook at low heat until oxtail is done.

title: strawberry banana float
directions: Blend 1 1/2 cups ice cream with strawberries and banana in blender or electric mixer. Gradually add milk and orange juice. Pour into large glasses.
Top with scoops of remaining 1/2 cup ice cream.
Serves 3.

title: tightwad cocoa
directions: Mix the ingredients in a large bowl and store in covered container.
To prepare the hot cocoa, mix 3 to 4 tablespoons with 1 cup of hot water.
Serve with a dash of cinnamon or some marshmallows or both.

title: green tomato pickles
directions: Chop tomatoes, onions and green peppers.
Sprinkle with salt and let set overnight.
In the morning, pour cold water over and drain.
Put in kettle with vinegar and water (equal parts) to cover and boil 20 minutes.
Discard vinegar and water in whey have been boiled.

title: chocolate chip cake
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Pour into greased Bundt pan.
Bake about 45 to 50 minutes at 350°.
A very moist cake. (Good keeper.)

title: virginia cake
directions: Sift together dry ingredients, add eggs and pineapple, beat well.
Bake in 9 x 13 pan at 300 F for 50 minutes.

title: baked mashed potatoes
directions: Cook and mash potatoes. Add all ingredients. Mix well. Sprinkle with cheese. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: blueberry scone
directions: Mix and sift the dry ingredients together.
Cut in the shortening as for biscuits.
Add the beaten eggs and sour milk or buttermilk to make a soft dough.
Mix in the blueberries.
Bake in a greased 7 1/2 x 11 1/2-inch pan at 375° for about 30 minutes.

title: italian herb bread
directions: Sprinkle yeast from roll mix over warm water, stir to dissolve.
Blend in eggs, add remaining ingredients and roll mix. Beat 50 strokes.
Pour into greased 2 qt. loaf casserole.
Cover, let rise in warm place until double in size.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes or until deep golden brown.
Remove from pan immediately, cool on rack.

title: cajun deviled eggs
directions: Shell cooked eggs. Cut lengthwise into halves. Slip out yolks and mash with fork. Stir in mayonnaise and next five ingredients. Fill egg whites with yolk mixture, heaping lightly. Sprinkle with paprika and garnish with cilantro if desired. Makes 2 dozen.

title: vermicelli salad
directions: Cook and drain vermicelli; rinse with cold water.
Add olive oil to coat noodles.
Chop celery, green onion, black olives, green olives, Swiss cheese and lots of fresh garlic.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Toss all ingredients.
Refrigerate and keep covered.

title: zesty chili
directions: Brown meat with onion and green pepper.
Drain.
Add chili beans, stewed tomatoes and tomato juice until desired consistency is reached.
Use less juice for thicker chili.
Add chili powder to taste.
Simmer for 1 hour.
Serve with shredded Cheddar on top.

title: florida delight
directions: Mix flour,
margarine
and chopped nuts like pie crust. Pat into a 9
x
13-inch
baking pan and bake at 350° (325° if glass baking dish) for 20 to 25 minutes.
Let cool.

title: tom's plain tomato sauce
directions: In a pot, add 1 onion finely chopped to hot oil with a dash of butter until the onion turns yellow and soft.
Add 4 cans of tomatoes (2 crushed, 2 pear shaped) and a small amount of water, 1/2 cup or so.
Mash tomatoes with masher and add 1 1/2 teaspoons of basil and 1/2 teaspoon oregano to pot.
Bring to slight boil and simmer.
Chop up 3 cloves of garlic and add to sauce.
Add 1 tablespoon sugar and salt and pepper to taste.
Add a little more olive oil and cook on low for 1 1/2 to 2 hours.
Add more sugar if needed.

title: almond joy candy
directions: Mix sugar, karo and water. Cook to soft ball stage until sugar is dissolved. Add almonds, coconut and vanilla. Shape into balls. Melt chocolate bark and dip each ball in it.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Place in greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes, uncovered.
Serves 6.

title: "down east" applesauce cake
directions: Cream shortening and butter; stir in syrup.
Add the egg and beat well.
Put dates, raisin and nuts through food grinder.
Add to first mixture.
Sift dry ingredients together and combine with the mixture.
Blend in applesauce.
Bake in an 8 x 12-inch pan at 325° for 25 to 40 minutes.

title: low calorie orange salad
directions: Stir all together and refrigerate.

title: sweet and sour cabbage(norwegian)
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Bring to a boil and let simmer for 2 to 3 hours.
Very good with pork roast.

title: toasty cheese bake
directions: Heat oven to 300°.
Toast bread; butter both sides.
Cook and stir meat, onion, celery, prepared mustard and 1/2 teaspoon salt until meat is brown and onion is tender.
Alternate layers of toast, meat mixture and cheese in greased 9 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
Mix in remaining ingredients.
Pour over layers in pan.
Bake uncovered 30 to 35 minutes.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: pound cake
directions: Cream butter and Crisco.
Gradually add sugar, creaming well. Add eggs, 1 at a time, beating hard after each egg.
Add sifted dry ingredients with buttermilk.
Continue to beat.
Add flavorings.

title: rice pudding
directions: Mix sugar, rice and milk; boil 1 hour, stirring occasionally. Set aside.
Beat eggs; add leftover 1 cup milk plus vanilla.
Add to milk mix, slowly stirring.
Cool and serve topped with cinnamon or nutmeg.
Do not boil after egg mixture is added.

title: oregon bread
directions: Combine yeast, shortening, sugar, salt and 3 cups of the flour.
Heat milk to 120° to 130°.
Add milk and beat 200 strokes. Stir in as much of the remaining flour as possible.
Knead 10 minutes on floured surface.
Place in greased bowl, cover with damp towel and let rise until doubled, 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: snowballs
directions: Melt margarine over low heat.
Add marshmallows, vanilla and salt; stir until melted and well blended.
Divide mixture into 3 parts.
Tint each part with food coloring in separate bowls.
Pour each mixture over 1 quart of popped corn; toss lightly until well coated.
With hands slightly moistened with cold water, form into balls.
Makes 15 balls.

title: pot roast(a nice spicy type of pot roast)
directions: Dredge roast in flour and brown in cooking oil.
Add all ingredients and simmer for 2 1/2 hours, covered.
Serve in sauce surrounded by parsley.
After browning, it's great in a crock-pot on low.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: pickled cole slaw
directions: Place cabbage, pepper, onion and celery in alternate layers in large bowl and cover with sugar.

title: spanish rice
directions: In a deep skillet heat oil; add onions, tomato, green peppers, cilantro, garlic powder, salt, pepper, rice and tomato sauce.
Add water to just go over the rice.
Boil.
Cover on low heat for 15 minutes.
Stir; cover until done.
Serves 6.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli, drain. Mix all ingredients, except cheese. Pour into casserole dish and spread cheddar cheese on top. Bake at 375° for 30 - 40 minutes.

title: sweet and sour sausage
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Simmer soup mixture, salad dressing and preserves on stove top for 5 minutes.
Cool.
Put sausage in one quart casserole dish.
Pour cooled mixture over them. Marinate overnight.	Bake uncovered at 350° for 1 1/4 hours.
Yield 1 quart.

title: h.l.'s grated apple pie
directions: In a medium bowl, combine apples, egg, margarine, sugar, salt, flour and cinnamon.
Pour into an unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 350° until done or golden brown.

title: cereal killer cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
In a small bowl, mix the oats with the brickle chips.
Sift the flour, baking soda, baking powder and salt together.
In a food processor, mix the sugars until blended, then gradually add the butter.
Continue to process until creamy. Add the eggs and vanilla; process until blended.
Add the flour mixture and process just until combined.
Pour this mixture over the oats and brickle chips, stirring until well combined.
Place 2-inches apart on an ungreased cookie sheet, using a 2 tablespoon scoop.
Bake for 12 to 15 minutes or until golden brown.
Cool on wire racks.

title: pastor mark's potato pancakes
directions: Shred potatoes and onion in food processor.
Heat oven to 400 degrees.
Mix potato-onion mixture and remaining ingredients together.
Line baking pan or cookie sheet with sides with aluminum foil.
Spray with Pam.
Place mix onto foil and flatten out.
Make lines to define each section of pancake.
Cook 15 minutes, then flip over when firm.
Can use broiler if you want it crispy on top.

title: cool whip delight
directions: Drain crushed pineapple well.
Mix pineapple with Eagle Brand milk, cherry filling and pecans.
Add Cool Whip and coconut; stir completely.
Chill in refrigerator overnight.

title: eggs for brunch
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Put into a 9 x 13-inch buttered pan.
Refrigerate overnight.
In the morning, bake at 450° for 30 minutes or until set.

title: manicotti
directions: Mix cheeses, eggs, parsley, salt and black pepper.
Fill manicotti with cheese mixture.
(I slit manicotti to make this easier.)
Pour half of sauce into bottom of 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Top with single layer of filled manicotti.
Cover with sauce.
Bake at 400° for about 25 minutes.

title: mexican eggrolls
directions: You will need toothpicks.

title: baked corn chips
directions: Cut tortillas, several at a time, into 8 pie shaped wedges using kitchen shears.
Arrange in a single layer on cookie sheet. Bake at 350° until crisp and slightly browned (10 minutes).
Store in an airtight container.
Makes about 4 cups.

title: phyllis buchsbaum's chocolate chip cake
directions: Grease well and flour a Bundt pan.
Preheat oven to 350°. Combine cake mix, milk, oil, eggs and dry pudding.
Beat until well blended.
Coat chocolate chips with flour and fold chips and grated chocolate into batter.
Pour into Bundt pan and bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes, until toothpick comes out dry when inserted.
Cool cake and remove from pan.
Sprinkle top with confectioners sugar.

title: banana split dessert
directions: Mix 2 cups graham crumbs and 1 stick butter.
Pat this mixture into a 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: roast
directions: Pour onion soup in bottom of baking bag.
Put roast in; pour cream of mushroom soup and water.
Cook in a 350° oven for 3 hours.

title: lemon pound cake
directions: Cream margarine and shortening with sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Sift flour, baking powder and salt.
Add to creamed mixture alternately with milk.
Add extract.
Bake in a large tube pan at 350° for 55 to 60 minutes.
Glaze.

title: raisin cookies
directions: Cook raisins and water for 5 minutes; cool.
Cream the shortening and sugar.
Add eggs and beat well.
Add vanilla to mixture and beat well.
Add raisins and nuts.
Sift together the remaining ingredients and add to raisin mixture; blend well.
Drop by teaspoonful on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: zippy barbecued beef strips
directions: Partially freeze round steak and cut into strips 1/8 inch thick and approximately 3 inches long.
Combine flour, salt and pepper.
Dredge strips of beef in seasoned flour and brown lightly in cooking fat.
Pour off drippings.
Add water and onion, cover tightly and cook slowly 30 minutes.
Add barbecue sauce and sliced mushrooms, cover and continue cooking slowly 30 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Serve on hamburger buns.

title: grandma's white cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add eggs and continue to mix. Add dry ingredients alternately with milk.
Put some flour in a small bowl.
Drop batter by spoonfuls into flour in bowl and roll around with your fingers until dough is coated.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° about 10 minutes.
Frost when cool.

title: baked beans with beef
directions: Brown beef, onion and bell pepper and drain off fat.
Add beans, salt, mustard, sugar and Worcestershire sauce, mixing well. Top with bacon slices and a small amount of ketchup.
Bake in an open pan at 350° for about 1 hour.

title: seafood supreme
directions: Put lobster, shrimp, crab and chicken into large bowl.
Break up into bite-size pieces, removing cartilage.
Cover scallops with water in medium saucepan.
Boil 5 minutes and drain.
Cut in half and add to bowl.
Set aside.
In same saucepan, melt butter.
Stir in flour, mustard and salt.
Add milk.
Cook, stirring until mixture boils.
Add sour cream and sherry or wine.
Pour over contents in bowl.
Stir lightly to combine.
Pour into 2 1/2 quart (3L) casserole.

title: salmon loaf
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Pack lightly into a greased loaf pan (8 1/2 x 4 1/2 x 2-inches).
Bake at 350° about 1 hour.

title: boiled red apples
directions: Boil water, sugar, lemon juice and food coloring together. Add apples, bring to a boil again and simmer for 45 minutes.

title: lemon nut balls
directions: Mix dry milk and sugar in a 1-quart bowl.
Melt butter in a 2-quart saucepan over low heat.
Take from heat and stir in lemon juice.
Add sugar mixture, about 1/2 cup at a time, mixing until smooth each time.
Shape into 1-inch balls.
If too soft for shaping, chill until easily handled.
Roll balls in nuts.
Chill until firm.
Yields 2 1/2 dozen.

title: chocolate chip pie
directions: Put in an unbaked 9-inch pastry.
Bake at 325° for 55 to 60 minutes.
Best served warm.

title: quick barbecue
directions: Brown beef and onion, then add other ingredients.
Let simmer 20 minutes.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Mix together the mayonnaise, sugar, onion and vinegar or lemon juice.
Refrigerate for 1 hour.
Toss together the broccoli, walnuts and raisins.
Fry bacon.
Cool and then chop or crumble.

title: whole wheat oatmeal cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugars. Add eggs. Sift together flour, soda, salt, nutmeg and cinnamon. Add to creamed mixture. Stir in oats and walnuts. Add raisins. Drop by teaspoon onto greased cookie sheets. Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes. Cool on cookie sheets 2 minutes before removing to wire racks to cool. Makes 7 to 8 dozen.

title: chocolate cake(diabetic)
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Line an 8-inch round cake pan with paper; grease lightly with butter.
Sift first four ingredients together; blend in cocoa and coffee.
Beat egg, sweetener, water, oil and vanilla.
Stir into dry ingredients; mix until smooth. Pour in pan, cover with foil and place in shallow pan of water. Bake 30 minutes.
Remove from pan; cool and frost (see recipe for frosting).

title: hamburger pie
directions: In a large skillet, cook meat and onion until meat is lightly browned and onion is tender.
Add salt and pepper.
Add drained beans and soup.
Pour into greased 1 1/2-quart casserole.

title: vegetables vinaigrette
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients in 2-quart bowl or casserole. This is a basic vinaigrette excellent for salad dressing.

title: indian summer stir-fry
directions: Stir-fry first 3 ingredients in oil for 3 minutes, then add next 3 ingredients and stir-fry for another 3 minutes, covered. Then add last 3 ingredients and stir-fry another 3 minutes.
Do not overcook.

title: nut roll cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients thoroughly.
Form into 2 rolls.
Wrap in foil and store in freezer.
Slice in very thin slices and serve cold.
These rolls will keep indefinitely in freezer.

title: zucchini crabcakes
directions: Mix together and form patties. Roll in regular bread crumbs. Fry in electric frypan with a little oil. Serve with cocktail or tartar sauce.

title: pudding dessert
directions: Make the puddings and set aside.
Drain fruit cocktail, mandarin oranges and crushed pineapple.
Mix all ingredients together in a large bowl. Refrigerate before serving.

title: mexican chicken
directions: Heat oil.
Add chicken, onion and pepper.
Cook and stir until chicken is cooked clear through.
Add corn, broth and 1 cup medium salsa.
Bring to a boil.
Stir in rice.
Cover and remove from heat when comes to a boil again.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Fluff with fork.
Sprinkle cheese on top.
Cover and let stand 2 or 3 minutes, until cheese melts.

title: beer batter for fish
directions: Mix.
Let set 15 minutes.
Will set up on fish.

title: strawberry angel delight
directions: In large glass dish (13 x 9-inch), crumble cake (pack tightly).
In bowl, dissolve Jell-O in hot water and stir.
Add sugar and strawberries.
Pour mixture over crumbled cake (evenly). Spread Cool Whip over entire surface and refrigerate overnight (or at least 6 hours, until set).
Cut in squares and serve. Yields 20 squares.

title: banana split cake
directions: First Layer:
Put in the bottom of a pan the graham cracker crumbs, 1 stick melted butter and 1/4 cup sugar.

title: chocolate salad dressing cake
directions: Mix in order listed.
Grease and flour pan.
Bake very slowly (350°) about 20 minutes.

title: dishpan cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Make into balls; press with fork.
Bake at 350°.

title: peppy spread
directions: Mix all ingredients and chill.
Serve on assorted crackers.

title: cabbage with creamed celery
directions: Cook cabbage in lightly salted water until tender-crisp about 10 minutes.
Drain.
Mix together soup and milk.
Heat just below boiling, stirring often.
Remove from heat; add cheese.
Place cabbage in warmed serving dish; pour sauce over.
Makes 4 servings.

title: elephant stew
directions: Cut elephant into small bite-size pieces.
This will take about 2 months.
Add enough brown gravy to cover.
Cook over kerosene fire for 4 weeks at 450°.

title: rice krispies treats
directions: Put sugar and corn syrup in large pan and bring to boil over medium heat, stirring constantly. Remove from heat. Add peanut butter and stir well. Add rice krispies and mix well. Put in 9 x 13 pan. Top with melted chocolate chips.

title: cracker cake
directions: Crush crackers very fine; add 1 cup sugar, baking powder and pecans.
Beat egg whites until soft peaks form.
Add cream of tartar and add rest of sugar; beat until stiff.
Fold the dry ingredients in egg whites.
Pour into well-greased pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes or golden brown.
Remove cake after cooling, chill.
Frost with Cool Whip.
Spread top with pineapple, then cover with coconut and candied cherries.

title: orange chocolate chip cookies
directions: Mix together butter, cream cheese, sugar, egg, grated orange rind and vanilla.
Sift flour and salt together.
Add to batter, mixing thoroughly.
Next, add chocolate chips and stir in, mixing well.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto lightly greased baking sheet, 1-inch apart.
Bake at 350° for about 15 minutes.

title: chicken-marinated baked
directions: In a measuring cup, combine salad dressing and soy sauce. Pour 3/4 cup into a large, resealable plastic bag. Add chicken. Seal the bag and turn to coat. Refrigerate for 4 hours or overnight, turning several times. Refrigerate remaining marinade for basting.

title: chocolate gravy
directions: Dissolve cocoa, flour and sugar in 1/2 cup of water, then add other cup of water.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: In 9 x 13-inch pan, spray Pam on bottom.
Layer in order. Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: pineapple cake
directions: Cream shortening and sugar; stir in eggs. Sift flour, soda and baking powder together and add alternately with buttermilk to shortening mixture.
Add vanilla extract.
Bake in two 8-inch greased and floured cake pans.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Add pineapple frosting.

title: potato chip cookies
directions: Beat margarine, eggs and sugar until well blended. Stir in remaining ingredients and mix well. Shape into 3/4 inch balls and place 2 inches apart on greased cookie sheet.

title: turkey breast a la gretchen
directions: Empty turkey breast cavity and rinse the breast.
Melt the butter.
Add the wine, thyme, salt, and pepper.
Shake the flour in
a large size cooking bag.
Pour the butter mixture into the bag and place the turkey breast in the bag.
Follow the cooking bag's instructions in the top.
Turkey does not need any basting. Cook at 350° for 2 1/2 hours.

title: mom's chili
directions: Cook beef, onion and salt together until meat loses redness and browns some.
Combine all other ingredients and simmer until done.

title: strawberry angel food cake
directions: Mix strawberries, Jell-O and water.
Cut out the center of the cake and break up into pieces.
Add the strawberry mixture.
Stuff back into cake and refrigerate.
Cover with pink whipping cream.

title: sausage 'n' cheese skillet
directions: In large skillet, brown sausage; drain.
Add onion, green pepper and garlic; cook and stir until tender.
Add tomatoes, juice, mushrooms, bouillon and seasonings; mix well.
Simmer, uncovered, 30 minutes.
Stir in 1/2 cup cheese; heat through. Serve with chips and remaining cheese.
Refrigerate leftovers.

title: grandma zimmerman's monster cookies
directions: Combine sugars, peanut butter and margarine.
Add eggs; beat until creamy, then add oatmeal, baking soda and salt.
Add chocolate chips and M&M's.

title: four layer chocolate delight
directions: Mix together flour, sugar, 1/2 c. nuts and margarine.
Spray the bottom and sides of a 9 x 13 in. baking dish with cooking spray and spread crust in bottom.
Bake for 15 min at 375 degrees. Combine cream cheese, 1 cup Cool Whip and powdered sugar together to form second layer.
Spread over cooled bottom layer.
Follow directions on pudding box using 2 3/4 cups milk instead of 4 cups as called for.
Spread over second layer.
Cover with remaining Cool Whip and sprinkle remaining nuts for fourth layer. Refrigerate.

title: tofu lasagne
directions: If you haven't thawed your tofu, do it in microwave, while noodles are cooking.
Wring out tofu like a sponge to get rid of liquid.
Chop it in chunks and put it into blender or food processor.
Add Ricotta, parsley and milk until smoothly mixed.

title: peanut chunkies
directions: Mix dry ingredients together; beat butter, egg, sugars and peanut butter until light and fluffy.
Mix with dry ingredients. When dough is well mixed, pinch off pieces and roll between palms into cylinders.
Roll cylinders in nuts.
Place 2 inches apart on lightly greased cookie sheet.
Bake 10 minutes at 375°.

title: spicy apple pie
directions: Fill pie shell with sliced apples.
Mix sugar, spices, salt and lemon juice and sprinkle over the apples.
Dot with butter. Moisten pie crust edges with water.
Fit top crust over the apples and seal the edges of the pie.
Bake at 425° for 30 to 40 minutes. Make sure you cut slits in the top of the top pie crust.

title: kraft mac and cheese pizza
directions: Prepare dinner as directed on package.
Add eggs, mix well. Spread into well-greased 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes.
Spoon pizza sauce over dinner mixture.
Top with meat and cheese.
Continue baking until cheese is melted.

title: microwave tortilla dogs
directions: Place cheese on wiener on tortilla.
Roll up; secure with toothpick.
Microwave on paper towel on High for 45 seconds or until cheese is melted and wiener is hot.
Serve with salsa. Makes 1 serving.

title: coffee cake
directions: Mix the last 3 ingredients for filling.
Mix remaining ingredients; spread 1/3 batter (about 2 cups).
Add 1/3 of filling.
Spread rest of batter.
Top with the rest of the filling.
Bake at 350°.

title: apple fritters
directions: Combine
flours, powder, salt, sugar and cinnamon.
Mix together eggs,
milk
and oil.
Core and finely chop apples to measure 1
cups.
Add	apples and raisins to liquid.
Add dry ingredients and mix well until thoroughly moistened.

title: pecan fingers(makes  4 to 5 dozen)
directions: Melt butter and add all other ingredients; mix thoroughly. Mold into finger-shapes or balls.
Bake at 325° for 20 minutes. Remove and roll in confectioners sugar twice.
Enjoy!
Mmm!

title: grandma's casserole
directions: Saute onion in butter for 3 minutes.
Add hamburger and brown meat as it cooks.
Add salt, pepper and sugar.
Stir in tomatoes, tomato sauce and water.
Heat mixture to boiling, reduce heat and simmer 15 minutes.
Into a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan, layer tomato mixture and uncooked wide noodles.
Top with sliced Mozzarella. Make sure noodles are well covered with sauce.
Cover pan with aluminum foil and bake in preheated oven (350°) for 45 minutes. Cut and serve as you would lasagna.

title: stuffed mushrooms
directions: Wash mushrooms and remove stems.
Fry and drain sausage.
Cube and add Velveeta cheese until melted.
Spoon mixture into mushroom bottoms.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: easy cookie
directions: Mix all. Drop by teaspoon on cookie sheet and bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: huevos con chiles
directions: In a bowl, beat together eggs, milk, salt and pepper.
Stir in diced green chiles. Set aside.
In skillet, melt oleo over medium heat and cook onion until soft. Add egg-chile mixture and cook, stirring occasionally, until done as desired. Serves 3 to 6.

title: punch bowl cake
directions: Bake cake in a 9 x 13-inch pan following directions on box of mix.
After cake has cooled, cut in half and break into chunks. Place half of cake pieces in punch bowl.
Layer half of pineapple, pie filling and whipped topping over cake.
Repeat, ending with whipped topping.

title: pecan supreme
directions: 1st Layer:
Mix flour, margarine and pecans to a crumbly mixture.
Press into a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes.
Cool.

title: microwave potato chips
directions: Spray a dinner plate with Pam.
Place slices on plate in a single row.
Microwave on High for 4 minutes.
Turn slices over and continue to microwave on High another 3 to 5 minutes.
Potatoes are done when lightly browned.
If they aren't browned, they won't get crisp.
This may take longer depending on your microwave's wattage, but you'll be safe with the initial 4 minutes of cooking. You need to watch them carefully after that.
Now comes the hard part.
Remove from plate and toss in a bowl with salt or seasoning of your choice and let cool!
It's important to let cool so they can crisp up.

title: mr. rogers' snack(a kid-pleasing snack)
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients and form into bite-sized balls. Roll balls in graham cracker crumbs.
Store in plastic container in layers on waxed paper in refrigerator.

title: blue ribbon gingersnaps(maryland state fair 1st place winner)
directions: Cream the Crisco, brown sugar, egg and molasses.
Mix the remaining ingredients.
Combine. Cover and chill 1 hour or overnight. Shape into balls. Roll balls in sugar. Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: baked chicken breast
directions: Line a pan with foil. In a bowl, mix cheese, parsley, garlic, salt, and pepper. Dip chicken breast in melted margarine then, dip breasts in cheese mixture then, dip the breasts in corn flake crumbs. Roll into tight rolls and fasten with toothpicks; put in baking dish; spoon broth over chicken. Bake uncovered for 1 hour at 350°. Baste several times during cooking with broth.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Cook chicken (boil).
Saute green peppers and onions in margarine until tender.
Cook the spaghetti in the chicken broth (4 cups).
Do not drain.
Add peas, tomatoes, pimentos, cheese, diced chicken, mushrooms, black olives, peppers and onions.
Add salt and pepper.
Put in casserole dish and bake 30 minutes at 325°.
Enjoy!!!

title: quick chicken and stuffing
directions: In a large bowl, combine croutons, broth, carrots, celery, onion and herbs. Spoon stuffing mixture down center of a 13 x 9-inch baking dish. Mix soup, milk, parsley and pepper in a medium bowl; spoon 1/2 the soup mixture on each side of stuffing. Place chicken breasts over soup, overlapping if necessary. Pour remaining soup mixture over chicken. Sprinkle with paprika. Bake covered for 20 minutes at 400°; uncover and bake 10 minutes longer. Makes 6 servings.

title: baked french toast
directions: Melt oleo in 9 x 13 pan.
Mix brown sugar and cinnamon together.
Add brown sugar mixture to melted oleo.
Cover with 2 layers of bread slices.
Combine eggs, milk and salt.
Pour over bread.
Cover and chill overnight in fridge.
Uncover and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Cut in squares and turn upside down on a plate to serve.
Serve with butter or syrup.

title: mary's divine bean dip
directions: Mix all together and chill.
Eat with potato chips or taco chips.
You can't go wrong on this dip.
You can vary from the recipe to suit your taste buds.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Mix with a mixer; shape into a ball, or put in crock.

title: carrot-raisin salad
directions: Mix ingredients; let stand in refrigerator at least 2 hours.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Cook spaghetti according to package directions.
Drain. Combine all ingredients, except part of cheese.
Pour into casserole dish and top with remaining cheese.
Heat in 350° oven until hot and bubbly.

title: hot corn casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Butter 1 1/2-quart souffle dish.
Mix all ingredients and bake for a minimum of 30 minutes.

title: baked pork chops with beans
directions: Season chops with salt and pepper and brown well in pan. Place in shallow baking dish.
Dot with butter.
Mix all ingredients and pour over chops.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: savory minestrone soup
directions: Slice sausage into 1/4 inch pieces.
Brown lightly in oil in large soup pot.
Stir often to prevent sticking and burning.
Add onion, garlic, carrots and zucchini.
Cook for 5 minutes, stirring frequently.
Add broth, soup and water and bring to a boil.
Stir in beans and pasta and reduce heat to low.
Simmer about 15 minutes or until the pasta is cooked.
Stir occasionally.
Yield:
4 to 6 servings.

title: baked ziti
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
Mix cooked ziti, 1 cup marinara sauce, 1/2 cup Mozzarella and all the Ricotta and Parmesan.
Top with remaining sauce and Mozzarella.
Cover and bake for 45 minutes. Serves 6.

title: quick swedish meatballs
directions: Mix beef with egg, crumbs, sage, salt, pepper and milk.
Shape into balls; brown on all sides in hot fat in skillet.

title: sherry pecan cake
directions: Mix altogether; bake at 350° for 1 hour and 10 minutes.
Cool 10 minutes in pan.

title: apple upside-down cake
directions: Melt 1/2 cup butter in saucepan or microwave.
Stir in 1/2 cup brown sugar and cinnamon.
Pour half of this mixture into each of 2 round cake pans.
Peel and core apples.
Slice lengthwise into even slices with lemon juice.
Arrange slices in pattern on top of brown sugar mixture in pans.
Prepare cake mix according to package directions.
Divide batter evenly in pans.
Bake
at 375° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Immediately turn each pan over onto serving dish.
Do not remove pans for about 15 minutes.
Serve with ice cream if desired.

title: beef kabobs
directions: Combine in medium bowl the oil, vinegar, lemon juice, mustard, soy sauce, salt, garlic powder, pepper, bay leaf and 1 medium chopped onion; add in 1-inch cube beef.
Let soak at least 6 hours.
Place beef on broiler pan, then add cut-up pepper, mushrooms, onion and tomatoes.
Broil until done.
Serve over rice.

title: barbecue beans
directions: Brown beef and drain.
Fry bacon and crumble.
Mix remaining into meat mixture and pour into 9 x 13 pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes.
Don't overbake.

title: dinette cake
directions: Sift together the flour, sugar and baking powder.
Add remaining ingredients, except egg.
Beat vigorously with spoon for 2 minutes or with electric mixer on slow to medium for 2 minutes. Add unbeaten egg and beat 2 more minutes.
Pour into greased Bundt pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
After cake is cooled, may dust with powdered sugar.

title: cape cod clam chowder
directions: Discard tough part of clam stomach and neck.
Chop remaining part.
Fry salt pork and remove pork.
Add water, clam liquor, potatoes and onion to fat. Cook 15 minutes.
Add clams. Cook until clams and potatoes are tender.
Add milk and butter.
Heat through, but do not boil.
Add salt pork and season to taste. Canned clams and broth may be used in this recipe.
Makes 8 servings.

title: easy salad
directions: Grate carrots; use Angel Flake coconut.
Add all ingredients and mix together.
Needs no dressing.
Pineapple juice is dressing.
This salad will keep for many days.

title: mrs. field's cookies
directions: Combine flour, soda, and salt with whisk.
Set aside.
Use an electric mixer to blend sugars.
Add butter and mix to form a grainy paste.
Blending at medium speed, add eggs and vanilla (do not overmix).
Add flour mixture and chocolate chips at a low speed.
Bake on an ungreased cookie sheet at 300° for 22 to 24 minutes or until golden brown using rounded tablespoonfuls, 2-inches apart.

title: p.c.'s mustard
directions: Cook over low heat while stirring until thickened.
This is very nice to give at Christmas.
(Sweet Mustard)

title: chili with pork and beans
directions: Fry
hamburger	until brown.
Add onion.
Add remaining ingredients,
except pork and beans.
Just before serving, add pork and beans.
Simmer for a few minutes.	Serve over rice.

title: broccoli-rice casserole
directions: Steam packages of broccoli.
Cook rice on package as directed. Combine broccoli and rice in a 13 1/2 x 8 3/4 x 1 3/4-inch pan. Mix cream of chicken and cream of mushroom soups and stir.
Pour in about 1/2 can of water and add 1/2 block cubed cheese.
Stir and mix all these together.
Bake at 350°
for 10 to 20 minutes.

title: sugar and molasses cookies
directions: Soften the shortening and add sugar, molasses, cloves, ginger and cinnamon.
Add egg; beat well.
Sift together flour, salt and soda.
Add to first mixture.
Chill and make into 1-inch balls. Flatten and bake at 375° about 10 minutes.
Serves 36.

title: freezer slaw
directions: Shred cabbage, green pepper and onion.
Add sugar.
Mix and set aside.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Mix first four ingredients and set aside.
Sift remaining ingredients.
Mix well with liquid.
Grease pan.
Bake at 350° for 70 minutes.
Bake at 350° for about 15 to 18 minutes or until done for muffins.

title: broccoli casserole 1
directions: Thaw broccoli in hot water and drain well.
In skillet, saute chopped onion and chopped celery in margarine until soft. In a large bowl, put broccoli, onion and celery. Stir well. Add celery soup.
Add uncooked instant rice. Stir to mix well.
Last, add Cheez Whiz and stir.
Put in baking dish with cover and bake for 45 minutes at 375° in a preheated oven.

title: philadelphia cream cheese cookies
directions: Mix the first 3 ingredients into a dough (by hand).
Store in refrigerator overnight or until ready to bake.
Roll 1/4 of the dough at a time on floured table into a thin sheet.
Cut into approximately 3 1/2-inch squares.
Put a teaspoon of preserves in center of each square.
Fold diagonally over preserves.
Press in edges.
Roll and form into crescent shape.
Bake on cookie sheet at 325° until very light brown (approximately 8 to 10 minutes). Remove from cookie sheet onto wax paper.
Sift powdered sugar onto warm cookie.
After cooling, store in plastic covered container. Makes about 8 dozen crescents.

title: hot rolls
directions: Stir 1 cup hot water with the sugar, salt and oil.
Add the warm water and cold water. Stir, then add the yeast.
Add plain flour until thick. Cover with dry towel and let rise until double in size.
Knead together and make into rolls.
Let rise again. Bake at 450° for about 20 minutes.

title: quick delicious baked chicken
directions: Pour chicken soup, mixed with sour cream, over chicken. Sprinkle cracker crumbs and poppy seed over chicken mixture.
Melt butter and pour over top.
Bake in a 350° oven for 30 to 40 minutes.
Serve with broccoli and rice.

title: family pie
directions: Mix together smoothly with complete faith in God.
Add 2 tablespoons wisdom, 1 teaspoon of good nature for flavor, and 1 pound laughter for spice.
Sprinkle generously with thoughtfulness and serve with kind words.

title: vegetable bars
