directions: Cover bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan with rolls.
Bake per directions.
Mix cream cheese, mayo and salad dressing.
Spread evenly over cooled rolls.
Top with any selection of fresh vegetables.
Top vegetables with shredded Mozzarella cheese. (Best prepared the night before using.)

title: hardy biscuit
directions: Put yeast in warm water and set aside.
Measure flour, sugar and soda.
Mix well then add liquid.
Mix and wait 15 minutes. Cook what you want and put remainder in tight covered bowl and refrigerate.
Will keep for 2 weeks.

title: egg puffs
directions: Boil eggs and cool.
Remove shells and rinse.
Chop finely and place in a small bowl.
Add deviled ham, mayonnaise and Cajun seasoning.
Mix well; set aside.
Remove crust from bread slices. Cut into halves.
Spread 1/4 teaspoon softened butter on each half.
Place each half slice in separate cup of a mini-muffin pan, conforming to cup shape.
Fill each slice with one tablespoon of egg and ham mixture.
Garnish with paprika.
Broil about 5 to 6 inches from heat until bread is toasted and filling is heated, about 3 minutes.
Serves 12.

title: jello salad with topping
directions: Dissolve jello in hot water.
Add pineapple juice and pineapple.
Add bananas; let set.

title: potatoes and hamburger
directions: Saute onion and cook hamburger; drain.
In a baking dish, mix onion, hamburger and soup.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Lay Tots on top. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until cheese bubbles and Tots are cooked.

title: bible study delight
directions: Cream margarine and butter with sugar.
Add egg, then vanilla and flour.
Put 2/3 of batter in 9 x 13-inch greased pan.
Spread pie filling over batter, then dab or glob the remaining batter over filling.
Bake at 350° for approximately 30 to 35 minutes or until lightly browned.

title: pound cake
directions: Sift dry ingredients 3 times.
Cream shortening and sugar; add eggs one at a time.
Add dry ingredients alternately with milk, beginning and ending with flour.
Add flavoring.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: grandma jean's egg nog pie
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients together.
Allow to set in refrigerator.
When set, fold in Cool Whip.
Place in baked shell. Sprinkle with nutmeg.
Chill and serve.

title: donna's dessert
directions: First Layer:
Mix butter, flour and walnuts.
Put into a 9 x 13-inch pan and bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes. Cool.

title: broccoli-potato casserole
directions: Layer broccoli, cheese and potatoes in casserole dish. Crumble crackers on top.
Melt margarine and pour on top of crackers.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: family chicken
directions: Cook chicken breasts in water.
Add pinch of rosemary, drained mushrooms, one can cream of mushroom soup, salt and pepper.
Cook down for 15 minutes with low temperature on range.

title: grandma murdock's chocolate pie
directions: Mix all ingredients, except butter.
Cook in saucepan over medium heat until thick.
Add butter.
Pour into a baked pie shell.

title: cheezy apples
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine sugar, flour, margarine, evaporated milk and cheese.
Pour sliced apples into casserole dish and cover with cheese mixture.
Bake for 45 minutes.

title: italian asparagus
directions: Cook asparagus until tender; drain.
Place in casserole dish. Melt margarine and add soup mix.
Pour this mixture over asparagus.
Cover with Mozzarella cheese and Parmesan.
Bake 10 minutes at 450°.

title: fabulous fudge cake
directions: Melt chocolate over hot water.
Cream oleo, adding sugar gradually.
Beat in eggs, one at a time.
Stir in vanilla and chocolate.
Alternately add flour and milk.
Stir in water.
Bake at 375° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Makes two 9-inch layers.

title: mexican fish fillets
directions: Arrange fish on an ungreased 8 x 8-inch baking dish.
Combine vegetable juice, cilantro, garlic salt and lemon juice and pour over fish. Cover and bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Uncover and bake until fish fillets flake easily with a fork (10 to 15 minutes). Serve with Jalapeno Tomato Sauce.

title: garlic spread
directions: Combine all ingredients in a small bowl, stirring until well blended.
Cover and chill thoroughly.
Serve spread with crackers or fresh raw vegetables.

title: cocoa brownie drops
directions: Beat softened margarine at medium speed of an electric mixer until creamy.
Gradually add sugars, beating well.
Add egg substitute, 1/4 cup at a time, beating well after each addition. Combine flour, baking soda, salt and cocoa.
Add to margarine mixture, stirring just until blended.
Stir in miniature chocolate chips.
Drop cookie dough by level teaspoon, 2-inches apart onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 6 minutes.
Remove from cookie sheets and let cool on wire racks.
Yields 4 dozen.

title: hawaiian salad
directions: Sauce:
Mix sugar, flour and 1/2 teaspoon salt.
Add pineapple juice and eggs.
Cook until thick.
Add lemon juice and cool.

title: chili
directions: Brown beef, onion and garlic.
Drain off fat.
Stir remaining ingredients.
Mix and simmer.

title: quick and easy pie
directions: Mix Eagle brand and cool whip until smooth.
Add 1 1/2 c. cool whip, pudding, and water.
Mix until smooth.
Pour into crust.
Refrigerate one hour then top with remaining cool whip. Refrigerate for two hours.

title: pecan pie
directions: Cream margarine and sugar.
Add eggs.
Beat and add syrup and vanilla.
Beat thoroughly.
Add nuts.
Pour into pie shell.
Start oven at 375°, then turn to 300°.
Bake until firm.

title: microwaved broccoli-stuffed vidalia onions
directions: Remove stem and root ends of Vidalia, then cut in half and carefully press out center rings, leaving a 2 to 3 ring shell. Place shells in baking dish and set aside.
Chop the removed portion of Vidalias and set aside.

title: pork chops supreme
directions: In a 9 x 13-inch casserole, place sliced potatoes until the pan is 1/2 full.
Brown 8 pork chops and season with salt and pepper.
Mix together 1 can cream of celery soup, evaporated milk and onions.
Pour over chops which have been placed on top of potatoes.
Sprinkle grated cheese on top.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: clam chowder
directions: Drain clams; pour the juice over vegetables.
Cover with water.
Cook over medium heat until tender.
In saucepan, melt butter.
Add flour and blend until smooth.
Add half and half a little at a time.
Do not drain vegetables.
Add sauce.
Heat through.
Cool.
Reheat.

title: vidalia onion pie
directions: Saute onions in melted margarine or in microwave in broth (toss to coat; separate).
Cook until transparent.
Mix in bowl the yogurt, mayo, Scramblers, bacon bits, chives and thyme; season with a dash of salt and pepper.
Stir in onions.
Pour into crust. Sprinkle with small amount of Parmesan cheese if desired.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: savory cheese bites
directions: Combine water, butter and salt in a pan; bring to a boil. Stir until butter melts.
Add flour.
Stir vigorously until mixture leaves sides of pan to form a smooth ball.
Remove from heat.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Stir until well blended.
Return to heat and beat mixture until smooth.
Remove from heat; stir in cheese.
Drop batter by heaping teaspoonfuls onto a greased baking sheet.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes or until puffed and golden brown.

title: braised bear
directions: Cut meat into bite-size portions.
Roll in flour seasoned with salt, garlic powder, paprika, parsley and pepper.
Brown in oil and add carrots, onion and green pepper; brown these.
Add tomatoes and simmer for 2 hours until meat is tender.
Serve over rice.

title: baked beans
directions: Mix all together and bake, covered, at 400° for 30 minutes.

title: fruit cocktail pie
directions: Mix flour, sugar and liquid and bring to boil over medium heat, stirring constantly.
Pour small amount of hot mixture into beaten egg yolks, stir then add back to hot mixture and bring to boil.
Add fruit and stir until mixed.
Pour into 9-inch baked pie shell.
Top with meringue.
Bake in oven at 350° until lightly brown.
Chill for 4 hours and serve.

title: old-fashioned apple pie
directions: Preheat oven and baking sheet to 400°.
Remove pie crusts from freezer.
Invert 1 crust onto wax paper and allow to thaw until flat.
Trim the crimped edge off after crust is flattened.
In a large bowl, combine dry ingredients.
Add apples; stir until evenly coated.
Spoon into bottom crust; dot with butter.
Place top crust over apples.
Recrimp edges to hold both crusts.
Cut several slits in top crust.
Bake on preheated baking sheet 40 to 45 minutes.
Serve warm or cold.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Brown hash browns and onions in oil. Place in 9 x 13 baking dish. Mix sour cream and soup; pour over hash brown mixture. Sprinkle cheese. Mix cereal and butter and sprinkle over top. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: salmon salad
directions: Combine salmon, mustard, lemon juice, eggs, mayonnaise, pepper and dill pickle in a medium mixing bowl, stirring well. Cover and refrigerate
until chilled.
Cut each tomato into 8 wedges, cutting
to,
but not through, base of tomato.
Spread wedges apart
to form a shell.
Spoon salmon salad into tomato shells. Top
with
a
dollop
of
mayonnaise;
sprinkle
with paprika. Serve on lettuce lined plates.
Yield: 6 servings.

title: rice pudding
directions: Cook rice until done.
Rinse in strainer with warm water. Beat eggs and add remaining ingredients.
Put rice in casserole dish.
Pour egg mixture over rice and stir.
Place casserole dish, uncovered, in a pan of water and bake at 350°.
Stir every 15 minutes until skin forms.
(Bake for about 1/2 hour more after skin forms.)
Sprinkle with nutmeg.
Great served with baked ham. Total baking time is about 1 1/2 hours.

title: peanut butter eggs
directions: Mix all together but milk, then add milk slowly as needed. Roll into balls; shape like egg.

title: dinner in a dish
directions: Put shortening in skillet and lightly fry pepper and onion for 3 minutes. Add seasonings and meat. Remove from fire. Stir in eggs and mix well. Put 1 cup of corn in casserole, then half of meat mixture and a layer of sliced tomatoes. Repeat layers and cover with crumbs. Dot with bits of butter. Bake in oven at 375° for 1 hour. Will serve 4.

title: spinach loaf
directions: Place the olive oil, diced onion, leaf lettuce and Mozzarella cheese on top of bread.
Roll it up and seal edges with water. Bake in foil at 350° for 45 minutes.
Let it cool and serve.

title: creamy peanut butter sandwiches
directions: Put spoonfuls of peanut butter in a bowl.
Put in 2 teaspoons of milk.
Beat together, putting milk in 1 teaspoon at a time. Beat each time until peanut butter is creamy.
Spread on bread. Sliced fruit such as strawberries or bananas can be added for extra special taste.
Also a jam or jelly spread would be nice for change of taste.

title: energy bars
directions: Melt butter, peanut butter and marshmallows.
Add oats, unsalted peanuts, raisins and Rice Krispies.
Spread mixture in buttered pan.
Cut and wrap in waxed paper.
Pan size: 9 x 13-inch.

title: meat loaf-meatballs
directions: Beat eggs well.
Add milk, onion, salt, nutmeg, sage, pepper, ground beef, ground pork and bread crumbs.
Mix well with your hands, keeping it light.
Shape into a meat loaf and cover with a sauce of brown sugar, mustard, catsup and garlic.
Bake at 350° for about 1 hour.

title: ranch wings
directions: Heat hot sauce, margarine and vinegar in a bowl.
Dip in sauce.
Lay wings on cookie sheet and sprinkle with Ranch dressing.
Bake at 300° for approximately 1 hour.

title: microwave baked apples
directions: Core as many apples as desired to bake.
Also, peel skin from around 1/2 to 1/4-inch around top side of core.
Place apples in microwavable dish.
Place 1 to 2 tablespoons (depending on how sweet the apples are) cinnamon sugar in the core hole of each apple (1/4 cup for 4 apples).
Put 1 to 2 tablespoons of water (with a little sugar in it) per apple into the dish (1/4 cup for 4 apples).
Microwave with lid on (or microwavable plastic wrap on top) for 5 to 10 minutes (4 apples) on High power or until the apples are tender.
If after 5 minutes not much water has cooked out the apples, you may want to put 1 to 2 tablespoons more water per apple.
Let apples stand a few minutes before serving with whipped cream, milk, vanilla ice cream or a marshmallow on top!

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Melt 1/4 cup butter in a large heavy saucepan over low heat and whisk in all-purpose flour.
Cook, whisking constantly, 1 minute. Gradually whisk in chicken broth and milk; cook over medium heat, whisking constantly, until mixture is thickened and bubbly.
Add salt and pepper.
Melt 2 tablespoons butter in a skillet over medium-high heat; add mushrooms, onion and celery.
Saut until tender.
Drain.
Stir vegetable mixture, chopped cooked chicken and chopped egg into sauce.
Fit 1 pie crust into a 9-inch deep dish pie plate according to package directions.
Spoon filling into crust; top with remaining pie crust.
Trim off excess pastry.
Fold edges under and crimp.
Cut slits in top.
Bake at 375° for 30 to 40 minutes or until top is golden.
Shield edges with strip of aluminum foil during last 10 minutes to prevent excessive browning.

title: sausage and cheese balls
directions: Combine all ingredients in large bowl and mix well.
Shape into balls and place on baking sheet.
Bake at 400° for about 20 minutes or until brown.
Makes 3 dozen.

title: skillet cookies
directions: Beat eggs; add sugar and butter.
Mix in salt and dates; place in skillet.
On low heat, cook until thick.
Add nuts and Rice Krispies.
Roll into balls and roll in coconut.
When cool, they are ready to serve.

title: chocolate cheesecake
directions: Reserve 1 cup dry cake mix.
In large bowl, combine cake mix, 1 egg and oil; mixture will be crumbly.
Press in pan 3/4 up the side of greased cake pan. Blend cream cheese and sugar; add 3 eggs and reserved cake mix. Beat at medium speed for 1 minute at low speed. Add milk; beat until smooth.
Pour into crust. Bake at 300° for 45 to 50 minutes. Cool and add Cool Whip.

title: green enchiladas
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients and melt in double boiler to make a sauce.
Salt and pepper meat.
Cook meat until brown; add onion when meat is done.
Add cheese and melt.
Remove from heat.
Dip tortillas in hot oil about 10 seconds.
Drain.
Roll meat in tortillas; place in baking dish and cover with cheese sauce.
Bake.

title: elan's lemon fromage
directions: Beat eggs well, adding sugar slowly while beating.
Add lemon rind.
Beat until thick and creamy.
Dissolve gelatin in lemon juice which has been warmed slowly.
Add dissolved gelatin to egg mixture.

title: refrigerator pan rolls
directions: Combine 3/4 cup hot water, the sugar, salt and Crisco in small saucepan.
Heat until dissolved; cool to lukewarm.
Dissolve the yeast in 1 cup warm water.
Add yeast mixture and water mixture to beaten egg.
Add 2 1/2 cups of flour and beat until smooth.
Add enough flour (approximately 3 cups) to make soft dough.

title: special baked beans
directions: Brown ground beef; drain.
Brown bacon and onion.
Drain.
Put together with beans and other ingredients and cook 4 to 6 hours.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Cream shortening, peanut butter, sugars and eggs.
Stir in flour a cup at a time.
Add baking powder and soda.
Add Reese's peanut butter chips.
Spoon onto cookie sheet and crisscross with fork.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: meatball soup
directions: Melt butter in a large pot.
Add sliced onions and cook until wilted.
Add the tomatoes and 4 cans of water.
Add beef bouillon cubes. Add carrots. Salt and pepper to taste.

title: heavenly hash cake
directions: Spread crushed vanilla wafers in bottom of pan; reserve 1 cup for the topping.

title: brownies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Spread shortening on bottom of 9 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
In saucepan, put margarine in; heat over medium burner until melted.
Remove pan from burner; stir in chocolate syrup, flour, sugar and baking soda.
Add eggs, mixing everything. Pour batter into greased pan.
Bake for 18 to 20 minutes.
Take out; sprinkle chocolate pieces and nuts on top.

title: spanish rice
directions: Wash rice in cold water and drain.
Heat oil in skillet, then add rice.
Cook until rice is transparent.
Add garlic, onion, cumminos, add tomatoes.
Stir in tomato sauce, peas and carrots, water and bouillon.
When it is boiling hard, cover skillet and turn down heat.
When all the water is gone, turn off stove and eat.

title: pear jello salad
directions: Drain juice from can of pears and heat 1 cup of it to boiling point.
Pour over gelatin and stir until dissolved.
Cool until slightly thickened.
Beat cheese and cream until smooth.
Add slightly thickened gelatin and beat well with rotary mixer.
Fold in pears which have been cut into small pieces and add whipped cream.
Refrigerate.

title: heavenly hash
directions: Drain pineapple and save juice.
Mix pineapple juice with cream cheese; blend well.
Mix with all other ingredients.
Chill before serving.

title: ham-cheese casserole
directions: In
a greased 13 x 9-inch pan, lay 8 slices bread.
Top each slice with 1 slice ham and 1 slice of cheese.
Top with bread slice.
Mix together the eggs, milk, salt, pepper and dry mustard. Pour mixture over bread and refrigerate overnight.
Sprinkle with cornflake crumbs and drizzle 1/4 cup melted margarine over casserole.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.
Let stand 10 minutes before serving.

title: mamie's million dollar fudge
directions: Place chocolate chips, marshmallow cream and German sweet chocolate in a large bowl.
Place sugar, salt, milk and margarine in saucepan and bring to a boil, stirring constantly.
Simmer 6 minutes.
Stir the entire time as it will scorch.
Remove immediately and pour over ingredients in bowl.
Mix until all blended and all chocolate is melted.
Add vanilla.
Pour into well-buttered 9 x 13 x 2-inch baking dish.
Makes 5 pounds of delicious fudge.

title: steak pizziaola
directions: Saute garlic in olive oil until slightly brown (do not burn!). Saute steak in garlic and oil until browned.
Remove steak and set aside.
Add cans of tomatoes, basil, parsley and oregano.
Salt and pepper to taste and a dash of sugar.
Cook sauce 20 minutes without meat.
Add meat back to sauce and continue to cook for another 15 minutes (according to desired meat tenderness).
Serve over rice or pasta.

title: peanut butter balls
directions: Mix in a large bowl the Rice Krispies, peanut butter, confectioners sugar and margarine.
Form into small balls.
Then take Hershey bar, chocolate bits and paraffin wax.
Melt chocolate and paraffin in a double boiler.
Dip balls in melted chocolate. Place on a sheet of wax paper and refrigerate.

title: easy peanut brittle
directions: Mix sugar, light corn syrup, peanuts and salt in large, covered microwave safe dish and stir well.

Microwave on high for 8 minutes, stirring halfway through cooking time. Add vanilla and butter, mix well and microwave on high again for 2 more minutes. Keep in mind that cooking times might vary, depending on the wattage of your microwave.
After cooking, remove and add baking soda.

Stir well until mixture becomes foamy and light in color. Immediately pour onto wax paper and use a metal knife to spread the mixture to about 1/4 inch thick. Plastic knives will melt. Wear oven mitts when cooking and handling this mixture.
It is very hot.
Let sit until completely cooled.
Remove wax paper and break into pieces.
Store in an airtight container.
Makes about 1 pound.

title: lo-cal rice pudding(top of stove)
directions: In heavy pot, put rice, 3 1/2 cups milk, Sweet 'N Low and salt.
Stir on medium heat until it boils.
Reduce heat to simmer. Cover and stir often 25 to 35 minutes until rice is tender.
Beat egg, 1/2 cup milk and vanilla.
Slowly stir into rice mixture. Cook and stir until slightly thick 2 to 3 minutes.
Add raisins. Spoon into bowl and refrigerate.
(If you like a thicker pudding, do not rinse rice.)

title: blueberry crumble
directions: Place berries, sugar and cornstarch in saucepan.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly until berries become juicy and thick.
Stir in lemon juice and peel.
Then pour into a shallow 2-quart baking dish.

title: corn relish
directions: Cut corn from cobs.
Seed peppers and chop with cabbage and onions.
Mix vegetables together; add remaining ingredients and cook until corn is tender, 20 to 30 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Pack in hot sterilized jars and seal.
Makes 5 pints.

title: macaroni and ham casserole
directions: Simmer onion
and
ham	in
oleo
for 5 minutes.
Brown lightly.
Combine all ingredients except 1/2 cup cheese.
Pour into greased 1-quart casserole.
Sprinkle with rest of cheese. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Makes 6 servings.

title: chicken divan
directions: Lightly brown chicken in 1/2 stick of butter.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Place broccoli in casserole dish.
Arrange chicken over broccoli.
Heat remaining butter in same skillet.
Add flour and cook 2 minutes.
Slowly add milk, stirring constantly.
Cook and stir until boiling and thick.
Add sour cream and 1 to 2 teaspoons paprika.
Remove from heat.
Stir well.
Pour over chicken.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: omelette
directions: Preheat pan.
Keep fire low.
Beat 2 eggs.
Pour into pan. Cook 1 minute.
Sprinkle with cheese and salsa.
Fold over.
Cover and turn off fire.

title: simple caramel frosting
directions: Melt butter in small pan and stir in brown sugar.
Stir in milk and bring mixture just to a boil.
Cool to lukewarm (about 110°).
Stir in vanilla and confectioners sugar and beat until creamy.

title: homemade ice cream
directions: Beat eggs and sugar until creamy.
Add vanilla, condensed and whole milks.
Pour mixture into canister; add ice and salt to bucket.
Takes 20 to 30 minutes to make.

title: salsa
directions: Chop onion, jalapenos and garlic in the food processor.
Add whole tomatoes (not juice).
Chop a little bit, not until a puree. Add salt to taste.
Add juice to mixture.
Jalapeno's juice can be added to make it spicier.

title: lemon nut cake
directions: Mix flour with raisins and pecans.
Cream butter and sugar. Add beaten egg yolks, dissolved soda and floured nuts and raisins. Add extract last; fold in stiffly beaten egg whites.
Bake in tube pan at 250° for 2 hours and 45 minutes or 3 (8 x 4 x 2 1/2-inch) loaf pans at 250° for 1 hour and 35 minutes.

title: granny in a pecan pie
directions: Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes. Lower heat to 250° or less if edges brown too fast.
Bake 1 hour.

title: nutritious dog food
directions: Cook beef and drain fat and cool.
Add remaining ingredients and mix.
Yields 1 3/4 pounds.

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix together all ingredients except cheese and bake 30 minutes at 350°.
Take out of oven and sprinkle cheese over top.
Return to oven and bake another 15 minutes or until center is firm. Delicious served hot or cold.

title: rhubarb crunch
directions: Put rhubarb in 9 X 13 pan. Mix 1 cup sugar & 2 tablespoon flour together and sprinkle over rhubarb. Dot with butter. Sift together remaining cup of sugar, flour, baking powder, and salt. Add beaten eggs to mixture until crumbly. Sprinkle over rhubarb and bake 40 minutes at 350 degrees.

title: enchilada casserole
directions: Brown hamburger meat.
Make up mixture of soups and Ro-Tel. Cover bottom of a pan with flour tortilla shells.
Add layer of cooked hamburger meat, grated cheese and soup mixture.
Repeat this procedure until all of the ingredients are used up.
Cover with grated cheese and cook for about 45 minutes at 350°.

title: oreo sundae
directions: Melt margarine in a 9 x 13-inch pan. Reserve about 1/2 cup crushed Oreos for top and mix remaining with margarine to form a crust in pan (press into pan). Spread softened ice cream over crust (work fast). Add fudge sauce on top. Top with Cool Whip. Sprinkle with remaining crumbs. Freeze.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Grind eggs, garlic and shrimp in food grinder or blender. Combine with rest of ingredients and blend well (by hand), adding enough mayonnaise to make mixture right "dipping" consistency. Refrigerate 12 hours before serving.
Makes 15 to 25 servings.

title: butterscotch pie
directions: Mix egg yolks, water, flour, milk and brown sugar together. Cook over medium heat until thick.
Remove from heat; add vanilla and butter.
Cool.
Pour in 9-inch baked pie shell.
Use egg whites for meringue.

title: spiced mixed nuts
directions: In large bowl, combine egg white and water.
Add nuts; toss to coat.
Combine sugar and spice; sprinkle over the nuts and toss until well coated.
Place nuts in single layer on lightly greased baking sheet.
Bake at 300° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Immediately transfer the nuts to wax paper; cool.
Break up large clusters. Store in covered container.
Yield:
6 cups.

title: cheese sauce
directions: Melt margarine in saucepan over low heat.
Stir in flour, salt and dash of pepper.
Add milk and stir until smooth.
Add cheese and cook until thick.
Serve hot over vegetables or whatever.

title: pear honey
directions: Cook about 1 1/2 hours. Pour into pint jars and seal.

title: garden loaf(4 to 6 servings)
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Line an 8 x 4-inch loaf pan with foil; grease foil.
In a large bowl, stir together onion, celery, carrots, green pepper, walnuts, bread crumbs, salt, black pepper and dill weed.
In a small bowl, stir together mayonnaise and eggs until smooth.
Stir mayonnaise mixture into vegetable mixture until well mixed.

title: drop cookies
directions: Mix ingredients well and drop small dabs on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: dump cake
directions: Dump can
of
pineapple into cake pan (do not grease or flour), dump cherry pie filling on top of pineapple.
Dump box of cake
mix on top of cherries.
Put margarine on top of cake mix in pats.
Dump pecans on top of margarine.
Bake 40 to 50 minutes at 350°.

title: raised potato doughnuts
directions: Add
sugar,
shortening,
salt and potatoes.
Heat milk until film
forms
on top (DO NOT BOIL).
Soften yeast in warm water. Let
stand
minutes.
Add to milk and potatoes mixture, eggs, lemon extract and cinnamon.
Add flour a little at a time, working smoothly into a nice dough, cover and let rise until double in bulk.
Roll 1/4-inch and cut doughnuts and let rise.
Fry
in shortening
or
salad oil heated to 375° until golden brown.

title: ratatouille(8 servings)
directions: Saute first 3 ingredients; drain oil.
Add rest of ingredients; simmer over low heat, covered, for 35 to 45 minutes. Uncover about 10 minutes prior to serving to reduce liquid.

title: texas sheet cake
directions: Bring the first 3 ingredients to a boil.
Mix in a bowl the flour, sugar and salt.
Add hot mixture and beat together. Add the eggs, sour cream and soda.
Pour into a 1 1/2-inch cookie tin. Bake at 375° for 20 minutes. Test with a toothpick.

title: quick cobbler
directions: Flan is an open round pastry usually filled with fruit.

title: creamy chocolate mints
directions: Melt, over hot (not boiling) water, chocolate morsels.
Remove from heat.
Add sour cream; blend well.
Stir in mint flavored liqueur.
Transfer to small bowl.
Chill until thick (about 1/2 hour).
Fill pastry bag fitted with decorative tip.
Pipe 1-inch candies onto foil-lined cookie sheets.
Refrigerate until ready to serve.
Makes about 3 1/2 dozen candies.

title: chocolate angel food cake
directions: Add water to egg whites and let stand until they reach room temperature.
Sift sugar and cocoa together.
Sift flour with salt.
Beat egg whites until foamy.
Add cream of tartar and continue beating until mixture holds a peak.
Continue beating slowly adding sugar and cocoa.
Fold in flour and add vanilla. Bake in tube pan at 375° for about 40 minutes.
Serve with whipped cream and fresh raspberries.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Cut broccoli in small pieces.
Add bacon, onion and raisins. Mix mayonnaise, vinegar and sugar.
Pour over salad; let marinate in refrigerator.

title: mile-high meringue
directions: Beat egg whites until foamy.
Add salt, vanilla and 6 tablespoons sugar, one tablespoon at a time, beating well after each addition, until mixture is thick and holds a peak.
Set aside.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Mix mayonnaise, sugar and vinegar and let stand.
Then cut broccoli, cheese and bacon into small pieces and add into the mayonnaise mixture.
Refrigerate.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Butter bottom of pan.
In bowl, mix stuffing and melted butter.
Cover bottom of pan with this mixture (set aside about 1/4).
In another bowl, mix chicken broth, sour cream and mushroom soup.
Place chicken on top of stuffing mix (already in pan). Pour chicken broth mixture over chicken.
Sprinkle remaining 1/4 stuffing mix on top.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: chow fun
directions: Bring water to boil and add salt and 1/4 cup oil.
Break noodles into 4-inch lengths and boil for about 10 minutes, stirring constantly.
Do not overcook.
Remove noodles and rinse in cold water and drain.
In wok or skillet, add 1/4 cup oil. Stir-fry pork and bacon until cooked.
Remove excess oil.
Add onions, noodles and bean sprouts.
Stir-fry.
Add salt, pepper and oyster sauce.
Continue cooking until sprouts are wilted.
Serve with shoyu sauce.

title: caesar salad dressing
directions: Combine all ingredients in blender.
Blend until well mixed.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Beat shortening and sugars together.
Add eggs and dry ingredients and mix by hand.
Add nuts, raisins and oats.
Bake in 375° oven 12 to 15 minutes on greased cookie sheet.

title: blueberry tea cake
directions: Mix ingredients as usual for a cake, but blend 2 c. Flour mixed with Blueberries in last.

title: a different chicken salad
directions: Mix coleslaw, chicken and fruit.
Toss gently.
Chill.
Cut cantaloupe into quarters.
Fill each with 1/4 chicken mix.

title: english toffee
directions: Using a minimum 5-quart heavy gauge pan, stir the above ingredients until the sugar and butter are melted. Allow it to come to a rolling boil and cook without stirring until it reaches the hard-crack stage. This is tricky, but is indicated by smoke coming up and the color turning much darker. If undercooked, it will not harden and if overcooked, it will have a burned taste. Good luck.

title: southern baked beans
directions: Mix all ingredients in a pan.
Put in oven at 350° for 1 hour.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine Crisco, brown sugar, milk and vanilla.
Beat egg into creamed mixture.
Add flour, salt and baking soda mixture together.
Add chocolate chips and pecan pieces.
Drop onto baking sheet.
Bake for 8 to 10 minutes for chewy cookies and 11 to 13 minutes for crisp cookies.

title: becca's go everywhere brownies
directions: In large saucepan, melt butter.
Stir in sugars, eggs and vanilla.
Beat well with wood spoon.
Mix dry ingredients together and add to wet; blend well.
Spread into greased 9 x 9-inch or 10 x 10-inch pan and bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: mexican hors d'oeuvres
directions: Mix together and spread on tortillas.
Roll up and slice into 1/2-inch slices.
Serve with hot sauce or salsa.

title: squash souffl
directions: Mix all ingredients together (except last 3) and pour into a casserole dish. Sprinkle top with bread crumbs. Dot with margarine. Sprinkle lightly with paprika. Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes. Serves 6 to 8.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Mix and mash all ingredients.
Pour into a buttered casserole dish.
Bake 20 minutes at 400°.

title: orange pineapple muffins
directions: Drain pineapple.
In large bowl, combine flour, sugar, baking powder and salt.
In a small bowl, combine eggs, milk and butter. Stir in pineapple, nuts and orange peel.
Make a well in center of dry ingredients.
Pour in milk mixture.
Stir just until moistened.
Spoon onto greased muffin cups.
Bake in 400° oven for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: "sinful" potatoes au gratin(serves 6)
directions: Butter	 a
shallow
baking
dish.
Arrange
layers
of potatoes, sprinkling
each layer with salt, pepper, cheese and butter.
Pour cream over the assembled dish.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour or until tender.

title: baked beans
directions: Boil beans.
Drain off most of the water and add the rest of ingredients.
Bake 2 to 3 hours at 350°.
Do not cover.

title: sweet pickles
directions: Drain liquid from pickles (pour out).
Slice pickles about 1/4-inch thick.
Put a few slices of pickles back in gallon jar. Pour a good layer of sugar over pickles.
Continue to layer pickle slices and sugar until they are all back in the jar.
Put garlic in the middle of the jar (or when half of the pickles have been placed back in the jar).
Will make its own liquid.
When all sugar is dissolved, put in refrigerator and keep until all are eaten.

title: cheap baptist punch
directions: Stir together the pineapple juice, thawed lemonade, Kool-Aid, sugar and water (fill the large pineapple juice full of water). Buy the flavor/color of Kool-Aid that fits the color of punch you want. Freeze punch in gallon freezer bags. Thaw 6 to 8 hours before serving.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Boil chicken and save broth.
Remove chicken from bone and spread in bottom of greased 3-quart casserole.
Mix soups and milk.
Pour over chicken.
Sprinkle stuffing mix over this; melt margarine with broth.
Pour over stuffing.
Bake 40 minutes at 400°.

title: baked lasagna
directions: Brown meat; drain off fat.
Add oregano and salt; simmer 5 minutes.
Stir in spaghetti sauce and tomato paste.
Cook 10 minutes.
Boil lasagna in salted water for 5 minutes.
Combine eggs, Ricotta cheese, Parmesan cheese, parsley and pepper; blend well.
Layer half the lasagna in greased 13 x 9-inch baking dish. Spread with 1/2 cheese mixture.
Add 1/2 the Mozzarella cheese, then 1/2 the sauce mixture.
Repeat the layers, ending with sauce on top.
Bake 30 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: no-bake chocolate oatmeal cookies(makes 3 dozen)
directions: In medium saucepan, combine sugar, cocoa, oleo and milk. Bring to a boil; boil 1 minute.
(Use a timer; don't overcook!) Stir in vanilla, peanut butter and oats; mix thoroughly.
Drop by spoonfuls onto waxed paper.
Let cool.

title: chocolate lover's decake
directions: Combine milk and vinegar; let stand.
Combine flour, cocoa, soda, baking powder, butter and vanilla.
Gradually add sugar and eggs; beat smooth.
Add flour.
Mix with milk; beat smooth.
Put into 2 round or square cake pans or 1 loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes, or until done.

title: greek chicken
directions: Take the salad oil, lemon juice and spices and mix together. Take chicken and place in the mixture to soak.
Peel potatoes and cut into chunky pieces.
Place chicken in 9 x 13-inch dish and add potatoes.
Then pour remaining mixture over chicken and potatoes. Bake covered for 45 minutes at 350°.

title: garbanzo bean soup
directions: Mix beans and chopped onions in a large kettle; add 2 to 3 cans water and cook over medium heat until liquid becomes creamy, about 45 minutes.
Cut sausage into bite size pieces and add to mixture. Add potatoes; cook until potatoes are tender.
Salt and pepper to taste.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Brown ground beef.
Drain off grease.
Add Ranch beans (in a bowl mix soup and Ro-Tel).
Line baking dish (9 x 12-inch) with flour tortilla.
Add hamburger meat and Ranch beans.
Spoon Ro-Tel and soup over it.
Grate Cheddar cheese over it and bake for 20 to 30 minutes in a 350° to 375° oven.

title: island treasure cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
In bowl, combine flour, baking powder, salt and baking soda.
Set aside.
In bowl beat butter, brown sugar, sugar and vanilla until creamy.
Add egg and mix well. Gradually add flour mixture.
Stir in coconut, Macadamia nuts and Treasures.
Drop by slightly rounded tablespoonfuls onto ungreased cookie sheets.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes.
Allow to stand 2 minutes before removing from cookie sheets.
Cool completely, makes about 2 dozen 3-inch cookies.

title: ranger rice with beef
directions: In skillet, cook beef, green pepper and onion with garlic until vegetables are tender.
Drain, if needed.
Add remaining ingredients.
Bring to boil; reduce heat.
Cover; cook 10 minutes or until liquid is absorbed.
Stir occasionally.
Makes about 5 cups.

title: date cake
directions: In the large bowl of an electric mixer, stir together flour, baking powder, baking soda, salt, cinnamon, nutmeg and sugar.
Add buttermilk, egg and butter.
Beat at medium speed until batter is smooth.
Fold in dates.
Turn into a greased and floured 9-inch square cake pan.
Bake in preheated 350° oven until a cake tester inserted in center comes out clean (40 to 45 minutes).
Cut in squares and serve warm with lemon sauce and garnish of cream cheese whipped all fluffy.

title: fried okra salad
directions: Fry okra in corn meal.
Dice fresh tomatoes and onions.
Put in separate bowl.
When okra is done, put in bowl with paper towel to absorb grease.
Take out paper towel.
Add tomatoes and onions to cooked okra; stir and season to taste.

title: sloppy joes
directions: Brown ground beef and drain off fat.
Add rest of ingredients. Simmer for 5 minutes.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients except margarine and cornflakes, in a 9 X 13 pan. Top with corn flakes and margarine. Bake at 350° for about 1 hour and 25 minutes.

title: fruit cobbler
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Melt butter in baking dish in oven. Make batter with sugar, flour, baking powder, salt and milk.
Add to melted butter.
Do not stir.
Pour fruit on top.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: potato cakes
directions: In mixing bowl, blend together eggs, potatoes and flour.
Fry in butter until brown.

title: mrs. c's coleslaw
directions: In a large bowl, toss together the cabbage and carrots.
Mix together the mayonnaise, vinegar, sugar and celery seed for dressing.
Stir into the cabbage and mix well to coat.
Chill before serving.

title: pecan balls
directions: Beat sugar and butter together.
Add vanilla, pecans and flour; mix.
Roll into balls the size of walnuts.
Bake at 275° for 1 hour.
Roll in powdered sugar.

title: turtle cake
directions: Mix the first 4 ingredients together.
Use a Tupperware 3 quart stack cooker with pan and cone sprayed with Pam.
Time may have to be adjusted with some microwaves.
Sprinkle pecans in the bottom of pan.
Pour in the cake mixture.
Slowly pour caramel sauce around the pan in a circle, being very careful that the caramel doesn't touch the cone or the outside of the pan.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Bake in microwave oven for 9 minutes at 50% power, then 7 minutes at High power.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Turn out onto a plate.
Enjoy.

title: cauliflower-cheese soup
directions: Place first 7 ingredients together in a pot. Bring to a boil; cover and simmer 15 minutes. Puree the entire mixture in the blender until smooth and creamy. Transfer to a kettle or double boiler and whisk in Cheddar, dill weed, mustard, milk, dill or caraway seed and black pepper. Heat the soup gently as you whisk in the ingredients. Steam or saut in butter 1 1/2 cups more cauliflowerets. Add these to the soup. Serve topped with chopped scallion and extra cheese.

title: "that" salad
directions: Mix dry jello together.
Add boiling water.
Dissolve all. Add remaining ingredients; stir together.
Top with cherries for color.
Enjoy!

title: cheese cake
directions: Mix the first 5 ingredients together, except egg white, then add the milk and water.
Beat the egg white; blend white in.
Bake at 400° until brown on top, then turn oven to 325° and bake until you insert knife and it comes out dry.

title: easy chicken casserole
directions: Cook chicken and cut in bite-sized pieces.
Mix chicken, soup and sour cream.
Put in casserole dish.
Crush crackers.
Melt oleo and pour over crackers.
Mix well and put over chicken mixture. Cook at 350° until bubbly.

title: glazed sweet potatoes
directions: Cook fresh sweet potatoes just until tender; drain.
Cut into chunks.
Place cooked or canned sweet potatoes in a 2-quart baking dish.
In a small saucepan, combine butter, syrup, brown sugar and cinnamon.
Cook and stir until mixture boils.
Pour over potatoes. Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: sesame green beans
directions: Melt butter in skillet.
Lightly brown sesame seeds.
Drain vegetables after cooking or heating.
Season and sprinkle with toasted seeds.
Serves 2, maybe 3.

title: old-fashioned sugar cakes
directions: Sift together the first 3 ingredients.
Add butter and mix. Beat in the eggs, milk and lemon.
Add to dry mixture and blend well.
Drop by full teaspoonfuls on cookie sheet.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes at 375°.

title: old fashion pound cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour 10-inch tube pan. Cream butter and shortening in large mixing bowl until fluffy. Add sugar 1/2 cup at a time, creaming well.
Stir in vanilla, lemon extract and juice.
Add eggs, blending well at each addition.
Sift flour and baking powder.
Add to creamed mixture alternately with milk.
Stir thoroughly.
Pour into prepared pan. Bake 1 hour and 20 minutes or until wooden toothpick inserted comes out clean.
Cool 15 minutes on wire rack.
Makes 1 (10-inch) cake.

title: stuffed flounder
directions: In
a
skillet,
cook
onion in 1/4 cup of butter until tender.
Stir
drained mushrooms in skillet with crab, cracker crumbs,
parsley,
1/2 teaspoon of salt and pepper.
Put a few spoonfuls
of
this mixture on a fish filet and roll up.
In a saucepan,
melt
3	tablespoons of butter;	blend in flour and 1/4 teaspoon of salt.	Add enough milk to the mushroom liquid to make 1 1/2 cups.
Cook until thickens.
Pour over fish and bake for
minutes
at
Sprinkle
with
paprika and cheese; bake for 10 minutes more.

title: hamburger upside-down casserole
directions: Put beef, onions, garlic and butter in hot skillet.
Cook until meat loses its redness.
Stir in tomato sauce, salt, pepper and oregano.
Simmer a few minutes.
Spread over bottom of 2-quart greased casserole, packing firmly.
Toss macaroni, sharp cheese and cottage cheese.
Arrange on top of meat mixture and also pack firmly.

title: new potatoes
directions: Wash potatoes; leave skins on and slice lengthwise, approximately 1/4-inch thick.
Spray baking pan with Pam.
Lay potatoes in pan in layers.
Pour Italian dressing over each layer. Top with parsley flakes.
Cover and bake for 1 hour at 400°.

title: fruit cake squares
directions: Melt butter; pour into a 15 1/2 x 10 1/2-inch jelly roll pan. Sprinkle on graham cracker crumbs; sprinkle in coconut.
Spread candied fruit as even as possible over coconut.
Cut dates into small pieces.
Drop in flour and mix well.
Press dates into mixture evenly.
Pour sweetened condensed milk over the top.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Cool.
Cut into bars.

title: salad dressing
directions: Mix all ingredients until well blended.
Keep refrigerated

title: enchiladas
directions: Cook chuck roast in water to cover 1-inch over meat until tender (4 hours).
Shred meat.
Make gravy with water from meat, soup, chili con carne and spices.
Dip tortilla in salad oil and fry quickly on both sides.
Dip in gravy and wrap meat, onions, cheese and mushrooms.
Place in a 10 x 13-inch baking dish. Garnish with Mozzarella cheese.
Pour gravy over enchiladas.
Bake in 350° oven for 35 minutes.
Garnish with green onions and Parmesan cheese before serving.

title: chicken pilaf
directions: Using wok or heavy frying pan, add 1/2 cup oil, onions and celery.
Saute.
Add vegetables; stir-fry until crisp-tender.
Add chicken and rice and soy sauce.
Cover and cook until hot.
Serves 4.

title: coconut cream cake
directions: Combine cake mix, 1 cup coconut, water and egg white.
Beat for 2 minutes on high speed; reduce to low and beat 1 minute. Pour into 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Cool in pan 1 minute.
Poke holes in cake with toothpick.
Pour cream of coconut over cake.
Spread Cool Whip and sprinkle with coconut and cover.
Chill 4 hours.

title: cantaloupe pie
directions: Cut melon in half; remove the seeds and peel.
Cut into chunks and place in container of electric blender; process until smooth. Combine 1/2 cup melon puree and cream cheese in container of an electric blender; process until smooth.
Add to remaining melon puree; set aside.
Combine sugar, gelatin and orange juice in a small saucepan; let stand 2 minutes.
Cook over low heat, stirring until sugar and gelatin dissolve.
Slowly add to melon mixture, stirring well.
Pour into chilled crust; chill until firm. Garnish pie with a dollop of whipped cream and cantaloupe balls, if desired.

title: taco chicken
directions: Saute onions in butter in skillet.
Add soups, Ro-Tel tomatoes, chicken and broth, mixing well.
Bring to a boil.

title: phyllis lightvoet's flank steak
directions: Cover with plastic wrap and marinate for 24 hours at room temperature.
Turn steak occasionally and pour sauce over the top. Broil for 10 to 15 minutes.
Slice in one-inch strips across grain of meat.
Enjoy.

title: hot pepper cornbread
directions: Bake in a 9 x 13-inch pan at 450° for 30 minutes.

title: holiday fruit gems
directions: Dissolve strawberry gelatin in 1 cup boiling water.
Add 1/2 cup of ginger ale.
Beat cream cheese with electric mixer. Gradually beat in gelatin.
Pour into Flintstones mold, sprayed with vegetable cooking spray.
Chill until set but not firm. Meanwhile, dissolve lime gelatin in 1 cup boiling water.
Add 1/2 cup of ginger ale.
Chill until thickened.
Stir in fruit.
Spoon over gelatin in mold.
Chill until firm, 4 hours.
Unmold.
Makes 10 servings.

title: stir-fry chicken with vegetables
directions: Heat 2 tablespoons oil in wok or large skillet over medium-high heat.
Add radishes, peppers and onions.
Stir-fry 3 to 5 minutes or until crisp-tender.
Add mushrooms and chestnuts; stir-fry 1 minute and remove vegetables from pan.
Add remaining oil and stir-fry chicken for 6 to 8 minutes or until tender and done.
Add vegetables and all remaining ingredients except rice; mix well and simmer 1 minute.
Serve over rice.

title: sherbet tea punch
directions: Pour hot tea over sugar; stir until sugar dissolves.
Add juices.
Refrigerate until chilled.
Pour into punch bowl and add ginger ale.
Spoon into sherbet.
Makes 16 punch cup servings.

title: banana bread
directions: Place the sugar in a large bowl, then add beaten egg, flour, salt and baking soda.
Add mashed bananas and mix all together. Last, add melted shortening and mix everything together well. Place in a greased and floured loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: cashew and noodle casserole
directions: Cut drained tenderbits in fourths.
Mix with mushrooms, celery and onions.
Mix everything together.
Place in oiled casserole dish and bake in a 350° oven for 30 minutes.
Serves 8.

title: deluxe chocolate pecan cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°. Combine flour, baking soda and salt. Cream Blue Bonnet and brown sugar. Add eggs and vanilla; beat until light and fluffy. Blend in flour mixture. Stir in chocolate chips and nuts. Drop by rounded teaspoons onto ungreased cookie sheets. Bake 10 to 13 minutes or until golden brown. Allow to stand 2 to 3 minutes before removing from cookie sheets. Makes 4 dozen cookies.

title: cream cheese pie
directions: Let cream cheese soften for 1 hour. On medium speed, beat the milk and cream cheese until smooth. Add lemon juice and vanilla; mix well. Pour into graham cracker pie crust; chill in refrigerator and serve.

title: banana bread
directions: Cream shortening and sugar, add eggs and beat well.
Put dry ingredients together, add to creamed mixture alternatively with bananas.
Stir in walnuts.
Pour into well greased 8 1/2 x 4 1/2 x 2 1/2 loaf pan.
Bake at 350° oven about 1 hour.
Remove from pan, cool on rack.
Better a day old.

title: swedish meatballs
directions: Mix all ingredients except cream of mushroom soup; shape into meatballs about the size of a silver dollar.
Brown in deep fat. Put in crock-pot.

title: dutch meat loaf
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients together and bake.
Blend and baste together rest of the ingredients to form sauce while you bake. Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.
You may freeze meat loaf and use when needed.
Add baste ingredients while you bake.

title: biscuits
directions: Set oven to 450°.
Put flour, baking powder and salt into sifter, then sift dry ingredients into a bowl.
Add shortening and cut it in using a pastry blender or two knives.
Add and stir just enough milk to make a soft dough.
Turn dough out on a lightly floured board and knead gently 15 to 20 times.
Roll out or pat dough to 1/2-inch and cut with 2-inch cookie cutter.
Place on ungreased baking sheet.
Bake 12 to 15 minutes until brown.

title: chicken in mushroom sauce
directions: Arrange chicken in roasting pan; brown in 350° oven, then sprinkle seasoned salt and garlic powder over chicken.
In large bowl, combine soup, water, Lipton onion soup, flour and bay leaf; pour over chicken and bake until chicken is done.
Serve on rice.

title: chocolate balls with cookies
directions: Mix the cookies with 2 tablespoons cocoa in a plate and add the almonds.
Combine the honey and orange jam (may substitute the orange jam with orange juice) to the mixture and mix.
Shape into small balls and roll in cocoa powder on the coconut.

title: lotsa potatoes
directions: Defrost hash browns.
Warm 2 cans of soup, 2 cans milk and cream cheese over low heat.
Add salt, pepper, onion salt and margarine to milk.
Pour over potatoes and sprinkle grated cheese over top.
Makes 2 casseroles of potatoes, 1 (13 x 9 x 2-inch) and 1 (10 x 6-inch).
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes.

title: mrs. rohe's butterscotch syrup(makes 3 cups)
directions: Put brown sugar and maple syrup in a saucepan and heat gently until syrup is dissolved.
Now boil rapidly for 5 minutes.

title: grandma's goulash
directions: Saute onion, green pepper and mushrooms in olive oil.
Brown ground beef and add to sauteed mixture.
Add salt, pepper and garlic powder to taste.
Stir in spaghetti sauce and brown sugar. Mix macaroni and above mixture in casserole dish.
Top with cheese.
Cook for 45 minutes at 400°.

title: pork chops with caper sauce
directions: Dredge chops in flour.
Brown in oil.
Season chops with salt and pepper.
Add bouillon mixture, onion, mustard and capers to chops.
Cover and simmer 45 minutes.
Remove chops to platter.
Add 1 tablespoon flour to drippings and mix well.
Add 1/4 cup water and stir until thickened.
Fold in sour cream.
Serve sauce over chops.

title: breakfast pizza
directions: In skillet, cook sausage until browned; drain off fat. Separate crescent rolls into 8 triangles; place in an ungreased 12-inch pizza pan with points toward center.
Press over bottom and up sides of pan to form a crust.
Seal perforations.
Spoon sausage over crust.
Sprinkle with potatoes.
Top with Cheddar cheese.
In a bowl, beat together eggs, milk, salt and pepper. Pour into crust.
Sprinkle Parmesan cheese over all.
Bake in 375° oven for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: hot milk cake
directions: Beat sugar and eggs.
Add flour; beat again.
Heat oleo and milk.
Add, then beat.
Add vanilla, lemon and baking powder. Beat.
Will be a thin batter.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes in tube pan.

title: fruit dip
directions: Mix well; serve with fresh fruit.
Goes best with apples and bananas.

title: barbecued chicken wings
directions: Cut off wing tips.
Cut parts in half at joint.
Sprinkle with salt, pepper and oil, set aside.
Mix remaining ingredients.
Pour over chicken.
Preheat oven to 375°, cook for about an hour. Reduce heat in case of burning.

title: not bailey's irish cream
directions: Beat eggs in blender.
Add other ingredients and blend thoroughly.
Use more chocolate sauce to taste.
Store in refrigerator.

title: baskin-robbins pie
directions: Mix pudding and spread over second layer.
Spread on rest of the Cool Whip.
Sprinkle nuts on top.

title: broccoli and cheese casserole
directions: Boil broccoli according to package instructions.
Cover bottom of casserole dish with drained broccoli.

title: frozen waldorf salad
directions: Drain pineapple, reserving juice.
Set pineapple aside.
In a saucepan, combine juice with sugar, eggs and salt.
Cook, stirring constantly, over medium-low heat until slightly thickened.
Remove from heat and cool.
Stir in pineapple, celery, apples and pecans. Fold in whipped cream.

title: madcap cake
directions: Sift together flour, cocoa, sugar, baking soda and salt.
Make three depressions in dry ingredients.
Pour cider vinegar in one, the vanilla in another and the oil in the last depression.
Spoon applesauce over all.
Mix well until smooth.
(If still dry add more applesauce.)
Pour in 8-inch greased baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Cool and top with whipped cream.

title: oatmeal cookiescreston, iowa
directions: Cook raisins and let stand while mixing batter.

title: sherry's punch
directions: Mix and freeze.
Remove from freezer about 5 hours before serving.
May substitute different flavors of jello in order to get color desired.
Makes 2 gallons.

title: rosemary's glaced grahams
directions: Place graham crackers on a cookie sheet.
Melt other ingredients and pour or spoon over the crackers.
Bake about 12 minutes at 300° or 325°.
Cool slightly; break apart into squares or bars.

title: mayonnaise rolls
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Mix all ingredients together and drop into greased muffin tins.
Bake for 15 minutes.
Makes 6 rolls.

title: peanut butter balls
directions: Mix sugar, margarine and peanut butter.
Roll into balls. Place on cookie sheet and chill thoroughly.
Melt wax and chocolate in a double boiler until smooth.
Use a toothpick and dip balls in chocolate.
Place on waxed paper and chill thoroughly.

title: chicken and rice bake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease a 13 x 9-inch (3-quart) baking dish.
Pour uncooked rice over bottom of greased dish.
Sprinkle evenly with seasoning mix packet.
Arrange chicken pieces over rice.
Spoon celery and mushrooms around chicken.
In medium saucepan, combine water and soup.
Bring to a boil.
Pour evenly over chicken and vegetables.
Sprinkle chicken with paprika.

title: peanut butter sticks
directions: Cut off crust from bread.
Cut each slice in 4 strips.
Toast crusts and strips in a 250° oven until very crisp (not brown). Roll crusts into fine crumbs.

title: microwave lemon curd
directions: In a microwavable bowl, microwave the butter for about 3 minutes on High, until melted.
In a small microwave-proof bowl, whisk together the eggs, sugar, lemon peel and juice until well combined.
Whisk in the melted butter.
Microwave on High for 1 1/2 to 2 minutes, whisking often
(may take longer), until the curd is smooth and thick enough to coat a wooden spoon.
Remove from microwave and pour into hot sterilized jars (or glass bowl with a cover if you're going to use within a couple of days). Cover and allow to cool at room temperature.
Store in refrigerator and use within 4 weeks.
Makes about 2 cups.

title: grandma's sugar cookies
directions: Sift all the dry ingredients together. Cut in shortening to mix well. Add unbeaten eggs and flavoring. Mix well. On a floured counter, roll out the dough and roll thin and cut out the cookies with cookie cutters. Bake at 375° for 10 minutes. Makes about 5 dozen cookies.

title: hot crab dip
directions: In a two quart baking dish mix all ingredients together, except crab.
Add crab and sprinkle with cheese.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes.
Serve with favorite crackers.

title: chocolate peanut butter pie
directions: Blend vanilla pudding, sour cream and milk; set aside.
Melt chips with oil in microwave on High for 45 seconds.
If necessary, microwave an additional 15 seconds or until melted and smooth. Gradually blend into pudding.
Pour one-half of mixture into each pie shell.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Mix all together.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until done. Makes 2 loaf pans.

title: cream of reuben soup(can be made low carb.)
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients in large sauce pan and bring to boil. Reduce heat and cook until veggies are crisp tender. Add remaining ingredients and stir well.
Cornstarch can be added to thicken.

title: parsnip and carrot saute(side dish with roast chicken or turkey.)
directions: In large frying pan, heat 1/2 to 1 cup water; toss in the carrots and parsnips.
Cover; simmer 5 to 7 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Remove cover and add remaining ingredients.
Toss to mix.
Season to taste.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: dandelion wine
directions: Put sugar and water together and boil.
Pour over blossoms while hot.
When cool, add yeast cakes.
Put all in a big crock, if available.
Let stand for 9 (nine) days, stirring every morning.

title: ham and asparagus roll with cheddar cheese sauce
directions: Place 3 asparagus spears at the end of each slice of ham. Roll up and place side by side in casserole.
Combine remaining ingredients.
Blend well.
Spoon over asparagus rolls.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: taco salad
directions: Cream sour cream and cream cheese together. Mix in 1/2 package of Cheddar cheese and spread on bottom of pan. Cut up veggies and put in
layers. Put remaining cheese on top.
Serve with nacho chips.

title: diet nibble mix
directions: Pop the popcorn without oil.
Combine with next 2 ingredients and bake in 300° oven for 5 minutes.
Sprinkle with butter. Combine cheese and dressing mix.
Sprinkle this over mixture. Makes 9 cups.
One-half cup servings contain 57 calories, 2 gm. protein, 9 gm. carbohydrates and 2 gm. fat.

title: garlic soup
directions: In a large bowl or saucepan, combine bouillon cubes and water, stirring until cubes are dissolved.
Peel garlic and mince.
In a heavy saucepan over low heat, lightly brown garlic in butter with minced green onions, stirring constantly so as not to burn.
Add flour and stir until slightly browned.
Add broth and pepper; simmer 30 minutes to an hour.
Just before serving, slowly add egg yolks, stirring constantly.

title: garden coleslaw
directions: Combine first four ingredients well.
In salad dressing jar combine remaining items.
Shake very well.
Pour over vegetables. Refrigerate.

title: catfish cakes
directions: Cook carrots and onions in butter; set aside.
Combine fish fry mix, cornbread mix, baking powder, Creole seasonings and black pepper in large bowl.
Blend milk with egg yolk and hot sauce. Stir rice, fish, carrot mixture and milk mixture into dry ingredients.
Beat egg white until stiff; fold in beaten egg white.

title: asparagus quiche
directions: Arrange asparagus in spoke like fashion in pie shell. Sprinkle with Swiss cheese.
Beat together eggs, flour, salt and cream.
Pour over asparagus and cheese.
Sprinkle on the Parmesan and paprika.
Bake at 375° for 45 to 50 minutes or until filling is set.
Let stand 10 minutes before cutting.

title: pepper relish
directions: You can slice, grind or chop peppers and onions.
Mix all ingredients together and boil for 30 minutes.

title: lemon chess pie
directions: Mix well
and
pour in unbaked pie crust.
Bake at 350° until brown and firm (about 30 minutes).

title: easy pie crust(makes 2 pie crusts)
directions: Pour oil into milk; mix.
Pour into well blended flour.
Mix with fork until well blended.
Roll between wax paper.
Fit into pan and bake.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: In a frying pan, saute onion until it is translucent.
Cook rice; add to onion.
Add broccoli and soup to mixture.
Pour into baking dish; cover with slices of cheese.
Place in a 350° oven until cheese is melted.
Also add nacho cheese to soup for a zesty taste.

title: layered salad
directions: Wash lettuce and drain well!
Break up and put in bowl.
Layer celery, bell pepper, green onions and English peas.
Sprinkle sugar over peas.
Cover peas with mayonnaise.
Refrigerate overnight or several hours.
Before serving, sprinkle top with grated Cheddar cheese.

title: caramels
directions: Boil all together except 1 cup cream, nuts and vanilla.
Boil 30 minutes.
Add second cup of cream and boil to firm ball (248° on candy thermometer).
Remove from heat; add vanilla and nuts and pour into well buttered cookie sheet.
Cook in a heavy pan and stir.
A pressure cooker kettle works well.

title: cheesecake dip
directions: Beat cream cheese, sugar and milk until well blended and smooth.
Fold in whipped topping and vanilla.
Store in refrigerator.
Use to dip cookies, cake cubes, fresh fruit, pretzel sticks, etc.
Makes 2 cups.

title: peanut butter twist shake
directions: Mix all ingredients together in a blender until smooth. Serves one.

title: california mix casserole
directions: Mix the ingredients together, no particular order, in a casserole baking dish.
Cook in 350° oven for about 1 hour.
Cook covered.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: mexican corn bread
directions: Pour 1/2 of batter into pan; put in layer of cream cheese. Pour in rest of batter.
Cook until done.

title: hawaiian cake
directions: Prepare cake mix according to package directions.
Pour batter into greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes, or until done.
Cool.

title: cranberry gelatin salad
directions: Dissolve jello in 2 cups boiling water.
Stir in pineapple; chill until partially set.
Fold in cranberries.
Spoon on sour cream and stir through to marble.
Cut into squares to serve.

title: chicken noodle soup
directions: Bring the water to a boil in a 6 to 8-quart saucepan.
Add the next 8 ingredients.
Mix well; continue cooking over medium heat. Add meat from the chicken (meat should be boned, skinned and veined).
Soup is better if the beginning 6 cups water is broth from stewing the chicken.
Extra can of soup may be added to stretch recipe.
Cook for approximately 30 minutes, until noodles and vegetables are done.
Makes approximately 10 to 12 servings.

title: easy as pie
directions: Mix pudding according to package directions.
Fold into most of Cool Whip.
Pour into crust.
Top with remaining Cool Whip. Refrigerate or freeze.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: viva la chicken casserole
directions: Bone chicken and cut meat in large pieces.
Mix milk, soups, onion and salsa.
Cut tortillas in strips.
Grease 13 x 9-inch baking pan and sprinkle broth over bottom.
Place a layer of tortilla strips and a layer of chicken.
Spoon sauce over chicken. Make several layers, ending with sauce.
Top with cheese.
Cover and refrigerate 24 hours.
Bake at 300° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Mix all ingredients in large bowl except 1/2 cup potato chips to put on top of casserole.
Bake about 20 minutes in 350° oven. Note:
A little of the chicken broth added to casserole will make it more moist.
Also, you might want to try sour cream and onion potato chips.)

title: butterscotch cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Form into rolls and let stand overnight in refrigerator.
Slice and bake on ungreased sheet at 375° for 10 minutes.

title: nut icing
directions: Cook sugar, milk and flour until thick; add margarine.
Add powdered sugar until as thick as you want for spreading.
Add pecans.
Ready to spread on cake.

title: russian salad dressing
directions: Put all ingredients into blender.
Process on mix until thoroughly blended.
Store in fridge.

title: angel cookies
directions: Boil together the first 3 ingredients; stir.
Add remaining ingredients.
Make into balls.
Roll in coconut.

title: cup of cheer
directions: In saucepan, combine sugar, 1/2 cup water, cloves and cinnamon.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat, and simmer 20 minutes. Strain.
In large bowl, combine fruit juices and cider.
Mix well. Stir in sugar syrup.
Reheat and serve hot.

title: low-fat sweet potato and orange casserole
directions: Drain cool potatoes.
Slice in small pieces.
Mix in orange slices.
Place in 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Mix orange juice, honey, cornstarch and cloves.
Cook on medium heat.
Stir constantly until thick.
Pour over sweet potato mix.
Sprinkle with coconut.
Bake at 375° for about 15 minutes.

title: mounds dessert
directions: Mix together until crumbly butter, coconut, brown sugar and flour. Press into a 9 x 13-inch pan. Scatter the remainder on a baking sheet. Bake at 350° for 10 minutes, stirring baking sheet (not crust). Cook pudding with milk as directed. Whip topping mix as per instructions. Fold into pudding with chocolate chips and pecans. Pour over crust. Crumble crumbs over the top. Refrigerate overnight. This freezes well.

title: fruit drop cookies
directions: Mix well the margarine, sugar and eggs.
Stir in your choice of liquid.
(Cherry juice from the maraschino cherries is delicious.)
Sift the dry ingredients together and stir in and blend.
Stir in the nuts, cherries and dates.
Chill dough at least one hour.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Heat 2 tablespoons butter in frying pan and saute onions, then add zucchini, salt, pepper and garlic salt.
Cook 5 minutes and layer zucchini in baking dish with tomatoes and cheese.
Brown bread crumbs in 1 tablespoon melted butter and sprinkle on top. Bake at 350° for 25 minutes or until done.

title: clam fritters
directions: Combine beaten egg yolks, milk, clams, bread crumbs, parsley, salt and pepper.
Fold in stiffly beaten egg whites.
Drop batter from a tablespoon into a skillet containing 1/4-inch hot oil. Fry, turning once.
Garnish with orange slices.
Makes 6 servings.

title: deer jerky
directions: Thaw venison and let soak in vinegar and salt water for 1 day. Take venison and cut into strips about 1/4-inch x 1/2-inch thick and 1 to 2-inches long.
Place in a big bowl and add 1 bottle of soy sauce as a marinade.
Refrigerate and let soak in soy sauce overnight.
Next morning, place strips on cookie sheet (in rows) and cook on 150° in oven for 4 to 6 hours.
Turn strips over at 3 hour interval.

title: hot shrimp pockets
directions: My first trip to the valley on May 31, 1939.
Such a narrow road from Bakersfield.
I never thought we would get out of the curves.

title: streusel coffee cake
directions: Stir together the 1 1/2 cups flour, sugar, baking powder and salt.
Combine egg, milk and oil.
Add to flour mixture; mix well. Stir in raisins.
Turn into a greased 9 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.

title: strawberry smooth(for dieters)
directions: Mix ingredients in blender.
More ice may be needed for thickness.
Change flavor of smoothy by using different fruits and flavors of yogurt.
Serve in chilled mugs and enjoy!

title: comino rice(6 servings)
directions: Dice peppers, chop onion, mince garlic and heat broth.
In saucepan cook peppers and onion in fat (lard or butter) over medium heat 3 to 4 minutes.
Add garlic, cumin, rice and salt and stir until coated with fat.
Add hot chicken broth.
Cover and cook over low heat about 15 minutes.
Turn off heat.
Let stand covered 10 minutes.
Fluff and serve.

title: broccoli cheese soup
directions: Saute onions in butter.
Add flour, salt and pepper to butter. Stir until bubbly.
Add milk gradually to dissolve flour mixture. Separately cook broccoli in chicken bouillon seasoned water. Blend this mixture with cheese mixture.
Delicious!

title: surprise cake
directions: First Layer:
Mix Jiffy mix (follow directions on box) and bake.

title: apple pie in a bag
directions: Combine sugar, flour and salt.
Add margarine.
Mix until crumbly.
Sprinkle over apples.

title: seafood delight
directions: Steam clams, lobster tails, shrimp, Alaskan crab legs, scallops and crab meat.
Remove seafood from shells.
Chop all seafood in small pieces.
Put in pan with vinegar.
Melt butter and stir in. Spread Mozzarella cheese all through it and on top.
Bake at 300° for 15 minutes.

title: scalloped cabbage
directions: Boil cabbage and drain.
Add soup and milk.
Add slices of Velveeta cheese.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: meatballs
directions: Mix ingredients together. Roll into balls and put in sauce (recipe to follow).
Bring to a boil and let simmer for 3 hours.

title: 24 hour punch
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients.
Let stand for 24 hours.
Add soda and ginger ale at serving time.
Makes 5 quarts.

title: baked macaroni and cheese
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Cook macaroni as the package label directs; drain.
Meanwhile, melt butter in a medium saucepan; remove from heat.
Stir in the flour, salt and pepper until smooth.
Gradually stir in milk.
Bring to boiling, stirring. Reduce heat and simmer mixture 1 minute.
Remove from heat.
Stir in 1 1/2 cups of the cheese and the macaroni.
Pour into a 1 1/2-quart casserole and sprinkle remaining cheese over top.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes, or until cheese is golden brown.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: christmas cookies
directions: Cream all of these together, then roll out dough with rolling pin. Use cookie cutter to make cookies.
Makes about 2 dozen. Bake at 350° for about 12 minutes.
Delicious!

title: glaze
directions: Heat margarine in 1-quart saucepan, over low heat, until melted.
Mix in powdered sugar and vanilla.
Beat in hot water, 1 teaspoon at a time, until smooth.

title: swiss steak
directions: Combine salt with flour.
Pound flour into both sides of steak with the edge of a heavy saucer or a meat mallet.
Place fat in the pan; melt over medium heat and add steak.
Brown well on both sides; add onion, green pepper and boiling water or strained tomatoes.
Cover and reduce heat to low for 1 hour or until meat is tender.
Remove to preheated platter; pour juices over meat and garnish with parsley.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: suzi's special eggs
directions: Whisk all 12 eggs together.
Chop ham in small pieces.
Add to egg mixture.
Add garlic salt.
Add black pepper.
Pour into frying pan and scramble.
When cooked, place cheese on top to melt. Serve with toast or biscuits.

title: ricotta bread(for bread machine)
directions: In bread machine pan, place all ingredients in order suggested by manufacturer.
Select basic bread setting, choose crust color and loaf size if available.
Check dough after 5 minutes of mixing. Add 1 or 2 Tbsp. water or flour if needed. 1 loaf, 1 pound.

title: bread pudding
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Beat eggs and sweetener.
Add vanilla. Slightly warm the milk.
Add to the egg mixture, stirring constantly.
Spread oil on the bread, cut into cubes and place a layer on the bottom of a 2 to 3-quart casserole dish.
Sprinkle a little allspice on the bread.
Raisins may be added.
Pour egg mixture over the bread and sprinkle with allspice.
Bake for 25 minutes.
Serve warm or chilled.

title: broccoli and cheese to please
directions: Cook broccoli according to package and drain.
Transfer broccoli to large bowl-set aside.
Saute onion and celery in 1/4 c. melted butter in a large skillet until vegetables are tender. Add sauteed vegetables and mushrooms to broccoli; set aside.

title: banana bread
directions: In a bowl, combine salt, flour, baking powder and baking soda. In another bowl, combine sugar, eggs, and applesauce.
Beat vigorously until frothy.
Add bananas and blend thoroughly.
Fold into flour mixture until blended.
Pour into greased bread pan and bake in 325° oven for 1 hour, until crust is brown.
Makes 1 loaf.

title: 1 hour baked turkey
directions: You will need an oval shaped roaster pan with cover.

title: "melt in your mouth" pancakes
directions: Mix flours together and cut in Crisco.
Add remaining ingredients and pour onto a hot griddle.
Yields 10 to 15 (6-inch) pancakes.

title: oven chicken kiev
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients.
Mix well and shape a stick like butter.
Cover and freeze about 45 minutes or until firm.
Place each chicken breast half on a sheet of waxed paper; flatten chicken to 1/4-inch thickness using a rolling pin.
Cut butter mixture into 6 portions; place a piece in center of each breast half.
Fold long sides of chicken over butter.
Fold ends over and secure with wooden picks.
Spread oil in 13 x 9-inch pan and set aside.
Combine cracker crumbs and salt.
Dip each piece into milk and coat with crumbs.
Place chicken, seam-side up in pan.
Bake 15 minutes at 425°.
Carefully turn each piece.
Bake an additional 5 to 10 minutes.

title: frozen cole slaw
directions: Boil water, sugar, celery seed and mustard seed for 1 minute and let cool.
Grind cabbage, carrot, onion and pepper.
Add salt. Let stand for one hour.
Drain.
Pour mixture and vinegar over cabbage.
Freeze in containers.
Mmmmm good!

title: zucchini muffins
directions: In a separate bowl, combine 2 cups zucchini, eggs and oil; stir.
Add dry ingredients all at once
and bake in greased muffin pans at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: icebox fruit cake
directions: Chop all ingredients very fine.
Crush crackers and mix with fruit and nuts.
Melt marshmallows, milk and margarine over low heat or in double boiler.
Mix with fruit and crackers.
Pack very tightly in a 9 x 12-inch casserole dish.
Place in the refrigerator overnight.
Fruitcake can be eaten the next day.
Store in refrigerator.

title: sparkling champ punch
directions: In a bowl, dissolve sugar in hot tea.
Set aside.
In punch bowl, combine ginger ale, white grape juice, orange juice concentrate and seltzer. Slowly stir in reserved sugar syrup, adding just enough for desired sweetness.
Chill punch with a block or ring of ice.
Serve in champagne flutes.
If desired, add a strawberry or raspberry to each drink as garnish.
Makes about 24 (6 ounce) or 36 (4 ounce) servings.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix oil, vanilla and sugar.
Add grated zucchini and chopped dates or raisins and nuts.
Mix together. Grease and flour 2 loaf pans. Bake 1 hour.
Serves 30.

title: oobleck
directions: Start with 4 1/2 cups water; gradually add cornstarch, then food coloring.

title: raisin frosting
directions: Grind 1/2 cup raisins (best in old-time meat grinder); set aside.
In double boiler, place all ingredients except vanilla. Beat 30 seconds on low speed.
Place over boiling water in double boiler and cook for 7 minutes while beating constantly with electric mixer until frosting forms stiff peaks.
Do not overbeat. Remove from heat.
Add vanilla.
Beat for 2 to 3 more minutes. Fold in raisins.
Delicious!

title: burger loaf
directions: Mix all the ingredients in a large dish.
Let stand for 15 minutes and lay into a 3-inch deep greased baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: chocolate-peanut butter fudge
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients in a Dutch oven; cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until sugar dissolves.
Add 2 tablespoons butter, stir until butter melts.
Cover and boil mixture 3 minutes.
Remove cover, and continue to cook, without stirring.
Add remaining butter, pecans, peanut butter and vanilla. Cool 10 minutes.
Beat mixture until well blended and pour immediately into a buttered 9-inch square pan.
Cool before cutting into squares.
Yields 3 dozen squares.

title: blonde brownies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Melt shortening; add brown sugar.
Cool slightly.
Add eggs to shortening mix; blend.
Add vanilla; mix well.
Gradually add flour, baking soda, baking powder and salt. Use the hot water to help blend.
Add walnuts if desired.
Grease 13 x 9-inch pan.
Spread in batter.
Sprinkle chocolate chips on top.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: margie's celery seed dressing
directions: Blend together all ingredients except celery seed.
Add celery seed and stir in last.
Chill.

title: crunchy sauerkraut slaw
directions: In bowl, combine sauerkraut, green beans and carrot.
Combine sugar, vinegar and caraway seed; toss with vegetable mixture. Salad keeps several days in refrigerator.
Serves 8.

title: easy peanut butter-chocolate chip
directions: Heat oven to 375°. Beat eggs, water and shortening in large bowl. Add peanut butter and 1/2 dry mix. Mix well with wooden spoon. Add chocolate chips. Stir in remaining dry cake mix until smooth. Drop rounded teaspoonfuls about 2-inches apart on ungreased baking sheets. Bake 10 to 12 minutes. Makes about 6 dozen.

title: a good dip
directions: Mix all together and cook at 350° until bubbly.
Serve with big corn chips.
Enjoy!

title: party potatoes
directions: Combine potatoes, sour cream, cream cheese, chives and garlic powder.
Put in greased 2-quart casserole. Combine bread crumbs. Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes. Top with cheese and serve immediately.
You can assemble day before.

title: sloppy joes(large batch)
directions: Cook hamburger, onions, celery and green pepper; drain.
Add soups and tomato sauce; bring to a boil.
Cover, reduce heat and simmer until desired consistency.

title: zucchini patties
directions: Mix all.
Drop into oil in hot skillet.
Brown on one side and turn over.
Turn down heat and cook through.

title: cranberry nut pie
directions: Mix together cranberries, walnuts and 1/2 cup sugar.
Spread on bottom of greased 10-inch pie plate.
Mix together flour, rest of sugar, margarine, eggs and extract.
Pour over cranberry mixture.
Bake 35 to 40 minutes in a preheated 325° oven.

title: 1 egg cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Put flour, sugar, baking powder and salt in mixing bowl.
Add shortening and milk with mixer.
Beat 2 minutes on medium speed or by hand 300 strokes.
Add unbeaten egg, milk, lemon juice, vanilla and almond flavoring.
Beat 2 minutes with mixer or 300 strokes by hand.
Pour in 2 pans and bake 25 to 30 minutes.

title: applesauce bread
directions: Sift flour, spices, soda and salt 3 times in order to mix thoroughly.
Cream shortening well and gradually blend in sugar. Beat in egg with the applesauce.
Add flour mixture gradually, beating after each addition until well blended.
Wash raisins and stir into mixture.
Pour into a greased loaf pan 5 x 9 x 3-inches. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
You may use this recipe for muffins or sheet cake.
For cake it is very good with caramel icing.

title: pumpkin cookies
directions: In a medium bowl, combine flour, baking powder, baking soda, salt, cinnamon and nutmeg.
Set aside.
In a large mixer bowl, cream the butter and sugar.
Add pumpkin, egg and vanilla.
Beat until light and creamy.
Add dry ingredients and mix well.
Drop by rounded tablespoonful onto greased cookie sheets.
Smooth tops of cookies.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for 15 to 20 minutes or until lightly browned.

title: chi chi mochi
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cover with foil.
Bake on the middle shelf at 350° for 1 hour.
Cool and cut into 3/4 x 2-inch pieces.
Roll into potato starch or kinako.

title: jewish apple cake
directions: Grease 10-inch tube pan.
Pour in layer of dough, layer of apples, layer of dough, layer of apples, etc.
Cover with remaining dough.
Bake 1 hour and 15 minutes (or less, check after an hour) at 350°.
Let cool in pan 10 minutes and remove.
Top with drizzle of powdered sugar and milk.

title: carrot cake
directions: Beat eggs, oil and sugar.
Mix well.
Add vanilla.
Sift and stir dry ingredients.
Blend into the oil, eggs, sugar mixture. Stir in the carrots and nuts.
Pour mixture into a greased and floured 10 inch round or spring form pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: "pepperidge farm" squash casserole
directions: Mix squash, margarine and onion.
Mix water, cream of chicken soup, sour cream, salt and pepper.
Pour into squash mixture and mix well.
Layer in a 3-quart casserole, the squash and stuffing mix, ending with stuffing mix.
Top with shredded cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: gloria's rolls
directions: Pour boiling water over sugar and butter; stir until dissolved.
Dissolve yeast in 1/2 cup warm water; add to other mixture.
Then add eggs and flour.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Roll out and cut 4 to 5 hours before cooking.
Bake at 425° for 10 minutes.
Before cooking, dip cut rolls in butter and place on pan.

title: sunflower seed pie
directions: Beat eggs, sugar and butter.
Put seeds in bottom of crust, then mix filling.
Put on top of seeds.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes or until middle is set.
Do not overbake.

title: fish chowder
directions: Cut fat salt pork into small pieces and fry slowly in soup kettle.
Add onions and cook 5 minutes.
