Add potatoes, boiling water and fish, cut into small pieces.
Simmer until potatoes are soft.
Add milk, salt, pepper and parsley.
Melt butter; add flour and blend thoroughly.
Add gradually to chowder, stirring until slightly thickened.
Cook 5 minutes longer.
Pour over Pilot crackers.
Serves 8.

title: raisin bran muffins
directions: Stir together flour, baking powder, salt and sugar.
Set aside.
Measure cereal and milk into mixing bowl.
Stir to combine.
Let stand 1 or 2 minutes or until cereal is softened. Add egg and oil.
Beat well.
Add flour mixture to cereal mixture, stirring only until combined.
Portion batter evenly into 12 greased muffin cups or muffin pan.
Bake in preheated 400° oven about 25 minutes or until golden brown.
Serve warm.

title: pink ice cream punch
directions: Mix lemonade, Kool-Aid and pineapple juice.
Add ginger ale and ice cream just before serving.
Serves 50.

title: chicken corn soup with rivvels
directions: Stir eggs, some salt and flour with a fork.
This will be sticky.
Put 2 tablespoons flour in bowl to dip fingers in.

title: lasagna(serves 8 to 10)
directions: Combine first five ingredients.
Saute until meat is brown. Drain and return to pan.
Add next 7 ingredients.
Simmer for 20 minutes.
Place layer of noodles in greased baking dish or 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix egg and Ricotta cheese.
Spread 1/2 of this on noodles.
Cover with 1/2 of sauce, then 1/2 of cheese.
Repeat layers, ending with cheese on top.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese and paprika.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook and drain broccoli.
Combine soup, onion, egg, mayonnaise, salt and pepper.
Mix with broccoli and put in uncovered baking dish.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Combine melted butter with stuffing mix.
Sprinkle over casserole.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: grandma's fruit salad
directions: Peel oranges,
halve
and slice thin.
Mix with 1/2 cup sugar 2
hours
before
serving.	Drain juice from oranges and pineapple.	Add remaining ingredients.

title: mincemeat cookies
directions: Sift together flour, soda and salt.
Cream shortening and add sugar.
Add eggs and beat thoroughly.
Add mincemeat and beat. Add flour mixture, a little at a time and beat after each addition.
Drop by teaspoon on a greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: congealed salad
directions: Cook Jell-O and pineapple together until it boils.
Mix this with buttermilk and Cool Whip.
Put in refrigerator until firm.

title: st. mary's stuffed ham
directions: Use a corned ham.
If skin is still on ham, remove by paring off with a sharp knife.
Leave skin on hock end.
With fat side up, pierce with long thin knife in slits across first row about 1-inch apart, as deep as possible without going through the bottom.
In some areas the bone will stop you.
On the second row, stagger (like bricks) from the first row, so they are off center. Continue rows as far back as possible.
When all rows are complete, begin stuffing holes with prepared mixture.
It will take at least 1 hour to stuff.
Rest done in low metal baking pan with at least 2-inch edge, to catch juices that come from ham. Completely seal over edge of pan with foil to cook.
Steam bake approximately 20 minutes per pound at 325°.

title: quick chicken skillet
directions: Cook onion and green pepper in margarine in large skillet until onion is tender, but not brown.
Add cooked potatoes, cooked chicken, picante sauce, cumin and salt; mix well.
Simmer about 5 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Top with cheese; cover skillet and let cheese melt.
Serve with additional picante sauce if desired.

title: corn salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together in large salad bowl.
Refrigerate salad at least 1 hour for best flavor.

title: lemon bars
directions: For crust, combine flour, powdered sugar. Cut in butter until crumbly.
Press into bottom of 9x13 baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 mins.
Combine eggs, sugar, baking powder, lemon juice and flour.
Pour over crust and
bake for 20 minutes at 350°. Cool. Sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix chicken, broth, soup and stuffing.
Mix together.
Pour into a casserole dish and bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes or until brown.

title: squash casserole
directions: Mix all together well. Put in buttered casserole dish. Bake at 370° for 40 minutes.

title: italian chocolate roll(cookies)
directions: Melt chocolate chips in condensed milk in top of double boiler. Stir in walnuts.
Turn off heat and cool.
Combine flour, sugar, baking powder and salt.
Cut in shortening.
Add egg and milk; stir.
Divide dough into 5 balls.
Roll out each dough ball between sheets of wax paper.
Spread 1/5 of chocolate nut mixture on rolled out dough.
Roll up, pinching sides as you go.
Pinch ends of dough.
Repeat with remaining dough balls and chocolate mixture. Place rolls on a foil lined baking sheet.
Bake for 15 to 20 minutes in a 325° to 350° oven.
Do not overbake.
When rolls are finished baking, remove from oven and let cool completely.
Before serving, cut in slices.

title: big batch brownies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease bottom only of two 13 x 9-inch pans.
In large bowl, combine all brownie ingredients; beat about 75 strokes with spoon.
Spread half of batter evenly into each prepared pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Do not overbake.
Cool completely.
Frost brownies as directed below.

title: visitor's fruit salad
directions: Blend in large mixing bowl sour cream, Cool Whip, pudding mix and small amount of pineapple juice.
Add all fruits and coconut (if used).
Mix slowly.
Fold in marshmallows.
Chill.
Cover until ready to serve.

title: 4-bean casserole
directions: Fry bacon.
Save about 1/4 cup drippings for frying.
Drain first 3 cans of beans; add pork and beans and mix together.
Fry onion in bacon drippings until tender and drain on paper toweling.

title: medium cream sauce
directions: Melt butter over low heat in saucepan.
Blend in flour and seasonings.
Cook over low heat, stirring, until mixture is smooth and bubbly.
Remove from heat.
Stir in milk.
Bring to boil, stirring constantly.
Boil 1 minute.
Makes 1 cup of sauce.
Use with Frankfurter Supper Dish.

title: cheesy hash browns
directions: Bake 350° for 30 minutes.

title: meat loaf
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine all ingredients in large mixing bowl, mix well.
Place in loaf pan or shape in baking dish.
Bake for 1 1/2 hours or until center is done.

title: cajun spice rub
directions: Mix well.
Rub on all sides of chicken before cooking.

title: hamburger surprise
directions: Divide hamburger into four parts.
Shape into patties.
Place each patty into center of a 10-inch square of foil.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Cover with slices of onion and potatoes.
Wrap in foil.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes.
Can also be cooked on grill.

title: blueberry kuchen
directions: Blend together flour, salt, sugar and margarine.
Add vinegar and toss with fork.
Then press into 9-inch round pan.
Pat up around sides.

title: chocolate meringue pie
directions: In saucepan, combine sugar, cornstarch, chocolate and salt. Mix well.
Gradually stir in milk, mixing smooth.

title: linguine with veggies
directions: Cook linguine as directed on package.
In frypan or wok, place olive oil, garlic and onion (if desired).
Add broccoli flowerets and soy sauce.
Cook until broccoli is slightly soft.
Pour cooked veggies over linguine and sprinkle with Parmesan cheese, if desired.

title: banana cake
directions: Cream shortening, sugar and egg yolks together.
Add vanilla, bananas, milk and vinegar.
Add sifted dry ingredients.
Stir well. Fold in beaten egg whites.
Put into two 7-inch layer cake pans.
Bake at 375° about 25 minutes.

title: cherry pineapple vinegar cake
directions: Put vinegar in milk.
Add soda.
Stir briskly.
Cream butter, sugar and flour together and add the fruit and allspice.
Fold into the milk and beat well.
Bake in a well-greased pan at 350° for 1 hour.

title: chicken curry from india
directions: Cut chicken into pieces and wash.
Grate onions.
Cut tomatoes. Grind to a paste ginger and garlic.
Heat oil in pan and fry onions until golden brown.
Add ginger-garlic paste, tomatoes and yogurt. Fry until oil separates from mixture.
Add chicken, chili powder, turmeric, coriander, cumin, (c + c + c powder) 9th ingredient and salt.
Fry until chicken is slightly brown.
Add 1 2/3 cup water. Let it cook on medium heat for about 15 minutes.
See to it that the chicken is tender and remove from the heat.
Garnish with fresh cilantro and serve with rice or tortillas, bread or rolls.
Tastes great.

title: corn and zucchini medley
directions: Combine the walnuts, garlic, butter, and oil in a 10 inch skillet. Cook over medium low to medium heat until walnuts are lightly browned.
This could take up to 10 minutes. Remove the walnuts from the pan, using a slotted spoon.
Add the zucchini, onions, and red bell pepper. Add more butter and oil, if needed. Cook over medium heat until zucchini is tender but not mushy. Add salt, black pepper, and corn.
Simmer for about 5 minutes until corn is heated.
Stir in walnuts.
Makes about 10 servings.

title: stir-fry vegetables
directions: Brown
meat
in
peanut oil, until tender, using a wok, preferably.
Add
bouillon.
Add fresh vegetables first, then frozen.
We
use carrots, celery, onions, snow peas, broccoli, cauliflower,
pepper,
tomatoes,
bamboo shoots, bean sprouts, water chestnuts or squash.

title: yam mallow crisp
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Place yams in a 10 x 6-inch shallow, ovenproof dish.
Pour orange juice over yams.
Set aside.

title: country crust bread
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Stir in sugar, salt, eggs, oil and 3 cups of the flour.
Beat until smooth.
Mix in enough remaining flour to make dough easy to handle.
Turn dough onto lightly floured board.
Knead until smooth and elastic (8 to 10 minutes).
Place in greased bowl; turn greased side up.
(At this point dough can be refrigerated 3 to 4 days.)
Cover; let rise in warm place until double, about 1 hour.
(Dough is ready if impression remains.)
Punch down dough; divide in half.
Roll each half into rectangle, 18 x 9-inches.
Roll up, beginning at short side; with side of hand press each end to seal.
Fold ends under loaf.
Place seam side down, in greased loaf pan (9 x 5 x 3-inches).
Brush loaves with salad oil.
Let rise until double, about 1 hour.
Heat oven to 375°.
Place loaves on lower oven rack so that tops of pans are in center of oven.
Pans shouldn't touch each other or sides of oven.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes or until deep golden brown and loaves sound hollow when tapped.
Remove from pan; brush with butter.
Cool on wire racks.

title: onion casserole
directions: Saute onions in margarine until soft.
Add flour, broth, sherry and pepper.
Mix together and place in casserole.
Coat with a little margarine and add croutons and Parmesan cheese to taste.
Bake, covered, at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: chicken-stuffing bake
directions: Over high heat, heat butter and 3/4 cup milk to scalding.
In a large bowl, pour hot milk mixture over stuffing.
Toss to mix well.
Put stuffing mixture into buttered 12 x 8-inch baking dish.
tags: Campbell's condensed golden cream of mushroom soup

title: ice tup sicles(day care treats)
directions: Mix together and store in airtight container.
Take 6 tablespoons of mixture and mix into 3/4 cup boiling water.
Add 3/4 cup cold water or fruit juice.
Pour into Tupperware Ice Tups or paper cups and freeze.

title: orange taffy
directions: In a saucepan, combine first four ingredients.
Cook and stir over medium heat until sugar is dissolved.
Bring to a rapid boil and cook until candy thermometer reads 245°.
Add cream and butter.
Stir until mixture reaches 245° again.
Pour into a greased pan and cool.
When cool enough to handle, roll into 1 1/2 inch logs or 1 inch balls.
Wrap individually in foil.
Twist ends.

title: simple 7-layer dip
directions: Spread softened cream cheese over cake plate.
Spread bean dip over cream cheese.
Cover with salsa.
Layer lettuce, tomatoes, cheese and olives on top.
Dip with chips.

title: coffee banana smoothie
directions: In blender or container, combine frozen bananas, milk, yogurt, cinnamon and nutmeg.
Cover and blend until smooth.
To serve, pour into glasses, if desired.
Garnish with fresh bananas and mint. Makes 2 (1 1/2 cup) servings.

title: fried oysters
directions: In a mixing bowl, beat together egg and milk.
Dip oysters, one by one into egg mixture.
Dredge oysters in corn meal that has been seasoned with salt and pepper.
Panfry in oil in a skillet over medium heat until golden brown.
Serves 4.

title: brownie cake
directions: Melt margarine in pan and add sugar; mix well.
Add eggs and cocoa and mix well.
Add flour and vanilla.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Ice cake and chocolate chips, if desired.

title: skillet sausage
directions: Brown sausage, stirring to crumble.
Drain and remove from heat.
Stir in next 4 ingredients.
Cover and cook over medium heat 10 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Add cooled pasta and sour cream.
Stir until mixture is thoroughly heated.
Do not boil.

title: texas baked beans
directions: In skillet, partially cook bacon.
Drain and set aside.
In mixing bowl, stir together pork and beans, brown sugar, catsup, onion, Worcestershire sauce and mustard. Turn mixture into a bean pot or a 2-quart casserole.
Lay partially cooked bacon slices on top.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° about 2 hours.
Serves 10.

title: sugar coated brownies
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake at 350° for about 20 minutes.
Cut and roll in confectioners sugar while hot.

title: easy refrigerator rolls
directions: In mixing bowl, dissolve yeast in water.
Add sugar, salt and about half of flour.
Beat thoroughly 2 minutes; add egg and oil. Beat in gradually the rest of flour until smooth.
Cover with damp cloth.
Place in refrigerator.
Punch down occasionally as dough rises at least
2 hours or overnight.
Shape while cold into rolls and place on greased baking sheet.
Brush tops with melted butter; let rise until light, 1 1/2 to 2 hours.
Heat oven to 400°.
Bake 12 to 15 minutes.
Makes 4 dozen.

title: fruit dip
directions: Combine all ingredients and chill.
Wonderful with strawberries.

title: broccoli cornbread
directions: Mix all the ingredients together and bake in well-greased 9 x 12-inch baking pan.
Bake in a preheated 375° oven for 45 minutes.

title: creamy cauliflower soup
directions: Wash cauliflower and break into flowerets.
Combine water, onion and bouillon cubes in large saucepan; bring to a boil.
Add cauliflower; cover and cook until tender (10 to 15 minutes). Spoon cauliflower mixture into blender and process until smooth. Melt butter over low heat; add flour, stirring until smooth.
Cook 1 minute, stirring constantly.
Gradually add milk.
Cook over medium heat until thickened and bubbly.
Stir in salt, nutmeg and pepper.
Return cauliflower mixture to a large saucepan.
Stir in white sauce.
Cook over low heat until well heated, stirring constantly.
Serve immediately.
Sprinkle with cheese.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Cook the first three ingredients until it spins a thread.
Add raw peanuts and cook until nuts pop.
Remove from heat and add margarine and soda.
Pour into greased baking pan.
When cool, break into pieces.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Cream cheese and sugar until light and fluffy.
Add peanut butter and milk.
Beat until smooth and cream.
Fold in Cool Whip and pour into graham cracker crust.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix meat, bread crumbs, Accent, soup mix, eggs, ketchup and warm water.
Put in meat loaf pan and cover with 2 strips of bacon. Pour tomato soup or sauce over meat mixture.
Bake 1 hour at 350°. Serves 6.

title: baked squash
directions: Wash and cut squash.
Cook until tender; drain thoroughly, then mash.	Add all other ingredients.
Place in baking dish sprayed with vegetable spray.

title: buckeye bonbon
directions: Mix well peanut butter, margarine, vanilla and powdered sugar. First peanut butter and margarine.
Add sugar, little at a time. Roll into balls and chill overnight.
Melt chocolate bits and paraffin.
In double boiler, melt the ingredients.
Stick toothpick in balls and dip in chips.
Chill on waxed paper.
It can be stored in a cool place.

title: chex party mix
directions: Mix the cereals, pretzel thins and nuts.
Mix the remaining ingredients.
Pour liquid mixture over cereals.
Coat bottom of a large, deep pan with Wesson oil.
Bake at 200° for 1 1/2 to 2 hours, stirring and mixing together.

title: ham rolls
directions: In a small bowl, mix all the ingredients until creamy.
(A few drops of milk may be added.)
Spread on ham slices and roll each slice like a jelly roll.
Put in refrigerator 3 or 4 hours.
Slice in 1/4-inch size and serve on crackers.

title: layered mexican cornbread
directions: Mix all except cheese together.
Put 1/2 of the mixture in pan, then half of the cheese and repeat.
Bake 1 hour at 325°.

title: banana bread
directions: Sift together flour, soda and salt.
Cream shortening; blend in sugar.
Add eggs one at a time and beat until fluffy.
Add flour mixture alternately with bananas and liquid, beating well after each addition.
Turn into greased loaf pan and bake 60 to 70 minutes or until done at 350°.
Cool several hours before slicing. Makes 1 loaf.

title: rotini salad
directions: Mix all ingredients well in a large bowl. Cover and refrigerate overnight. Stir well before serving. Dressing will be somewhat thin, but will be fine next day.

title: potato casserole
directions: Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Use a greased dish.

title: salami
directions: Mix together very good.
Make into rolls about 1 1/2 to 2-inches diameter and 10 to 12-inches long.
Wrap in foil and refrigerate 24 hours.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.
Remove foil.
Pat dry.
Cool and rewrap in foil.
Refrigerate or freeze.

title: sock it to me cake
directions: Mix well the cake mix, sugar and oil.
Add 1 egg at a time; beat one minute after each.
Beat in sour cream, then nuts.
Pour 1/2 of batter into well-greased Bundt pan.
Sprinkle brown sugar and cinnamon on top, then pour in rest of batter.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: barbecue cocktail wieners
directions: Combine all ingredients, but wieners, in large saucepan. Bring to a boil and pour into crock-pot.
Next, brown wieners slightly in frying pan and then mix with sauce in crock-pot.
It's best to do this at least 2 hours ahead so they can simmer on low in crock-pot before serving.
Serve with toothpicks directly from crock-pot.
Check them occasionally to be sure they do not dry out.

title: braised celery
directions: Place celery and onion in a saucepan with 1/2 inch boiling water and salt.
Cover and cook until celery is just tender-crisp, about 15 to 20 minutes.
Drain, if necessary.
Blend the cornstarch with the milk and add to the celery.
Add salt and pepper.
Cook, stirring, until slightly thickened.
Sprinkle with the cheese; toss lightly until the cheese begins to melt.
This is delicious as a luncheon or supper dish with crisp bacon.
Serves 4.

title: frances bivins' "organdy" magnolia leaves
directions: Select about 25 fresh magnolia leaves.
Dissolve lye in 6 cups water in a glass or enamel container.
Heat the solution to simmering and simmer the leaves 30 minutes, stirring with a wooden spoon.

Remove and place in solution of vinegar and 3 cups water. Lift leaves out, one at a time, and rinse under running water. Brush with a soft brush, from stem-end down, until transparent skeleton leaf remains.
Bleach with bleach and 2 cups water.
Rinse.

title: peanut butter and chocolate no cook cookies
directions: Follow these directions very carefully.

title: martha washington chocolate balls
directions: Mix well and let sit overnight.
Shape into balls.
Dip in chocolate.
Place on wax paper until cool.

title: hospitality punch
directions: Combine fruit juices and tea.
Fill punch bowl 1/4 full of juices and tea.
Add sherbet and ginger ale.
Serve with a pineapple spear as garnish.
Makes 50 servings.

title: tomato basil salad
directions: Place 2 or 3 slices of tomato on salad plates.
Top with cheese; sprinkle chopped basil, salt and pepper, then drizzle with olive oil.
Chill covered until you serve.

title: orange cake
directions: Yellow cake mix may be used for the layers, if desired.

title: harvest soup
directions: Saute mushrooms, carrots and onion in corn oil.
Spread until lightly browned in Dutch oven over medium-high flame.
Stir in barley, salt, garlic salt, pepper, bay leaves, water and broth. Bring to a boil; reduce flame, cover and simmer 45 minutes or until barley is tender.
Stir in spinach and cook, covered, an additional 10 minutes.
Makes 8 servings.

title: bumsteads(sandwich)
directions: Mix all together. Cover halves of hamburger buns with some of this mixture.
Broil until bubbly and golden brown. Good as a main luncheon dish.

title: 24-hour beef marinade
directions: Soak meat for 24 hours in refrigerator.
(I use this to marinate meat before making shish-kabobs.)

title: holiday punch
directions: Prepare Kool-Aid and 1 cup of sugar with one quart of water. Freeze one pint of the Kool-Aid in a circle mold or some Christmas mold or any holiday mold.

title: baked flounder with potatoes
directions: Wash flounder and place in baking pan.
Slice potatoes and onion and place on
top of flounder.
Salt and pepper to
taste. Place bacon strips on top of fish and potatoes.
Cover with foil and bake at 350° approximately 1 1/2 hours or until fish is flaky.

title: sausage-cheese balls
directions: Add the sausage and the cheese (both at room temperature) to the Bisquick.
Use 1 teaspoon of the mixture to form a ball. Place on baking sheet.
Repeat until mixture is gone.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: lattice top chicken pie
directions: Combine soup, milk, salt, chicken and vegetables with 1/2 cup cheese and 1/2 can onions.
Place in baking dish.
Bake covered at 375° for 20 minutes.
Unwrap crescent rolls.
Separate into two triangles.
Press together perforated cuts.
Cut each square into 3 strips.
Place strips on top to form lattice top.
Bake uncovered 15 minutes.
Top lattice with remaining cheese and onions after the 15 minutes and bake uncovered 3 to 5 minutes or until onions are golden brown.

title: hot chocolate mix
directions: Mix powdered sugar and powdered milk together.
Then add remaining ingredients.
Keep in airtight container.
Use 3 to 4 heaping teaspoonfuls per cup.

title: oreo delight
directions: Crumble cookies; combine with ice cream and Cool Whip. Freeze.

title: sour cream apple cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease a 9 or 10-inch tube pan.

title: erma's beef 'n barley(in honor of erma schluter)
directions: Saute in skillet butter, chopped onions and pearl barley until brown.
Add 2 cups water; cover and simmer 15 minutes.
Add soup, mushrooms, salt, pimento, Worcestershire sauce and 2 cups more water to mixture.
Cut steak into 1-inch cubes or strips.
Roll in bread crumbs, seeds, salt and paprika, which were combined.
Brown in shortening and add to the barley mixture.
Pour all into 3-quart casserole; cover.
Place in preheated oven at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: fresh fruit dessert pizza
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
In medium bowl, combine Eagle Brand, sour cream, lemon juice and vanilla; mix well.
Chill.
In large mixer bowl, beat margarine and sugar until fluffy; mix in flour, oats and walnuts until thoroughly blended.
On lightly oiled pizza pan or baking sheet, press dough into 12-inch circle forming rim around edge.
Prick with fork.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes or until golden brown.
Cool.
Spoon filling evenly onto crust.
Arrange fruit on top of filling.
Garnish with mint leaves.
Chill before serving.
Refrigerate leftovers.

title: homemade jelly
directions: Cook fruit for about 10 minutes and strain, saving all juices. Measure juice and place into a large pot.
Add Sure-Jell; bring to a full boil.
Stir in sugar; bring to a rolling boil, stirring constantly.
Boil for 2 minutes.
Remove from heat and skim.
Pour into sterile jars and seal.

title: raspberry bars
directions: Cream together the margarine and brown sugar.
Add flour, salt and oats to creamed mixture.
Mix well.
Press 1/2 of crumb mixture in a greased 9 x 12-inch pan.
Spread raspberry preserves on mixture, then sprinkle remaining mixture on top.
Bake at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Cool completely before cutting into squares.

title: frosted lime jello salad
directions: Mix hot water and Jell-O; stir and refrigerate until like an unbeaten egg.
Add pineapple, cottage cheese and celery and pour into an 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan.
Refrigerate until firm.
Frost with mixture of cream cheese, lemon juice and mayonnaise.
Cut into squares.

title: pork tenderloin
directions: Season pork to taste.
Mix water into egg and add pepper.
Dip in egg/water mixture, then cover with bread crumbs.
Allow to set on wax paper for 20 minutes.
Brown pork patties and place in glass baking dish.
Fry bacon until crispy and crumble over pork.
Place raw sliced onions on top.
Add mushrooms.
Season with oregano. Add a can of bouillon.
Place foil on top and refrigerate until ready to cook.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.
Do not preheat oven.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients together, except for chocolate chips and chopped nuts.
Add chocolate chips and nuts after all mixed.
Drop by rounded teaspoonfuls on a cookie sheet (ungreased).
Bake at 375° for 9 to 11 minutes, then let cool.

title: hot spice russian tea
directions: Mix together, simmer and serve hot.
Pretty red tea that is extremely good and good for you.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Combine sugar and peanut butter.
Put 3/4 of the crumbs in a baked pie shell.
Cook the pudding according to directions on box. Cool a little and pour over crumbs.
After the pie is cold, spread the Cool Whip on the top and sprinkle the remaining crumbs on top.

title: chili cheese dip
directions: Brown ground beef and drain.
Melt Velveeta cheese.
Add all ingredients together and keep in the crock-pot on low heat.

title: barbecue chicken sauce
directions: Heat ingredients just until butter or margarine is melted. Pour over chicken; let marinate all day.
Grill chicken, dipping in sauce when turning.
This is the only barbecued chicken my girls will eat!

title: smoked pork with kraut
directions: Place flour in a 14 x 20-inch cooking bag. Shake to coat inside.
Place pork in bag. Close with twisted tie. Place slits in top of bag.
Bake at 350° for 2 hours.
Remove from oven and open bag.
Combine remaining ingredients.
Mix well. Spoon over and around pork.
Re-tie bag and bake for 40 minutes longer.

title: chocolate chip cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour in greased bundt pan. Bake at 350° for 40-50 minutes.
Let cool before removing from pan.
Make sure cake is completely cool before icing.

title: pasta salad
directions: Boil pasta until tender and drain; add other ingredients and refrigerate overnight before serving.

title: asparagus casserole
directions: Layer these ingredients into a large pan.

title: cheese sauce for vegetables(microwave)
directions: Combine all ingredients in blender.
Process until well blended.
Pour into 4 cup measure and microwave 3 to 4 minutes until thick.

title: b j's taco casserole
directions: Brown hamburg and onion and drain.
Add taco sauce and simmer for 30 minutes.
Heat soups together.
Layer 9 x 13-inch pan with Doritos, 1/2 meat mixture, 1/2 kidney beans and 1/2 cheese. Repeat, omitting 2nd layer of cheese.
Pour soups over everything and top with remaining cheese.
Place Doritos along sides of pans. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: old fashion potato soup
directions: Combine all ingredients in a saucepan.
Barely cover with water.
Cover and cook on medium heat until potatoes are a little mushy.
Remove from heat.
Make a white sauce with 2 tablespoons flour to 1/2 cup of milk.
Stir into vegetables.
Do not drain off water.
Add an additional 1 cup milk and 3 tablespoons butter. Diced ham may be added.
Reheat and serve.

title: make ahead potatoes
directions: Combine and boil potatoes, salt and 1 stick of butter until done; drain.
Add other stick of butter and beat with mixer.
Add cream cheese; blend well.
Add Pet milk until a little thin; put into baking dish.
Cool completely, cover and refrigerate.
When ready to use, dot with butter and microwave until warm, stirring often.

title: tuna noodle supper
directions: Cook noodles according to package directions.
While noodles are cooking, preheat oven to 350°.
In a 9 x 13-inch baking pan, combine the soups, milk, tuna with the water, and mixed vegetables.
Drain cooked noodles and add to soup mixture.
Toss until all is blended.
Top with crushed cracker crumbs and bake for 30 minutes.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: caramel ice cream
directions: Mix sugar and eggs.
Add creams.
Pour into 1 gallon freezer. Finish filling with regular milk.

title: no name cake
directions: Put eggs and brown sugar in mixing bowl; cream well.
Add vanilla and flour; mix, then add the coconut and pecans and mix by hand with a spoon.
Pour into prepared 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes or until done.

title: easy cobbler
directions: Melt butter in pan; mix the flour, sugar and milk.
Pour over melted butter.
Add fruit to the top of the mixture in pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: oven omelet brunch
directions: Heat oven to 325°.
In oven, melt butter in baking dish (13 1/2 x 9 x 2-inch).
Tilt dish to coat bottom with butter.
In a large mixing bowl, beat eggs, sour cream, milk and salt until blended.
Stir in onion.
Pour into dish.
Bake until eggs are set but still moist, about 35 minutes.

title: summer squash casserole
directions: Cook squash with onion in boiling salt water as directed above; drain well.
Combine soup and sour cream; stir in carrots. Fold in drained squash and onion; melt margarine and toss with stuffing mix.
Spread 1/2 stuffing mixture in a 12 x 7 1/2 x 2-inch baking dish.
Spoon vegetable mixture atop.
Sprinkle with remaining stuffing mixture.
Bake at 350° until heated through, 25 to 30 minutes.
Makes 6 servings.

title: rolled chicken and dumplings
directions: Cook chicken in water on stove top, de-bone and set aside meat. Add cream of chicken soup to broth.

title: easy peanut butter chocolate chip cookies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease and lightly flour a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
Prepare cake batter according to directions using eggs, water and oil.
Blend in peanut butter.
Spoon half of batter into pan.
Sprinkle 3/4 cup of chocolate chips over batter. Gently spread remaining batter over top.
Sprinkle remaining 3/4 cup chips and peanuts over batter.
Bake 45 minutes or until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean; let cool in pan.

title: mexican bean soup("a nice light soup")
directions: In a 2-qt. saucepan, cook bacon until crisp.

Add onion, celery and garlic; cook, covered over low heat, stirring occasionally, about 10 minutes or until vegetables are tender, but not brown. Add green chiles, beans, pepper, chili powder and hot pepper sauce. Stir in chicken broth.
Bring to boiling.
Serve very hot in bowls; pass cheese and tortilla chips to sprinkle over each serving.
To add a more piquant flavor, add a garnish of chopped onion and chopped tomato.

title: puffball or quick tea donuts
directions: Beat eggs.
Add sugar and milk.
Sift dry ingredients together and add to liquid.
Beat thoroughly and add melted fat.
Add enough flour to make batter stiff enough to hold a spoon in a standing position.
Drop by spoonfuls into deep fat at 375°. Remove when brown and drain on absorbent paper.
Makes approximately 4 dozen.

title: chicken and dressing casserole
directions: Boil breasts until tender; save broth.
Remove meat and line bottom of casserole with chicken.
Mix soup and sour cream and put on chicken.
Take 1/2 cup of broth and 1/2 cup water and simmer.
Add 1 stick of oleo; add stuffing and mix.
Put stuffing on top of casserole (be sure stuffing is moist; add more water if necessary).
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: corn bread
directions: Mix in order given.
Bake at 350°.

title: meat loaf "muffins"
directions: Mix together first 5 ingredients.
Form meatballs.
Put in double paper muffin cups in muffin pan.
Bake 40 minutes at 350°. When done, spoon tomato sauce over "muffins."
Kids love this!

title: taffy (1923)(over 50 years old)
directions: Place all ingredients in a pan and cook, without stirring, until small amount hardens when dropped in cold water.
Pour onto a well-buttered or greased plate and allow it to cool enough to handle.
Pull until white.
Form into a flat strip about two inches wide.
Cut into lengths with clean scissors.
Wrap in buttered tissue paper.

title: a trio of cheese dips in red apples
directions: Make diagonal cuts near top of each apple, each knife stroke at right angles to preceding one, and cut to center of apples. Lift off top; hollow apples using melon ball cutter.
Mix 2 tablespoons lemon juice with 2 tablespoons water; dip apple cups in lemon mixture and drain well.
(I use Fruit Fresh.)
Tops may be used as decorative float in punch, after dipping in lemon. Garnish with mint, parsley or salad burnet.

title: family casserole
directions: Brown hamburger and onions.
Stir in tomato soup and water. Add beans and noodles into meat.
Pour in large baking dish and top with cheese.
Bake at 375° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: party sausage balls
directions: Shape sausage into balls and brown; drain.
Combine the remaining ingredients into a frying pan.
Return sausage to the mixture; simmer, covered, about 15 minutes.

title: white chocolate cookies
directions: In a large mixing bowl, cream butter and shortening. Gradually add sugars; beat until light and fluffy.
Add egg; mix well.
Combine flour, soda and salt; add to creamed mixture. Blend in vanilla.
Stir in chocolate and nuts.
Cover and chill dough for 1 hour.
Drop by heaping tablespoonfuls about 3-inches apart on ungreased cookie sheets.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 14 minutes or until lightly browned.
Let stand a few minutes before removing cookies to a wire rack to cool.
Yield:
about 2 1/2 dozen cookies.

title: almond bark candy
directions: Melt bark in double boiler.
Stir in peanut butter.
Remove from heat and stir in Rice Krispies and peanuts.
Spread on ungreased jelly roll pan.
When hard, cut in squares.

title: strawberry bread
directions: Mix all together.
Spray 2 bread pans with Pam.
Fill each 1/2 full with mixture.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for about 30 to 45 minutes.
Serve hot or cooled.

title: twinkies pudding
directions: Line a 9 x 12-inch glass Pyrex with Twinkies.
Mix the cold milk and pudding; spread on cakes.
Layer the drained pineapple, then bananas, then Cool Whip.
Decorate with cherries and nuts.

title: chicken liver wrapped in bacon
directions: Drop chicken liver in boiling water to which 1 teaspoon salt has been added and allow to stay only until they are firm.
Drain livers.
Wrap each liver with a slice of bacon and secure with a cocktail pick.
Fry in hot fat until bacon is crisp.
Drop into colander lined with paper towel to absorb excess.
Serve hot.

title: quick-n-easy spinach egg scramble
directions: In a skillet, cook bacon until crisp. Add drained spinach and stir until hot. Pour in eggs with salt, pepper and nutmeg added. Stir until egg is firm. Remove from heat and serve hot. Serves 5 or 6.

title: melissa's pea salad(my daughter's favorite)
directions: Rinse peas and let drain in a colander.
Mix cheese, onions, mayonnaise, mustard and salt.
Add peas and peanuts.
Refrigerate a few hours.

title: hot cranberry cider
directions: In a saucepan, combine the cranberry juice, cider, nectar, cinnamon and nutmeg.
Bring to a boil; lower heat to simmer for 10 minutes.
Add rum and butter.
Serve steaming hot in mugs. Delicious on chilly Wisconsin evenings.

title: salsa(new mexico style)
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Serve in bowl to spoon onto tacos, tostados or tamales.
Use as a dip with corn chips.

title: baked pineapple
directions: Spread pineapple in bottom of baking dish.
Mix together flour and sugar; sprinkle over pineapple.
Top with cheese and crushed crackers.
Dot with margarine.
Bake at 325° until bubbly.

title: twice bake potatoes
directions: Scrub potatoes thoroughly and use a fork to prick potatoes. Bake at 425° for 40 to 60 minutes or until done.
Cut lengthwise strip from top of potatoes.
Scoop out potatoes, being careful not to break shells.

title: baking powder biscuits
directions: Mix dry ingredients. Cut in Crisco. Add milk and stir together quickly. Drop by tablespoon on greased baking sheet. Bake at 450° for 10 minutes.

title: raisin bran muffins
directions: Mix together dry ingredients.
Mix together wet ingredients. Mix wet and dry ingredients together.
Fill greased muffin tins 2/3 full.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Yields 2 dozen standard size muffins.

title: whipped cream frosting(bakery style)
directions: Whip shortening and water together until creamy.
Add vanilla. Add enough powdered sugar to hold its shape.
This makes a nice frosting or filling for your cakes.
Good and simple!

title: hawaiian holiday punch
directions: In punch bowl, mix juice and ginger ale.
Mix in strawberries. Float orange and lime slices on top.
Serves 14.

title: nan's pineapple cake
directions: Mix the ingredients with a spoon and pour into a greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: spice cookies
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Lightly spoon flour into measuring cup; level off.
In large bowl, combine all ingredients except 1/4 cup sugar; mix until well blended.
Shape into 1-inch balls.
Place 2 inches apart on ungreased cookie sheets.
Flatten with the bottom of a glass dipped in the 1/4 cup sugar.
Bake at 375° for 7 to 9 minutes or until lightly browned.
Let stand 1 minute before removing from cookie sheet.
Cool on racks.
Store in tightly covered container.
Makes 5 dozen cookies.

title: skillet burgers
directions: Brown ground beef, then add all other ingredients.
Simmer 30 to 45 minutes.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Pour in pie shell and bake for 1 hour or until set at 325°.

title: break away bread
directions: Dissolve
yeast
in lukewarm water.
Pour boiling water over shortening in large bowl and dissolve.
Add salt, sugar, flour, eggs
and
dissolved
yeast.
Mix well and refrigerate overnight.

title: carrot cake
directions: Cream sugar, oil and eggs 1 at a time. Sift together flour and cinnamon. Add flour and carrots to batter. Bake in 3 layers at 350° about 30 to 35 minutes.

title: white fruit cake
directions: Chop nuts and fruit in medium pieces.
Dredge with 1/4 cup of the flour.
Cream butter and sugar until fluffy.
Add well beaten eggs and blend.
Sift remaining 1 1/2 cups flour and baking powder together.
Mix into egg and butter mixture and blend well.
Add vanilla and lemon extracts and mix well.
Add fruit and nuts and blend well.
Grease 10-inch tube pan, line with paper and grease again.
Pour in batter.
Place in cold oven and turn oven on 250°. Bake 3 hours.
Cool in pan on rack before removing.

title: richard's spinach
directions: Microwave spinach with 1 tablespoon of water for 7 minutes. At low heat, add remaining ingredients until creamy.

title: dill pickles with pot roast
directions: Brown roast in oil; place in covered casserole with all items except sour cream. Simmer until tender (2 hours); add sour cream and simmer. Serve with rice. Delicious.....

title: chicken and rice casserole
directions: Heat and stir soups together with melted butter.
Add rice and stir.
Add salt, pepper and poultry seasoning to taste.
Pour into large casserole.
Lay chicken pieces on top of rice-soup mixture. Bake for 2 1/2 hours at 275°.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Boil vegetables according to instructions.
Drain and mix with celery, onion, mayonnaise and cheese.
Crumble crackers and sprinkle on top.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: cheese straws
directions: Mix all ingredients thoroughly. Batter will be very stiff and can be mixed better with hands. Press through a cookie press to make 3-inch pieces and place on an ungreased cookie sheet. Bake in 250° oven for 45 minutes. Cool thoroughly and then store in an airtight container.

title: german sweet and sour beans and carrots
directions: In a saucepan cook carrots, covered in salted water until tender.
Add green beans.
Cover and cook 5 minutes.
Drain well. In a skillet, cook bacon; drain.
Save 1 tablespoon drippings. Cook onion in drippings.
Add apple, vinegar, sugar and salt. Cover and cook until tender.
Add carrots and beans; heat through. Sprinkle with crumbled bacon.

title: fuzzy navel shake
directions: Combine all ingredients in container of blender; cover and process until smooth.
Serve immediately.
Yields 2 cups.

title: russian tea cakes
directions: Cream the butter until light and fluffy.
Add powdered sugar; mix well.
Add sifted flour; mix well.
Add vanilla and nuts; mix well.

title: dill dip or dressing
directions: Mix and refrigerate.
Serve on pumpernickel bread or crackers. Also may be used for dressing on salads.

title: low-fat meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients, except catsup, together.
Form into a loaf and put in a baking pan.
Put catsup on top.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour until done.

title: cheese and sausage delights
directions: In mixing bowl, combine cheese, butter, flour, salt and pepper.
Beat with electric mixer on low speed.
Stir in sausage. Make dough into 1-inch balls.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet. Bake at 375° for 20 minutes until light brown.
Can be made ahead and frozen.
Makes around 5 dozen.

title: ham with cherry sauce
directions: Slash fat edge of ham slice.
Place ham in 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish. Heat in moderate oven (350°) for about 30 minutes. Serve with warm Cherry Sauce.

title: orange delight
directions: Heat pineapple and Jell-O enough to dissolve Jell-O.
Cool. Mix Cool Whip and buttermilk and combine with gelatin mix; pour into lightly greased serving dish (9 x 13-inch dish).
Can add 1/2 cup chopped ???, if desired.
Chill until firm.

title: halloween popcorn balls
directions: Pop the corn and put into a large bowl.
Bring sugar, syrup and gelatin to a boil in a saucepan, stirring until sugar and gelatin are dissolved.
Pour over popcorn; mix until popcorn is completely covered.
Form balls quickly with buttered hands; place on waxed paper to cool.
Yield: 18 balls or more depending on size.
These have been a favorite of the trick or treaters for many years.
Red and green gelatin can be used to make Christmas popcorn balls.

title: baking powder biscuits
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Sift flour with baking powder and salt. Cut in butter to make coarse meal.
Stir in milk until dough forms a ball.
Knead dough on lightly floured surface and roll out to 1/2-inch thickness.
Cut with biscuit cutter.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet and bake for 10 to 15 minutes.
Makes 12 two-inch biscuits.

title: grandma mary's soup
directions: *May choose any soup meat, on or off bone.

title: gooey butter cake
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients and put into greased 9 x 13-inch pan. Blend cream cheese, eggs and powdered sugar until smooth.
Pour over first mixture.
Bake for 40 minutes at 325° or until top is golden.
Cool and sprinkle with powdered sugar.
Very rich.

title: mexican corn soup
directions: Cook 3 ears of corn 10 minutes.
Remove from water and cool. Cut corn off cobs and place in a stock pot.
Cut corn from uncooked cobs, scraping the cob for juices and add to the cooked corn.
Add stock.
In a small skillet, saute onion in butter until limp.
Add to the stock pot.
Add tomato sauce, salt and pepper and simmer 20 minutes until corn is tender.
Add cream, garlic, cumin and sugar and heat through.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: pie filling cake
directions: Melt butter into bowl.
Add other ingredients.
Divide into 2 parts, 3/4 and 1/4.
Press larger part into a 9 x 13-inch greased pan.
Cover with pie filling.
Crumble remaining dough over top. Bake at 325° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: broccoli soup
directions: Saute onion in butter.
Stir in 3 tablespoons flour.
Add milk, gradually as white sauce.
Add grated cheese.
In another saucepan, dissolve bouillon cubes in 1/2 cup boiling water.
Add broccoli; cook until tender.
Add broccoli and cooking liquid to cheese mixture.
Heat, but do not boil.

title: spanish rice
directions: Heat butter in saucepan; add onion, green pepper and rice. Cook and stir over high heat until lightly browned.
Add tomatoes, water, salt and pepper.
Mix well.
Bring gently to boil.
Cover tightly, lower heat and simmer gently for 30 minutes.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: katie's  sugar 'n' spice
directions: Combine all ingredients, store in a shaker for sprinkling on toast, french toast or applesauce.
Or use as you would plain cinnamon-sugar.
Yield:
2 cups.

title: picnic spice cake
directions: Sift all the dry ingredients together in a large mixer bowl. Add the shortening, milk and vanilla.
Beat slow to medium speed for 2 minutes.
Add the two large eggs and beat 2 minutes more. Bake in a 9 x 13 x 2-inch greased and floured pan for 40 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: hamburger-noodle casserole
directions: Cook noodles until tender.
Heat oleo in a skillet; add meat and stir until very lightly browned.
Add onion, water, tomatoes and salt.
Cover and simmer for 30 minutes, stirring occasionally. Add peas and their liquid and cooked noodles; cook, uncovered, for 10 to 15 minutes on low.
Makes 5 servings.

title: salsa
directions: Simmer, uncovered, 30 minutes.
Pour into hot jars and process 15 minutes.
Makes 7 pints.

title: lemon chicken slow cooked
directions: Pat chicken dry. Combine oregano, seasoned salt and pepper; rub over chicken. Brown the chicken in butter over medium heat. Transfer to a 5-quart slow cooker. Add water, lemon juice, garlic and bouillon to the skillet. Bring to a boil. Pour over chicken. Cover and cook on low for 3 to 4 hours. Baste chicken. Add parsley. Cover and cook 15 to 30 minutes longer. Serve chicken over rice. Yields 6 servings.

title: hearty beef and crescent pie
directions: Brown meat, onion and green pepper.
Drain well.
Stir in tomato sauce, beans and seasonings.
Pat crescent rolls into a 9-inch pie plate, forming a crust.
Combine egg and 1 cup cheese; spread over crust.
Add meat mixture.
Sprinkle with the remaining cheese; sprinkle with paprika.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: crab salad
directions: Cook rotini noodles until done.
Drain and cool.
Add crab meat, tomatoes, peppers, cucumbers, celery, salt and pepper.
Stir until salt and pepper are mixed well.
Pour the dressing into the salad and mix well.
Chill in the refrigerator.

title: shoe peg corn casserole
directions: Microwave cream cheese, milk and butter; mix until sauce is thick and not lumpy.
Add green chillies and corn.
Pour into an 8 x 8 x 2-inch dish, sprayed with Pam.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese; top with bread crumbs and sprinkle with paprika.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: homemade irish cream liqueur
directions: In blender, combine all ingredients and blend until smooth. Store tightly covered in refrigerator up to 1 month.
Stir before serving.
Makes 5 cups.

title: butterscotch sauce
directions: Combine ingredients in saucepan; cook over medium heat to a full rolling boil.
Continue cooking for 5 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Cool.
Spoon over cake or ice cream.

title: potato casserole
directions: Mix first 8 ingredients together.
Put in 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Sprinkle crumbs and butter over potatoes.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
(I turned oven to 400° and baked 10 minutes longer.)

title: plain pastry or unbaked pie shell
directions: Use this pastry with hamburger pie, buttermilk pie, fresh peach pie, pecan pie, magic pumpkin pie; also in this book)

title: refrigerator pickles
directions: Wash and slice cucumbers and onion.
Place in glass jar.
Mix remaining ingredients.
Pour cold mixture over cucumbers and onion.
Cover and keep in refrigerator.
Will keep for a year.

title: soft taco shells
directions: Be careful in your selection.
When once selected, give your entire thoughts
to
preparation
for domestic use.
Some insist upon keeping them
in
a
pickle; others are constantly getting them in hot water.
This makes them sour and sometimes hard and bitter.
Even
poor
varieties
may be made sweet and tender by garnishing
them
with patience, well sweetened with love and seasoned with
kisses.
Wrap
them
in
a
mantle
of charity. Keep warm with
a
steady fire of devotion and serve with peaches and cream.
Thus
prepared,
they
will
keep for years.

title: good sugar cookies(makes 6 dozen)
directions: Cream
and
mix
Nucoa, white sugar and powdered sugar. Add oil
and
eggs;
then
add	dry
ingredients and vanilla. Chill. Roll into balls and dip in sugar.
Press with glass to 1/3-inch. Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: beans in crock-pot
directions: Twenty-four hour process.
In the morning, rinse beans and then cover with water to soak.
In the evening, rinse and drain water and put into crock-pot (I spray with Pam before) along with smoked ham hocks, cover with an inch of water, cook on low until dinner time, next night.
Stir occasionally.
Add salt to taste.

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: Mix together and bake at 300° for 45 to 60 minutes or until firm.
Before baking, sprinkle paprika on top.
Serves approximately 25 to 30.

title: chicken parmesan
directions: Cook beef, add sauce, and water.
Bring to a boil.
In a casserole dish, layer patties, cheese, and pour sauce.
Bake at 350 uncovered for 30 minutes.

title: crock-pot dinner
directions: Put all ingredients in a crock-pot.
Stir well and cook on low for 4 to 5 hours.
Serve with warm bread and a nice salad.

title: cottage cheese salad
directions: Drain pineapple.
Mix all ingredients together.
Chill and serve.
Makes 16, 1/2 c. servings.

title: artichoke dip
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Pour into a 2-quart ovenproof casserole. Sprinkle with paprika.
Heat in a 325° oven for 20 minutes.
This dip is good spread on Carr's table water crackers.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Mix the first 4 ingredients and cream until fluffy.
Add eggs and beat again until fluffy.
Mix flour, baking powder and salt and add gradually.
Stir in chips and nuts.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto greased cookie sheets.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes at 375°.

title: snappy fruit dip
directions: In a small bowl, combine yogurt, sour cream, honey and ginger. Chill.
When ready to serve, arrange fruit decoratively on a plate around bowl of dip.
Use your favorite fruit.
Makes 4 servings; 105 calories per serving.

title: fudge cookies
directions: Bring to a boil sugar, butter, milk and cocoa and boil 2 minutes. remove from stove and quickly add vanilla and peanut butter. Mix thoroughly and quickly add oats and nuts. Drop by spoonfuls onto wax paper.

title: corn pudding
directions: Place in shallow greased casserole.
Top with crushed corn flakes.
Dot with lots of butter.
Refrigerate or freeze.
When ready to serve, bring to room temperature.
Bake at 375° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: saucy hot dogs
directions: In a 1-quart micro-safe casserole dish, combine jelly and mustard.
Add franks; stir lightly.
Cover.
Microwave on High 2 1/2 to 4 minutes or until bubbly and hot, stirring every 1 1/2 minutes.
Serves 8 to 10 people.
Delicious!

title: no bake orange nuggets
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Shape into 1-inch balls.
Roll in 1/4 cup powdered sugar.
Keep in refrigerator.

title: make 'n bake for chicken
directions: Mix all ingredients together until well blended.
Dampen chicken and coat well.
Bake at 350°.

title: skillet cookies
directions: Cook together 1st four ingredients until dates dissolve and thicken in cast-iron skillet.
Cool to handling stage, then add cereal, nuts and vanilla.
Roll in small balls.
Roll in coconut. Place on wax paper.

title: "almost as good as sex" dessert
directions: Prepare cake as directed on box.
Allow to cool.
Cut cake into 2-inch pieces.
Place half of the cake pieces in the bottom of a large, deep glass bowl.
Prepare one box of pudding.
(The Kahlua may be substituted for 1/4 cup milk.) Immediately pour pudding over the cake in the bowl.
Top with half the Cool Whip. Repeat procedure with remaining ingredients.
Chill in refrigerator.

title: sausage quiche
directions: Brown shell lightly.
Crumble and cook sausage with onion until sausage is done.
Drain and put in partially cooked pie shell. Combine eggs with whipping cream and pour over sausage.
Top with cheese and bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes or until set.
Cool slightly before cutting.

title: beef stew
directions: Cut beef into 1-inch cubes.
Coat with flour.
Heat oil in frying pan.
Brown coated beef, 1/4 at a time.
Cut vegetables into 1 to 2-inch pieces.
Combine all prepared ingredients in a 5-quart Dutch oven.
Fill with water, just enough to cover.
Bring to a slight boil.
Cover and simmer 1 to 3 hours (the longer the better).
Season to taste.

title: low-fat potato salad
directions: Cook potatoes until tender but firm.
Cool and slice in a large mixing bowl.
Combine all ingredients.
Add potatoes and stir until well covered or coated.
Cool 1 hour.
Serves 8.

title: broccoli casserole(serves 6)
directions: Melt margarine and cheese.
Add soup and rice, let it set 5 minutes.
Add broccoli and pour into 8 x 8-inch baking dish.
Bake at 325° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: beef-bean enchiladas
directions: Crumble ground beef in frying pan; add onion.
Saute until meat is browned and onion is tender.
Drain off excess grease. Stir in beans, salt, garlic powder, taco sauce and olives; heat until bubbly.
Heat enchilada sauce; pour half the sauce into an ungreased shallow 3-quart baking dish.
In skillet, heat the oil about 1/4-inch deep.
Dip tortillas, one at a time, in hot oil to soften; drain quickly.
Place 1/3 cup of beef filling on each tortilla; roll to enclose filling.
Place seam side down in baking dish; pour remaining sauce over all; cover with cheese.
Bake uncovered at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: sandy's shrimp dip
directions: Chop the green onions and the baby shrimp real fine.
Mix the remaining ingredients with the onions and shrimp and chill.
This dip is real good served with Fritos.

title: layered salad
directions: Layer first 6 ingredients in large salad bowl.
Cover with mayonnaise and sugar mixture.
Next, sprinkle with Cheddar cheese and bacon bits.
Do not toss.
Garnish with cherry tomatoes. Cover and refrigerate overnight.

title: pork in tomatillo sauce
directions: In large pan, brown meat; mix often to brown evenly, about 5 to 8 minutes.
Add onion and cook together about 2 minutes.
Add potatoes and cook 5 minutes more.

title: quiche to die for
directions: Line the bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan with the bread crusts, which have been removed from the bread.
Layer cheese, ham, broccoli and then bread centers.
Mix eggs, milk and onion; pour over top.
Bake at 350° for 60 minutes.

title: turkey fruit salad
directions: Combine mayonnaise, honey and ginger; mix well.
Add all remaining ingredients except pecans; mix lightly.
Season with salt and pepper to taste, if desired.
Chill.
Stir in pecans just before serving.
Serves 6.

title: e-z fudge
directions: Melt the chips with sweetened condensed milk.
Stir in vanilla, salt and nuts.
Add marshmallows and stir.
Pour into greased pans (two 8 x 8-inch or one 9 x 13-inch).
Chill and set.
Makes 1 1/2 pounds of fudge.

title: marinara sauce(low-fat)
directions: Saute garlic in oil until light brown.
Add tomatoes, parsley and pepper.
Smash tomatoes with fork or potato masher in pan. Cook at medium heat for 25 minutes.
Serve over pasta of your choice.

title: bourbon balls
directions: Over hot (not boiling) water, melt chocolate morsels, remove from heat.
Blend in corn syrup and bourbon.
In a large bowl, combine vanilla wafer crumbs, confectioners sugar and nuts.
Add chocolate mixture; mix well.
Let stand about 30 minutes.
Form into 1-inch balls.
Roll in granulated sugar.
Let season in a covered dish for several days.
Makes 4 1/2 dozen 1-inch candies.

title: orange cream fruit salad
directions: In a large salad bowl, combine fruits; set aside. In a small bowl, beat pudding mix, milk and orange juice; beat until smooth. Add sour cream; mix well. Pour over fruit and toss to coat. Cover and refrigerate for 2 hours before serving.

title: fijian chicken marinade
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Put chicken parts in plastic storage bag.
(I think chicken tastes best when skinned with this marinade.)
Pour marinade over chicken in bag.
Squeeze all the air out of the bag and close.
Refrigerate for at least 3 hours. Bake chicken as usual pouring remaining sauce over chicken. Serve with white rice.

title: perfect pasta salad
directions: Cook pasta; rinse in cold water. In a large bowl, combine pasta, vegetables and salami. Combine oil, vinegar, salt and pepper and add to the pasta mixture. Toss well. Cover and chill at least 2 hours.

title: italian country chicken
directions: Heat oil in large skillet over medium heat.
Add onion and garlic; cook until translucent, stirring occasionally, about 10 minutes.
Add chicken, stir until cooked through, about 5 to 10 minutes.
Mix in artichokes with liquid, peppers with liquid and olives; heat through.
Season with salt and pepper.
Pour over cooked hot pasta and toss well.
Serve with Parmesan separately. Serves 6.

title: best baked beans
directions: Cook onion and bacon until done.
Add hamburger and continue cooking until meat turns brown.
Drain off drippings.
Mix all ingredients together and pour into a long baking dish.
Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes.

title: potatoes and carrots
directions: Cut up potatoes, carrots and green pepper.
Mix together in a 9 x 13-inch casserole dish.
Cut up margarine and mix with vegetables.
Sprinkle rosemary, salt and pepper over vegetables. Cover with aluminum foil and bake at 450° for 1 hour.

title: reuben casserole
directions: Preheat oven to Tater Tots baking.
This is usually about 425° or 450°.
Brown hamburger.
Chop onion and add to hamburger. While this is cooking, pour cream of mushroom soup into a (oil sprayed) casserole dish.
Add 1 1/2 cups of milk or water to soup. Add the 16 ounce bag of frozen corn to soup.
Drain and add browned hamburger and onion to casserole dish and mix together. Spread mixture evenly in casserole dish.
Sprinkle 1 1/2 cups of Cheddar cheese over mixture.
Place single layer of Tater Tots on top of Cheddar cheese.
Place in oven (uncovered) and bake for about 35 minutes or until the cheese is bubbling up between the Tater Tots.

title: bean and corn casserole
directions: Mix corn and beans.
Put in greased casserole dish.
Mix cheese, onions, soup and sour cream.
Spread over beans and corn. Sprinkle crackers and almonds over mixture. Drizzle butter over crackers.
Bake on 350° for 1 hour.

title: biscuits
directions: Combine
dry ingredients into large bowl; cut in shortening until mixture resembles coarse meal.
Add milk and stir until well
mixed.
Place
dough	on
floured surface.
Knead lightly
8 to
10 times.
Roll out dough 1/2-inch thick.
Cut with
floured cutter.
Bake on ungreased baking sheet in 425° oven for 12 to 15 minutes.
Makes 12.

title: blueberry pie
directions: Sift flour and sugar together; add berries.
Mix well.
Pour into pastry lined pie pan.
Moisten edge of dough with water; cover with top crust, making opening for steam to escape.
Press pastry well over edge; trim.
If canned berries are used, measure scant 1/2 cup sugar and 2 tablespoons flour.
Bake in hot oven (375°) for 25 minutes with foil over pastry edge.
Remove foil; bake 20 minutes more or until browned.

title: fresh strawberry pie
directions: Mix all together. Add enough red food coloring to make red. Cook until thick and clear red. When cool, pour in a cooled 9-inch pie shell with 1 pint of sliced strawberries (fresh) in bottom of pie shell. Let stand until firm. Top with whipped cream.

title: onion pie
directions: Mix and press into bottom of 9-inch pan.

title: sherry chicken
directions: Place chicken breasts in baking dish.
Combine rest of ingredients, including the mushroom liquid; pour over chicken. Sprinkle with paprika.
Fifteen minutes before finished, slice black olives over chicken.
Bake 1 1/2 hours at 350°.
Serve over noodles or rice.

title: huevos rancheros
directions: Heat enough oil to cover bottom of skillet.
Cook onion and garlic over low temperature until transparent.
Add tomatoes, chiles, sugar, salt, pepper and coriander.
Bring to boil.
Reduce to low heat and simmer, uncovered, 30 to 45 minutes, stirring frequently.
In a small skillet place oil to depth of 1/8-inch. Over medium-heat, fry tortillas, one at a time, until firm.
Drain well.
With a large spoon, make 6 hollows in the tomato sauce. Drop 1 egg in each hollow and poach until cooked to doneness. Remove eggs and place 1 egg on each tortilla.
Spoon sauce around each egg and garnish with avocado slices, cheese and olives. Serves 6.

title: company meatballs
directions: Combine all ingredients using hands to mix well.
Form into balls and place in baking dish. Cover with Sauce.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Layer chicken in 9 x 13-inch casserole dish.
Mix broth and soup; pour over chicken.
Combine flour, margarine and milk.
Pour over chicken.
Bake at 350° for about 1 hour and 30 minutes or until golden brown.

title: baked chicken
directions: Put chicken in shallow dish.
Cover with foil.
Bake 30 to 45 minutes at 350°.
Mix together the soup, water, vinegar, brown sugar and Worcestershire sauce.
Pour over chicken and bake another 45 minutes.

title: low calorie banana milk shake
directions: Put milk in blender.
Add vanilla and frozen banana, a little at a time.
If a thicker shake is desired, add ice cubes until desired thickness.

title: chicken and rice casserole
directions: Melt butter in baking dish.
Coat chicken with the butter and set aside.
Add mixture of rice, soups and mushrooms.
Place chicken on top.
Cover and bake at 275°
for 2 hours.
Uncover and bake for 30 minutes.

title: broccoli souffle
directions: After all of the ingredients (except broccoli) are well mixed, add the broccoli and bake in a buttered casserole dish for at least 40 minutes or until firm at 325° to 350°.

title: old fashioned caramel
directions: Mix all ingredients together. In a saucepan melt 3/4 c of sugar to a golden brown color. Add the mixture and stir over low heat till done.

title: bierocks(german meat turnovers)
directions: Saute beef, onions, garlic, salt and lemon pepper in a large skillet over medium-high heat, until beef is browned. Add cabbage, Worcestershire sauce and caraway seeds. Cook until cabbage is limp; drain liquid from mixture. Preheat oven to 350 degrees. On a lightly floured board, roll each loaf of dough into a 12-inch circle. Cut each circle into 6 wedges. Spoon cabbage beef filling into each dough piece, divided equally. Pull three points of each wedge to center and pinch to seal. Place bierocks on a lightly greased cookie sheet. If desired, brush dough with melted butter or egg wash (one egg white with 2 Tbsp. water). Bake in preheated oven for 30 minutes, or until golden brown. Serve hot, or wrap and freeze for heating later.

title: pork chops italiano
directions: Pour some flour on a plate and lightly coat the chops on both sides, shaking off the excess.
On another plate, spread the bread crumbs and season with the salt, pepper, garlic salt and parsley. Dip the pork chops in the beaten egg, then in the bread crumbs, coating both sides.
Place the chops on a plate and let them "dry" for about 10 minutes.
In a skillet large enough to hold all the pork chops, heat the oil and the butter.
Fry the chops over medium-high heat for 6 to 7 minutes on each side, until nicely browned.

title: puritan punch
directions: Pour pineapple juice over sherbet; garnish with fresh strawberries.
Add ginger ale and serve.
Serves 20.

title: marinara sauce
directions: In a 2-quart saucepan, over medium heat, in the 2 tablespoons oil, cook garlic and onion until tender, about 5 minutes.
Stir in tomatoes, their liquid and remaining ingredients.
Reduce heat to low.
Cover; cook for 20 minutes or until thickened, stirring occasionally.

title: chocolate bonbon candy recipe
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients and roll into small balls; put on wax paper.
Chill.
When chilled, melt paraffin and chocolate chips together.
After cool, put toothpick into bonbons and dip into chocolate paraffin mixture and place on wax paper to set.

title: spoon rolls
directions: Mix altogether.
Place	1
tablespoonful in each muffin pan. Bake 20 minutes
at
400°.	Dough
will save one week in refrigerator.

title: sour cream coffee cake
directions: Cream margarine, 1 cup sugar and eggs.
Sift together flour, baking powder and baking soda.
Stir vanilla into sour cream.
Add dry ingredients to egg mixture, alternately with sour cream mixture.
When blended thoroughly, divide dough.
Place 1/2 into a greased and floured angel food pan.

title: creamy banana pudding
directions: In large bowl, combine condensed milk and water.
Add pudding mix; beat well.
Chill 5 minutes.
Fold in whipped cream.
Spoon 1 cup pudding mixture into 2 1/2-quart glass serving bowl.
Top with 1/3 each of the wafers, bananas and pudding.
Chill.
Garnish, as desired.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Cook.
After it starts boiling 5 minutes, drop in cooled water to make soft ball.
Put 1/2 jar Marshmallow Creme and 1/2 jar peanut butter; beat until cool.
Put in pan.

title: lima bean casserole
directions: Saute onion and celery in margarine.
Add mushrooms.
Combine all ingredients in 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Bake 30 minutes at 325°.

title: soda pop popsicles
directions: Stir all ingredients in bowl.
Pour into popsicle molds or ice trays.
Cover with foil.
Insert sticks or toothpicks through foil and freeze.

title: marinated vegetables
directions: Chop cucumbers, tomatoes, bell pepper and onion in bowl. Combine salt, pepper, vinegar, sugar and oil; mix well and pour over vegetables.
Let set for 1 hour before serving.

title: sausage casserole
directions: Brown meat; set aside after draining into casserole dish.
Cook noodles until al dente, drain and add to meat along with chopped onion and green pepper.
Stir in tomatoes and sour cream.
Mix all ingredients together.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes, or until bubbly.
May be frozen and consumed later.

title: taco party wings
directions: Put dry ingredients in plastic bag.
Shake wings (drummettes) in bag, a few at a time, until coated.
Place in single layer on greased shallow pan.
Bake in 350° oven 25 minutes.
Turn wings and bake 10 minutes more or until tender.

title: noodles milanese
directions: Brown onion and garlic in 1 tablespoon oil; add beef and cook until brown.
Stir in sauce, paste, oregano and 1 teaspoon salt. Simmer for 15 minutes.
Beat one egg and mix with noodles.
Beat second egg and add spinach, 1 tablespoon oil, cottage cheese, Parmesan cheese and 1 teaspoon salt.
Mix well.

title: old fashioned sweet potato pie
directions: Combine sweet potatoes, brown sugar, margarine, egg yolks, spices and salt in a large mixing bowl; beat until light and fluffy.
Add evaporated milk; mix until combined.
Beat egg whites until foamy; gradually add sugar, beating until stiff.
Fold into potato mixture.
Pour filling into pie shell.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes; reduce heat to 350° and bake additional 45 to 50 minutes or until set.
Cool.
Top with whipped cream if desired.

title: shrimp scampi
directions: Heat oil in a large skillet over medium-high heat.
Add shrimp and saute for 1 minute.
Add garlic and saute 1 minute. Stir in wine, salt, pepper and bring to a boil. Reduce heat to medium.
Cook 30 seconds and add parsley, lemon juice and toss well to coat. Cook 1 minute or until shrimp is done.

title: cinnamon muffins
directions: Toast English muffin.
Butter while warm and spread on honey. Sprinkle with cinnamon.
Serve warm.

title: broccoli hot vegetable
directions: Put broccoli in casserole dish.
Spread with mayonnaise. Sprinkle with garlic salt.
Top with Parmesan cheese.
Bake until golden brown.

title: creamy chicken soup
directions: Boil chicken breasts in pot until cooked. Reserve broth. Cut into bite-size pieces.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Mix shortening, sugar, eggs, peanut butter and vanilla.
Add the dry ingredients.
Bake at 350° until browned.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Steam beans and drain in 2-quart casserole.
Mix milk and soup.
Add beans and mushrooms.
Add cheese and onions to top. Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: foolproof fudge
directions: Over low heat, melt chocolate morsels with sweetened condensed milk.
Remove from heat; stir in remaining ingredients.
Spread evenly in wax-paper lined 8-inch square pan.
Chill 2 to 3 hours. Makes about 1 1/2 pounds.

title: forgotten cookies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Beat egg whites until fluffy.
Add sugar until it stands in peaks.
Drop on pan lined with aluminum foil. Put cookies in oven.
Turn off oven.
Leave for 2 hours.
Do not open oven door.

title: shrimp mold
directions: Bring tomato soup and gelatine to a boil while stirring. Remove from heat.
Mix cream cheese, mayonnaise, celery, onion and shrimp together.
Fold tomato soup and cream cheese mixture together.
Pour into mold and chill overnight.
Makes about 1 quart of liquid.
Serve with vegetables or crackers.

title: trifle
directions: Pour sherry over cake and set aside.
Save a few berries to slice for garnish.
Crush remainder of berries and chill in refrigerator.
Make instant pudding as per directions.
In large glass bowl, line bottom of bowl with cake slices.
Spread with chilled berries; pour on pudding.
Chill.
Sprinkle with slivered almonds.
Top with berries and whipped cream.
Enjoy!

title: shepherd's dip
directions: You will need aluminum foil.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Cook hamburger meat with onion and garlic.
Drain off fat. Add soup and simmer.
Cook noodles; drain.
Top noodles with hamburger mixture.
Serve with sour cream on top.

title: bacon and cheese chicken
directions: Combine ingredients to make marinade;
mustard, honey, oil and lemon juice.
Pour 2/3 of marinade over chicken breasts and marinate them for two hours.
Chill remaining marinade.
After chicken is marinated, preheat oven to 375 degrees.
Sear chicken in pan 3 - 4 minutes per side.
Place in baking dish.
As chicken is cooking, saute sliced mushrooms in butter.
Season the chicken with salt, pepper, and dash of paprika.
Stack 2 pieces of cooked bacon crosswise on each chicken breast.
Spoon mushrooms on chicken.
Spread 1/4 cup Monterey Jack cheese and 1/4 cup cheddar cheese on each breast.
Bake in pan for 7 - 10 minutes.
Sprinkle chicken with parsley.
Serve with extra honey mustard.

title: herbed-butterflied leg of lamb
directions: About 2 1/2 hours before serving, in skillet over medium heat in hot butter, cook onion, garlic, 1 teaspoon salt, 3/4 teaspoon rosemary, 3/4 teaspoon thyme and 1/4 teaspoon of pepper until onion is tender.

title: creamed beef
directions: Melt butter in pan.
Add flour until you have a stiff paste. Add milk, stirring continuously.
Add beef.
Cook until thick like gravy.
Serve over toast or biscuit.

title: magic cookie bars
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Melt margarine in pan.
Sprinkle in crumbs; pour in condensed milk, then morsels, then coconut. Press firmly.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes.
Cool thoroughly, then cut into bars.

title: baked penne with sausage, zucchini and fontina
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Grease a 2 1/2 to 3-quart deep casserole.
Cut each zucchini half in thirds lengthwise, then crosswise into 1 1/2-inch long pieces.
Heat oil in heavy, large skillet over medium heat.
Add sausage and cook, breaking up with fork.
Transfer to bowl using slotted spoon.
Add onion to skillet and cook until beginning to soften; stir occasionally, about 5 minutes.
Add zucchini.
Season with salt and pepper and saute until almost tender, about 8 minutes.
Return sausage to skillet. Add cream and oregano and bring to a boil.
Add half of cheese to sauce and stir until melted.
Cook pasta until tender but firm. Drain well.
Return to pot.
Add sauce and stir to coat.
Put in casserole.
Top with remaining cheese.
Bake until heated through, about 15 minutes.
Serve hot.

title: chocolate pound cake
directions: Preheat the oven to 325°.
Cream butter and shortening together in a large bowl until light and smooth.
Add sugar and continue beating until well blended.
Add the eggs, one at a time, beating after each addition until well blended.
Sift together the flour, baking powder, salt and cocoa; add alternately with the milk to the batter, beating well.
Add the vanilla and beat until well blended.
Grease and flour a 10-inch tube or Bundt pan.
Pour in the batter and "spank" the bottom of the pan to distribute the batter evenly.
Bake 1 hour and 10 minutes.
Let the cake cool in the pan and turn out onto a cake plate.
Wonderful!

title: chocolate or butterscotch dessert
directions: Press in 9x13 pan. Bake at 350° for 15 minutes. Let cool; crumble in bottom of pan.

title: taco pie
directions: Fry ground beef in skillet; season to taste.
In a large pan, heat soups, sauces and beans.
When meat is browned, add it to the soup mixture and mix.

title: ritz chicken casserole
directions: Boil, drain, and cube chicken.	Place in bottom of 9x13 casserole dish.
Mix sour cream and soups together.
Pour over chicken.
Pour crushed crackers over mixture.
Melt butter and pour over crackers.
Bake 30-40 minutes at 350 degrees.

title: banana bread
directions: Cream butter and sugar together.
Add remaining ingredients; mix well.
Bake in large bread pan or 3 small bread pans for 1 hour at 350°.

title: cherry yum yum
directions: Follow directions on Dream Whip package.
Mix Dream Whip until stiff.
Mix cream cheese and sugar together until smooth. Add cheese and sugar mixture to Dream Whip.
Spread on graham cracker crust.
Cover this with chopped nuts.
Pour cherry pie filling over this.
Let chill and serve.

title: tunnel of fudge bundt cake
directions: Cream butter in a large mixer bowl at high speed.
Add eggs one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Gradually add sugar, continuing to cream at high speed until light and fluffy. By hand stir in flour, frosting mix and nuts until well blended. Pour batter into well greased and floured Bundt pan.
Bake at 350° for 60 to 65 minutes.
Cool 2 hours before removing from pan. Cool completely before serving.

title: authentic buffalo style chicken wings(serves 4 to 5)
directions: Sprinkle wings with salt and pepper.
Heat oil in deep fryer or heavy pot.
When hot, add half of wings and cook 8 to 10 minutes.
When wings are golden, remove to warm paper towel lined platter.
Cook remaining wings.

title: blintz souffle
directions: Melt the margarine in a 9 x 13-inch pan in a 325° oven.
Put the blintzes, face up, in the pan.
Beat the eggs with the orange juice.
Add remaining ingredients.
Pour mixture over blintzes. Bake at 350° for 1/2 to 3/4 hour, or until done.

title: fall sausage stew
directions: Heat olive oil.
Saute onion, zucchini, cabbage, red bell pepper and tomatoes in olive oil.
Add bay leaves, kidney beans, dill, caraway seed, Polish sausage and tomato sauce.
Add water (about 1 cup).
Reduce heat to simmer after stew comes to a boil. Cook on very low heat for 1/2 hour or 45 minutes.

title: chicken crescent roll-ups
directions: Saute celery, onion, garlic and chicken bouillon in margarine. Add salt and pepper.
Pour into a large bowl.
Add diced chicken and mix thoroughly.
Separate crescent rolls into 8 rectangles. Gently press dough together along serrated edge so rectangle is one piece.
Divide chicken mixture among the rectangles.
Fold lengthwise and press edges lightly together.
Place pastries in greased baking dish and bake at 375° for 20 minutes or until lightly browned.

title: winter spaghetti
directions: Brown first 3 ingredients.
Melt cream cheese and milk together over low heat and add to hamburger mixture along with water chestnuts.
Prepare spaghetti and drain.

title: pineapple cheese ball
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Note the crushed pineapple must be well drained.
Chill.
Serve with crackers.

title: nut cups
directions: Blend margarine and cream cheese until creamy.
Add flour and blend.
Divide into 24 balls and press into tiny muffin tins.
Add filling.

title: praline toast
directions: Combine butter, sugar and pecans. Spread on bread. Toast until brown and bubbly in oven.

title: pineapple sausage appetizers
directions: Mix together sausage and Rice Krispies.
Shape into 1-inch meatballs.
Brown meatballs in large frying pan.
Drain and set aside.
Drain pineapple, reserving juice.
Add enough water to juice to measure 2 cups.

title: manicotti
directions: Mix cheeses, eggs, parsley, salt and pepper together until well blended.
Parboil shells in salted water for 8 to 10 minutes. Stir occasionally to prevent sticking to pot; drain in colander. Fill shells at once, using knife.

title: nana's strawberry pie
directions: In saucepan, crush 1 pint of strawberries with fork.
Stir in rest of ingredients.
Cook over moderate heat, stirring, until thick and clear.
Cool.
Halve the other pint of strawberries and fold into cooked mixture.
Pour into pie crust and chill.
Serve with whipped cream.
Enjoy!

title: chicken ball
directions: Shape into ball and refrigerate.
Serve with vegetable thin crackers.

title: fruit delight punch
directions: Mix juices.
Slowly add ginger ale.
Add ice.
Makes 18 (4 ounce) servings.

title: vegetarian lasagna
directions: In large baking dish, layer 1/3 each of sauce, noodles, vegetables and cheese.
Repeat twice.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: onion cheese biscuits
directions: In a bowl, combine the milk, egg and butter.
Add biscuit mix, 1/2 cup cheese and onion.
Spoon into 6 greased muffin cups. Sprinkle with the poppy seeds and remaining cheese.
Bake at 400 degrees for 12-14 minutes or until toothpick inserted near center comes out clean.
Cool 5 minutes before removing from pan.

title: sausage and rice casserole
directions: Brown and drain sausage.
Add bell pepper and onion and saute. Add all other ingredients (soups are undiluted).
Pour into casserole and bake, covered, for 1 hour at 350°.

title: blueberry gelatin salad or dessert
directions: Dissolve jello in 1 cup hot water.
Add 1 cup cold water.
Add lemon juice, chill to syrupy.
Add blueberry pie filling.
Mix sugar and sour cream.
Spread over jello.

title: chili chicken
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Cook noodles as directed on package; drain.
In large skillet, cook and stir onion in butter until tender; stir in soup, chopped pimientos and chili pepper.

title: layered lettuce salad
directions: Layer all the ingredients one at a time in a Tupperware bowl with a tight seal or a 9 x 13-inch pan with foil.
Refrigerate overnight and serve.
May be tossed at serving, but not necessary.

title: vegetable sandwich
directions: Chop all vegetables finely; drain well.
Add lemon juice and cream cheese.
Add a little mayonnaise to make it easier to spread.
These are better fresh.

title: marinated turkey
directions: Buy whole turkey breasts.
Remove all skin and bone.
Cut into pieces about the size of your hand.
Refrigerate turkey in marinade at least 8 hours and up to 48 hours.
(The longer it marinates, the less cooking time it takes.) Makes 1 quart of marinade (12 servings).

title: kosher dill pickles
directions: Pack jar with generous amount of dill.
Add garlic, mustard seed and cucumbers.
Warm jar in water.
Mix vinegar, water and salt; bring to a boil.
Pour into jar and seal.

title: mother's buttermilk icing
directions: Cook over low heat to soft ball stage, stirring constantly. This cooks to a caramel color and is clear.
