Spread on cake while still warm. This is enough for 1 sheet cake.
If you care to, punch holes in cake with fork before spreading icing on. This makes it even better.

title: pineapple sheet cake
directions: Mix.
Grease and flour jelly roll pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Blend sugars and oils together well.
Add eggs.
Blend in all other ingredients.
Mix flour last.
If moisture is needed, add small amount of milk to facilitate spooning dough.
Bake at 320° slowly until done.

title: "frogmore stew"
directions: Fill large container of a propane cooker halfway with water; add 1/4 cup Old Bay seasoning.
Bring to a boil.
Add potatoes; return to boil and cook 10 minutes.
Add sausage and corn; return to boil.
Cook 10 minutes or until potatoes are tender.
Add shrimp; cook 3 to 5 minutes or until shrimp turn pink.
Remove with slotted spoon onto serving platter or newspaper-lined table.
Serve with additional Old Bay seasoning and cocktail sauce.
(May be coked indoors in large Dutch oven on cook top surface over high heat.)
Yield:
12 servings.

title: spinach casserole
directions: Beat eggs and flour until smooth.
Mix rest of ingredients. Check seasonings.
Bake in 2-quart casserole, uncovered, for 1 hour at 350°.
Let stand a few minutes before serving.

title: easy chicken pot pie
directions: Mix chicken and other ingredients in a large bowl.
Pour into greased baking dish.

title: country breakfast pie
directions: Brown sausage.
Crumble; drain well.
Mix cheese and sausage. Sprinkle in crust.
Add cream to beaten eggs; mix lightly.
Add chopped vegetables.
Mix; pour over sausage mixture.
Bake at 375° for 40 to 50 minutes.
Cool slightly before cutting.

title: gooey pumpkin butter cake
directions: Crust: Mix 1 egg and 1 stick butter with yellow cake mix. Lay in greased square baking pan.

title: quick coffee cake
directions: Mix all ingredients and put in greased 9x9-inch pan.
Sprinkle top with 1/4 cup brown sugar mixed with 2 tsp. cinnamon.
Bake at 375 degrees for 25 minutes.

title: strawberry delight
directions: Dissolve jello in hot and cold water.
Leave sitting out and cool slightly.
Add pineapple, bananas and marshmallows.
Stir into jello and chill until firm.

title: gingerbread boys and girls
directions: Mix all ingredients until dough forms (work with hands, if necessary). Cover and refrigerate at least 1 hour.
Heat oven to 375°.
Roll dough 1/8-inch thick on lightly floured cloth covered board. Cut with cookie cutters. To hang cookies, make a hole 1/4-inch from top with a plastic straw.
Place on greased cookie sheet. Bake 8 to 10 minutes. Immediately remove from cookie sheet and cool.
Decorate as desired.

title: peach pie
directions: Place peaches in bottom of pan.
Put bread fingers on top. Pour other ingredients (mixed together) over peaches and bread. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: hot crab appetizers
directions: Mix all ingredients well, spread on muffins and place on cookie sheet.
Broil on lowest rack until cheese is brown and bubbly. Cut into 8 sections;
serve
warm.

title: rotel chicken
directions: Cook and salt chicken.
Keep broth.
Let chicken cool, then cut into bite size pieces.
Saute onion, celery and bell pepper in 3 tablespoons margarine.
Cook spaghetti in chicken broth.
When done, combine all ingredients.

title: french silk pie* * * * *
directions: Most people enjoy a cocktail before dinner, but it is a good idea not to let them have time for more than 1 or 2.
With these a bowl of nuts and a dip with chips or other nibblers are usually in order.
Many guests may prefer more hors d'oeuvres, but if I have worked to make a good dinner, I prefer they eat more of the meal.

title: easy chicken pot pie
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Place contents of seasoning packet and butter in a bowl.
Add hot water; stir to partially melt butter. Add stuffing crumbs; stir gently to mix.
Mix soup and milk in a 2-quart casserole dish.
Stir in chicken, vegetables and thyme. Spoon stuffing over chicken mixture.
Bake for 45 minutes or until hot and bubbly.
Serves 4.
tags: Stove Top chicken flavored stuffing mix

title: no fail meringue
directions: Combine 1/4 cup sugar, cornstarch and salt in a saucepan, stirring constantly.
Add water and cook over medium heat until mixture comes to boil.
Boil one minute; cool completely.
Beat egg whites at high speed of an electric mixer until foamy. Gradually, add remaining 1/4 cup sugar, one tablespoon at a time, beating until soft peaks form.
Add vanilla and cornstarch mixture.
Beat until stiff peaks form.
Be sure to seal crust. Yields meringue for one pie.
Bake pie with meringue on top for 12 to 15 minutes at 350°.

title: peanut and chocolate chip cookie
directions: Combine first five ingredients in bowl; mix until fluffy.
Add combined flour, soda and salt, mixing well.
Stir in chips. Spread in a greased 10 x 15-inch baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes, until golden brown.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Boil chicken, debone.
Saute onion in small amount of chicken broth; add soup, chilies and chicken. Remove from heat.
In baking dish, layer Doritos, then mixture. Repeat and top with cheese.
Bake 30 minutes.
Serves 8.

title: coconut refrigerator cake
directions: Bake cake according to directions.
Let cool punching a few holes to allow cream of coconut to absorb in cake.
Top with Cool Whip and a little coconut.
Refrigerate.
Better in 2 days.

title: red bean salad
directions: Combine all ingredients; refrigerate.
Best after several hours refrigeration.

title: cheese cookies
directions: Melt oleo and add flour and cheese.
Add Rice Krispies and mix well.
Roll into small balls and slightly press down with fork. Bake in a 325° oven for 10 minutes.

title: mom's meat loaf
directions: Mix all the above ingredients together, putting a dash of salt and a dash of pepper. After mixing thoroughly, shape it into a loaf and place into your pan.
Spread ketchup on top of the loaf and put in a 350° oven for 60 minutes.
Remove from oven and let it sit, then serve.

title: creamy orange dressing(heart healthy)
directions: Blend all ingredients thoroughly.
Refrigerate before serving. Yield: 1 1/2 cups.

title: stuffed pepper cups
directions: Cut off tops of green bell peppers; remove seeds and membrane.
Precook green bell pepper cups in boiling, salted water about 5 minutes.
(For crisp peppers, omit precooking.)
Sprinkle inside with salt.
Brown meat and onion; add tomatoes, rice, Worcestershire, salt and pepper to taste.
Cover and simmer until rice is almost tender, about 5 minutes.
Add cheese.
Stuff peppers; stand upright in 10 x 6 x 1 1/2-inch baking dish.
Bake uncovered in 350° oven for 25 minutes.
Sprinkle tops with more cheese.

title: spiced pear butter
directions: Cook pears with wine, vinegar, cinnamon and cloves over medium heat until pears are soft, about 10 minutes.
Put through a food mill and return puree to a heavy pot (see Note).
Add sugar, lemon juice and allspice and stir.
Cook over low heat for 1 hour or until thickened.
Watch for scorching.
Makes about 5 pints.

title: mom's pecan pie
directions: In large mixing bowl, combine flour, sugar and salt.
Add well beaten eggs, Karo syrup, vanilla and melted margarine; beat by hand until blended.
Stir in pecans.
Pour into unbaked pastry shell.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: calabacitas
directions: In a wide frying pan over high heat, melt drippings.
Add zucchini, corn, chiles, onion and garlic.
Cook, stirring often, until vegetables are tender/crisp, about 5 minutes.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: spudnuts
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Add beaten eggs.
Sift 1/2 of flour, sugar and salt.
Mix into egg mixture; beat well.
Add rest of flour, milk and mashed potatoes alternately.
Let rise in covered bowl until doubled in size.
Knead and roll out.
Cut with doughnut cutter.
Let rise until double in size and fry in deep, hot fat.

title: cabbage and beef soup
directions: In a Dutch oven, brown beef.
Add all remaining ingredients except parsley.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer covered for 1 hour.
Garnish with parsley.
Soup can be frozen in serving sized portions to enjoy months later.

title: peppers stuffed
directions: Slice top off firm fresh bell peppers and remove seeds and pith.
Cut in halves lengthwise and boil for 10 minutes.
Drain. Brown ground beef; drain.
Mix with corn, tomatoes, onions, chili powder, salt and pepper and cook slowly for 15 minutes, stirring constantly.
Add bread crumbs to thicken.
Fill peppers with mixture and sprinkle with bread crumbs.
Dot with margarine.
Bake in pan to which you have added 1/2 cup hot water for 30 to 45 minutes at 350° until crumbs are browned.

title: green tomato pie
directions: Combine white and brown sugars, flour and nutmeg.
Arrange peeled and thinly sliced tomatoes in bottom of unbaked pie shell. Sprinkle with 3 or 4 tablespoons of sugar mixture, until all tomatoes are used.
Sprinkle remaining.

title: southern fried chicken
directions: Place chicken on warm platter.
Pour fat from pan into bowl, leaving brown particles in pan.
Return 3 tablespoons fat to pan. Blend in the flour; cook over low heat, stirring, until mixture is smooth and bubbly.
Remove from heat.
Stir in the milk and water. Heat to boiling, stirring constantly.
Boil and stir 1 minute. Add a few drops of the Bouquet sauce; season with salt and pepper. Makes 1 1/2 cups.

title: pizza casserole
directions: Cook curly macaroni.
While macaroni is cooking, brown hamburg, onion and salt and pepper.
When done, mix macaroni and hamburger together.
Add pizza sauce, tomato sauce, tomato paste, sugar, garlic, salt, onion salt and oregano.
Mix all together. Place 1/2 mixture in casserole.
Top with Mozzarella cheese, sliced pepperoni, remaining mixture and more cheese.
Sprinkle with grated Parmesan cheese and sliced pepperoni on top.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
This can be made in 2 casseroles and one frozen.

title: 24 hour salad
directions: Toss lettuce, onions, peppers, carrots and peas together. Spread in a 9 x 13-inch dish, or put in a large salad bowl. Spread mayonnaise all over the top, then cover with Cheddar cheese and bacon bits.
Cover the dish and refrigerate for 24 hours before uncovering.

title: sweet and sour red chicken
directions: Place chicken pieces in a large shallow pan.
Mix together salad dressing, soup mix and apricot preserves (1 clove garlic, 2 teaspoons mustard or soy sauce may be added for extra flavor). Pour mixture over chicken.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 1 hour or until tender. Turn chicken twice during baking, basting with sauce. Arrange chicken on serving platter.
Spoon pan sauce over chicken. Garnish with orange slices and parsley.

title: eggnog
directions: Stir sugar into egg yolks.
Add bourbon and mix well.
Whip egg whites and whipping cream.
Add sugar, bourbon and egg yolk mixture; mix very slowly.

title: picante chicken with brown rice
directions: Heat in a nonstick skillet; add the chicken and sprinkle with chili powder and cumin.
Add 1/4 cup water, the green onions, and garlic.
Saute until the chicken is no longer pink
Stir in the tomatoes, corn, rice, chilies, and 1/2 cup water.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce the heat, cover, and simmer 5 to 10 minutes, or until the rice is done.

title: hickory nut pie
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add beaten eggs from center out.
Add Karo and vanilla.
Stir in hickory nuts.
Pour into a glass 9-inch unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes, then reduce heat to 300° for 25 minutes.
Variations:
Pecans, peanut butter.

title: broccoli supreme
directions: Cook broccoli just to thaw.
Drain.
Combine soup, mayonnaise, onion, cheese and egg.
Blend in broccoli; pour in bottom of buttered 9 x 12-inch baking dish.
Top with crumbled croutons. Melt margarine and pour over casserole.
Bake, uncovered, for 30 to 35 minutes at 350°.

title: white chocolate chunk cookies
directions: In a bowl, combine the flour, baking soda and salt.
In another bowl, cream the butter with the granulated and brown sugars until smooth.
Add the vanilla and egg.
Beat until light.
Add the flour mixture, the chopped white chocolate and walnuts.
Blend well. Shape cookies, using a rounded teaspoonful of dough for each.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes until golden brown.

title: cranberry sauce
directions: Combine sugar and water into saucepan.
Stir to dissolve the sugar.
Add a dash of cloves and bring to a boil.
Add cranberries and a dash of salt.
Cook cranberries in boiling water until the skin pops.
This will take about 10 minutes.
Very good with roast turkey or meat pie.

title: fruit cocktail cake
directions: Mix all ingredients except brown sugar in large bowl with a spoon.
Pour into floured pan and sprinkle brown sugar over cake. Bake for 35 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: payday squares
directions: Melt oleo, peanut butter chips, Karo and vanilla.
Add to this Rice Krispies and peanuts.
Pat on top of marshmallows.
Cool and cut into squares.

title: dump cake
directions: Spray a 13 x 9-inch pan with nonstick spray.
Pour pie filling into 13 x 9-inch pan.
Top pie filling with cake mix.
Cut butter into small chunks and scatter over cake mix.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: merry cookies
directions: Cream butter; add sugar.
Beat until fluffy.
Add eggs; beat well and add fruit, dates and flour ingredients together.
Add batter with applesauce, vanilla and pecans.
Drop by teaspoon onto a greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: mid-east eggplant dip
directions: Pierce the eggplants in several spots; set them on a baking sheet and bake in a preheated oven 375° until very soft when pierced, approx. one hour.
Half the eggplants lengthwise; scoop out the pulp and discard skins.
In a food processor or blender place eggplant pulp with remaining ingredients and process until smooth.
Transfer mixture to a serving bowl; drizzle with a little olive oil and sprinkle with parsley.
Serve with toasted pita bread wedges.

title: raspberry poke cake
directions: Prepare cake mix as directed on package, baking in well-greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Cool in pan 15 minutes; then poke with fork at 1/2-inch intervals. Dissolve gelatin in boiling water.
Add cold water and spoon over cake in pan.
Top with Cool Whip non-dairy whipped topping.

title: sugar cookies(cut-outs)
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Add more flour to make a stiff dough, if needed.
Cut to desired shape.
Bake at 375° for 7 to 8 minutes or until light brown on edges.

title: glazed sweet potatoes
directions: Boil sugar and water 3 minutes.
Add butter.
Pare potatoes. Slice and arrange in single layer in baking dish.
Pour over syrup.
Bake at 350° until brown.
Baste several times.
Serves 10 to 12 people.
A holiday dinner "must".

title: chicken pot pies
directions: Cook vegetables according to package directions.
Drain.
In saucepan, cook onion until tender but not brown.
Stir in flour, salt, sage and pepper.
Add water, milk and bouillon granules all at once.
Cook and stir until thick and bubbly.
Cook and stir 1 to 2 minutes more.
Stir in cooked vegetables, chicken or turkey and parsley flakes.
Heat until bubbly.
Pour mixture into 2-quart casserole dish.
Unwrap pie crust and cut into large pieces. Arrange on top of chicken mixture.
Bake at 450° for 10 to 15 minutes or until crust is golden brown.
Serves 6.
Bake on cookie sheet to avoid dripping in oven.

title: nell's sugar-free punch
directions: Mix grape juice and ginger ale.
Freeze one quart to put in punch bowl.
Refrigerate remainder and Sprite or 7-Up.
Pour into punch bowl with grape juice and ginger ale with frozen quart.

title: tater tot casserole
directions: Combine soup and milk; heat.
Brown hamburger; drain.
Layer Tater Tots in one layer on bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Put browned hamburger on next layer, then cheese, then soup.
You can put chips on top, if desired.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: battletown baked squash
directions: Slice squash and then boil in salted water until done.
Drain and mash.
Saute onion, cream and crackers in 2 tablespoons butter and add to squash.
Pour into greased casserole and top with butter dots and a few bread crumbs.
Bake at 400° for about 1/2 hour or until firm.
Makes 10 to 12 portions.

title: punch bowl cake
directions: Crumble baked cake in bottom of punch bowl.
Pour pineapple over cake (juice and all).
Make vanilla pudding as box directs and pour over pineapple.
Pour cherry pie filling over pudding, then add Cool Whip on top.
Sprinkle with nuts, if desired.
Place in refrigerator.

title: vegetable pizza
directions: Press rolls into 9 x 12-inch baking pan.
Bake for 8 to 10 minutes at 350°.
Cool.

title: poppy seed casserole
directions: In olive oil in large skillet, cook turkey, onion and green pepper, separating meat as it cooks, until well browned and crumbled.
Drain liquid.
(Cook noodles according to package directions while meat is cooking.)

title: potato casserole
directions: In large baking dish, cut potatoes into bite size pieces; fill bowl about 3/4 full.
Cut carrots and onion in pieces.
Top with large green pepper, cut in large strips.
Salt to taste (takes a great deal of salt).
Add about 1 cup water and top with "blocks" of butter (several big ones).
Bake about 1 hour, covered, at 400°.

title: honey mustard chicken
directions: Stir salad dressing, mustard and honey.
Place chicken on grill or rack of broiler pan. Brush with 1/2 of sauce.
Grill or boil 8 to 10 minutes.
Turn and brush with remaining sauce. Continue grilling or broiling 8 to 10 minutes, or until done. Makes 4 servings.

title: angel food cake filling and topping
directions: Cut 1 angel food cake into 3 layers.
Mix sweetened condensed milk with rind of 1 lemon and juice of 3 lemons.
Add crushed pineapple.
Whip the heavy cream and add to above mixture.
Spread between layers, top and sides.
Chill.
Serves 12.
Good.

title: beau monde sourdough bread
directions: Slice bread almost through.
Mix rest of ingredients, except cheese, together.
Spread mixture on both sides of bread slices. Place a slice of cheese between every other slice.
Wrap in foil, leaving top slightly open.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: corn casserole
directions: Saute onion and chilies in melted butter; set aside.
Mix eggs, muffin mix and corn.
Pour corn mixture into greased 9 x 13-inch casserole dish.
Top with onion mixture.
Spoon sour cream over this.
Sprinkle grated cheese evenly over top.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes.

title: cookie owls
directions: Melt 2/3 cup of chocolate chips in double boiler.
Blend shortening and sugar.
Add egg, vanilla and peanut butter.
Add flour, baking powder and salt.
Add oats.

title: party mix
directions: Melt margarine and add seasonings.
Pour over all other ingredients and stir well.
Bake at 200° for 2 hours.
Store in glass jars.

title: crazy cake
directions: Sift the first 5 ingredients in your baking pan.
Make 3 depressions in the sifted ingredients.
Into the holes put vinegar, into the next one put vanilla and the last one put oil.
Pour cold water over all and mix with fork.
Wipe edge of pan before baking. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Use glass baking dish for best results.

title: apple-walnut cake
directions: Combine apples and sugar; let stand.
Beat eggs slightly. Beat in oil and vanilla.
Mix and sift flour, baking soda, cinnamon and salt.
Stir in alternately with apple-sugar mixture. Stir in walnuts.
Pour into greased and floured pan.
Bake at 250° for 1 hour.

title: salad dressing for tossed salad
directions: Combine all ingredients together and pour over tossed salad.

title: crunch cookies
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Spoon onto an ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 15 minutes at 350°.

title: fresh blueberry muffins
directions: Beat eggs.
Stir in milk and oil.
Mix in everything else, until lumpy.
Grease 12 muffin cups; fill these 2/3 full.
Bake muffins for 20 minutes at 400°.

title: asparagus divine
directions: Arrange cooked asparagus in baking dish.
Place chicken on top.
Combine cream of chicken soup, mayonnaise, lemon juice and curry powder and pour over chicken.
Top with cheese and bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes or until hot and bubbly. Serves 6 to 8.

title: applesauce cake
directions: In large bowl, combine first 8 ingredients. Combine applesauce, 1/4 cup water, yogurt, egg whites and almond extract. Stir into dry ingredients until moist. Fold in raisins. Pour into greased 8-inch square baking dish. Bake in preheated 350° oven for 25 to 30 minutes. Whisk powdered sugar and 1 teaspoon water until smooth. Drizzle over cake.

title: quick and easy lasagna
directions: While browning the hamburger, boil the lasagna noodles as directed.
Mix the hamburger and spaghetti sauce together.
In 9 x 13-inch casserole dish, make first layer your hamburger mixture. Sprinkle some of both cheeses and add the lasagna noodles and repeat, ending with hamburger sauce and cheese on top.
Bake at 350° until cheese is melted.

title: cherry squares
directions: Mix together and put into an ungreased 8 x 8-inch pan.
Bake in oven at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes.
Set aside to cool and prepare topping.

title: chicken broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli about 5 minutes.
Mix drained broccoli, chicken and soup. Top with margarine and grated cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: boiled drop cookies
directions: Bring the first 6 ingredients to boil and let boil exactly 2 minutes.
Add oats and nuts.
Mix thoroughly.
Drop from teaspoon onto nonstick cookie sheet or wax paper.
Let cool, then eat.

title: neapolitian pork chops
directions: Brown chops in oil in skillet.
Remove chops.
Saute onions, mushrooms, peppers, oregano, salt and pepper until tender.
Add tomatoes.
Simmer for 5 minutes.
Add chops; cover and simmer 1 hour (very low heat) or until tender.
Uncover and simmer for 15 minutes.

title: easy pumpkin bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour 4 small or 2 large loaf pans.
In a large bowl mix flour, sugar, baking soda, salt, cinnamon, nutmeg, cloves and baking powder.
Add pumpkin, oil and eggs.
Stir until dry ingredients are moistened and mixture is smooth.
Pour into loaf pans.
Bake for 60 minutes or until toothpick comes out clean.
Cool on wire racks.

title: ambrosia(classic ambrosia)
directions: Peel oranges, section and cut into small pieces.
Add remaining ingredients.
Chill well.
Spoon into dessert dishes. Top with cherries, if desired.
Yields 12 to 15 servings.

title: banana pineapple cake
directions: In a large bowl, mix first 4 ingredients.
Make a well in the middle and add remainder of ingredients.
Mix all well with spatula; pour into prepared Bundt pan and bake at 325° for 1 hour, then 350° for 10 minutes.

title: good banana bread
directions: Mix together bananas and milk, then set aside.
In another bowl, mix shortening, sugar and eggs, then add banana mix.
Put in loaf pan.

title: baby stain remover
directions: Combine all ingredients until dissolved.
Soak clothes for 24 hours.
Launder as usual.

title: sausage balls
directions: Leave sausage and cheese at room temperature.
Mix well. Shape into balls (small).
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes or until brown.

title: easy quick stroganoff
directions: Cook ground beef.
Add soup and sour cream.
Serve over rice or noodles.

title: fresh apple pound cake
directions: Mix sugar, oil and eggs. Add flour, salt and soda. Add vanilla, coconut, apples and nuts. Spoon into a greased and floured tube pan. Bake at 325° for 80 to 90 minutes.

title: tuna noodle casserole
directions: Cook pasta; drain and cover. Set aside. Preheat oven to 350°. Spray a 2-quart casserole with nonstick cooking spray; set aside.

title: russian tea
directions: Scrape	off
the
outer
layer	of
bark from roots and discard.
Wash
through
several
waters and boil four average size roots	in a gallon of water for 15 to 20 minutes.
Strain and sweeten with sugar or honey.
Serve hot or cold.

title: butterscotch striped delight
directions: Prepare pudding as directed on package, using only 3 1/2 cups milk.
Pour over cream cheese layer.
Chill several hours or overnight.
Spread with Cool Whip.

title: elegant chicken casserole
directions: Wipe chicken breasts with paper towel. Combine flour, salt and paprika in a paper bag. Shake chicken (one at a time) in bag until well floured. Brown lightly in butter.
Place ham in a casserole. Sprinkle with a little savory and a few celery leaves on each slice.
Cover with chicken on each ham slice. Add sliced mushrooms.
Pour wine into skillet chicken was browned in and stir well.
Add remaining flour mixture to sour cream.
Pour over chicken/ham.
Cover and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: peanut butter kisses
directions: Cream butter, sugars and peanut butter together.
Add eggs and mix well.
Add baking soda which has been dissolved in water. Add vanilla.
Mix well and then add flour.

title: caramel ribbon brownies
directions: Melt caramels and evaporated milk in a double boiler on low heat.
Combine cake mix, evaporated milk and melted butter.
Put 1/2 in greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes. Sprinkle chocolate chips and drizzle caramel mixture over base. Put rest of mixture on top (crumble over top).
Bake for 20 minutes at 350°.
Wait 10 minutes and cut.

title: grandma's chocolate cookies
directions: Mix cookie ingredients together.
Bake at 375°.
Frost while hot with the following..

title: antipasto
directions: Combine all ingredients and cook slow until done.
Then seal in hot jars and lids.
Good as a snack on crackers.

title: frozen neapolitan delight
directions: Cut pound cake lengthwise into 2 equal layers.
Place one layer on an 18-inch square sheet of heavy-duty Reynolds Wrap.
Cut ice cream brick lengthwise into 2 equal slices and place on cake layer.
Top with second cake layer.
Frost top and sides with whipped topping.
Decorate with pecans and cherries.
Place on foil in freezer for about 2 hours.
Remove from freezer.
Bring foil up; double fold over top and fold in ends.
Return to freezer until ready to serve.

title: ostrich stroganoff
directions: Dredge meat in seasoned flour.
Heat 2 teaspoons of butter in skillet and brown ostrich quickly on all sides.
Add mushrooms, onions and garlic.
Cook 3 or 4 minutes or until onion is barely tender.
Remove meat and mushrooms and set aside.
Add 2 tablespoons of butter to pan drippings and blend in 3 tablespoons flour.
Slowly pour in cold meat stock.
Cook and stir until thickened.
Return meat and mushrooms to skillet.
Stir in sour cream.
Serve over rice or hot, buttered noodles.

title: unbelievable lasagne
directions: In 13 x 9-inch pan, spread 1 cup of sauce.
Arrange a layer of lasagne.

Top with sauce, Ricotta, Mozzarella, Parmesan and sauce. Repeat, gently pressing lasagne pieces into cheese mixture below. End with a final layer of lasagne; pour remaining sauce on top, making sure all of pieces are covered.
Top with remaining Mozzarella and Parmesan.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 55 minutes or until lightly browned and bubbling.
Allow to stand 15 minutes. Cut into squares.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: three-minute fudge
directions: Mix milk, sugar and salt in a 2-quart saucepan.
Heat to boiling over low heat.
Boil and stir 3 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Add marshmallows, chocolate chips, vanilla and nuts, stirring until chocolate and marshmallows are melted.
Pour into buttered square pan (9 x 9 x 2-inch).
Refrigerate until firm; cut into squares.

title: maine blueberry buckle
directions: Cream together 1/4 cup butter and 1/2 cup sugar.
Beat in the egg and vanilla.
Sift together the salt and 1 cup flour.
Add alternately with the milk to the creamed mixture, beginning and ending with flour.
Pour into a buttered 9-inch baking dish. Distribute the blueberries over the batter.
Combine the remaining sugar, remaining flour and the spices.
Cut in the remaining butter until the mixture resembles coarse meal.
Sprinkle over the blueberries.
Bake at 375° until a knife thrust in the center comes out clean, about 40 to 45 minutes.
Serve warm, with whipped cream.

title: marinated olives
directions: Place drained olives in an airtight Tupperware container.
Add crushed garlic, lemon juice and olive oil.
Sprinkle with garlic salt to taste.
Shake container and place in refrigerator.
Chill minimum of 2 hours, shaking container occasionally.

title: lasagna
directions: Prepare noodles as directed on package.
Brown hamburger.
Mix together cottage cheese and egg.
Add spaghetti sauce to hamburger.
Mix well and add garlic.
In large dish, layer sauce, noodles, cottage cheese mixture and Mozzarella cheese until all is used, ending with sauce.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: chocolate mousse
directions: Beat eggs with an electric mixture on high for 3 minutes until thick.
Gradually beat in sugar.
In a saucepan, Heat 1 cup half and half until very warm.
Gradually add in egg mixture, stirring constantly, for 5 minutes over low heat.
DO NOT BOIL! Gradually stir in chocolate chips until melted and cover and chill for 2 hours.
Fold cool whip into chocolate mixture until uniform and serve.

title: quiche provencale
directions: In large skillet over medium heat, cook onion and green pepper in oil until tender, about five minutes.
Stir in tomatoes, zucchini and seasoning.
Cook, uncovered, an additional 10 minutes.
Drain and set aside.
Beat eggs and milk until blended. Pour into pie shell.
Spoon in vegetables.
Bake at 375° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Let stand 5 minutes before serving.
Yields 6 servings.

title: herb-baked fish
directions: Melt butter in baking dish.
Coat fish in butter.
Turn in breadcrumbs and return to pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes depending on thickness of fish.

title: two tone salad
directions: Melt 9 marshmallows and add small can crushed pineapple. Cool.
Make 1 package lemon jello with 1 3/4 cups water and cool. Whip 1/2 pint cream.
Add pineapple-marshmallow mixture, whipped cream and cream cheese to jello.
When jello is solid, add lime jello or your choice, made according to package directions to top.

title: raw vegetable dip
directions: Mix together.
Keep chilled until serving time.

title: key lime pie
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Beat egg yolks with milk, lime concentrate and food coloring (enough to make it a pleasant green).
Pour into prepared crust.
Bake 30 minutes.
Prepare meringue and cook until browned.
Refrigerate.

title: layered pecan pie
directions: Combine and pour over bottom layer.
Bake at 375° for 35 minutes.

title: george washington pudding
directions: Mix flour, sugar, baking powder, salt, butter and milk and pour into baking dish.
Mix cherries, sugar, water and almond extract.
Pour over top of batter.
Bake at 350° until brown and crisp on top, 30 minutes or longer.

title: kahlua creme brulee
directions: Bring half and half, cream and sugar to boil, then remove from flame.
Let cool.
In bowl, lightly whisk yolks while slowly adding sugared creme.
Add Kahlua; remove any froth from the top.
Ladle mixture in ramekins and bake approximately 20 to 25 minutes at 325° in water bath, lightly covered with foil (they are ready when bounce to touch).
Refrigerate until completely cooled.
Cover top with coating of sugar and caramelize.
Serve immediately.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: smoked beef dip
directions: Soften cream cheese and mix.
Put in oven until warm.

title: velma's crab cakes
directions: In a mixing bowl, combine the crab meat, parsley, cayenne pepper, salt and pepper.
In a small mixing bowl, combine the egg, mustard, horseradish and mayonnaise.
Mix well.
Add the mayonnaise mixture to the crab meat and fold all the ingredients together until well blended.
This mixture will be quite moist.
Divide the mixture into 6 equal parts and shape into round cakes.
Dredge them lightly in breadcrumbs.
Heat the oil in a frying pan over low to medium heat.
Add the crab cakes and saute approximately 5 minutes on each side.
Drain on paper towels and serve.
Makes 6 crab cakes.

title: 7 layer salad
directions: Layer ingredients in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cover and seal with 2 cups mayonnaise.
Sprinkle over mayonnaise, 2 tablespoons sugar and 1 pound Cheddar cheese (shredded).
Cover and refrigerate at least 8 hours or overnight.

title: manhatten venison roast
directions: Sprinkle meat tenderizer on all sides of roast.
Let stand for 1 hour.

title: orange marmalade bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease a 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan.
Into a large bowl, sift together flour, baking powder and salt.
Stir in nuts.
Combine eggs, oil, honey, marmalade and milk; blend well.
Add to flour mixture; stir only until flour is well moistened (batter will be lumpy).
Turn batter into prepared pan. Bake 65 to 70 minutes or until lightly browned and a tester inserted in center comes out clean.

title: peach kuchen
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cut butter into dry cake mix until crumbly.
Mix in coconut.
Press evenly over bottom and halfway up sides of ungreased 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Arrange peach slices over partially baked crust. Mix sugar and cinnamon. Sprinkle over peaches.
Mix sour cream and egg (yolks).
Pour over top. Bake 30 minutes longer.
Do not overbake. Serve warm.
Makes 12 to 15 servings.

title: osgood pie
directions: Mix as listed. Pour into single unbaked pie shells and bake until knife comes out clean when inserted in pie. Bake at 425° for 10 minutes, then reduce heat to 325° for 30 minutes. Yield: 2 pies.

title: fast and easy fruit cobbler
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Melt the butter or oleo in a 13 x 9-inch glass baking dish.
Tilt to cover bottom and sides of dish.
Spread fruit over butter, enough to cover bottom of pan in single layer. Sugar and cinnamon may be sprinkled on top of fruit, if desired. Mix together the sugar, flour and milk.
Pour over fruit and spread to edges of dish.
Bake at 350° for about 30 to 45 minutes until golden brown.

title: meat loaf
directions: Saute onion, garlic and bell pepper.
Dissolve bouillon cube in small amount of hot water.
Mix all ingredients, except mushroom soup and mushrooms, in oven baking pan and pat into loaf.

title: grandma's cure for cold
directions: Combine all ingredients except liquor in 1 cup glass measure or mug. Microwave on High 1 to 2 minutes, until piping hot.
Stir in rum or brandy and serve immediately.
Serves 1.

title: taco casserole
directions: Brown hamburger with onion. Drain. Sprinkle garlic and turn off.
Add water, chili powder and taco sauce.
In a long pan, put a layer of meat mixture, then a layer of beans and then cheese. Do this again, if you have enough.
Crush corn chips and put on top. Put in oven at 350° until good and hot.
Chop up lettuce and tomatoes and serve with this.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
It will take awhile to mix in the flour, but do not give up and add moisture.
Bake in a 325° oven on a cookie sheet until golden brown.
Best when served hot. Very easy to microwave.

title: cheese ball
directions: Grate Cheddar cheese fine.
Mix with other ingredients.
Roll into a ball and roll in paprika and nuts.

title: easy chicken casserole
directions: Cook and debone chicken.
Cut into bite-size pieces.
Mix soup, mushrooms and sour cream.
Pour over chicken.
Crush crackers and pour evenly over chicken mixture.
Pour melted butter over crackers.
Cook at 300° for 1 hour.
Poppy seed may be sprinkled on top.
Serves 8.

title: french market soup mix
directions: Combine all beans.
Divide into 14 (2-cup) packages for gift giving and present with the following recipe for French Market Soup.

title: freezer fudge
directions: Put evaporated skim milk and cottage cheese in blender container.
Process at high speed until mixture is smooth.
Pour into small bowl and add rest of ingredients.
Using electric mixer, beat until thick and creamy.
Pour into shallow nonstick 8-inch square pan.
Freeze until hard.
Cut into 24 squares. Remove to airtight container and store in freezer.
Do not thaw before eating.
Entire recipe contains the equivalent of 2 ounces of protein and 4 milk allowances.

title: hawaiian nut sandwiches
directions: Blend milk and cheese.
Add pineapple and nuts; blend well. Spread between slices of thin, buttered bread.

title: bean soup
directions: Sort and wash 1 1/2 cups assorted beans.
Place in a Dutch oven.
Cover with water 2-inches above beans and soak overnight. Drain off water, leaving beans in Dutch oven.
Add 4 cups water, undiluted chicken broth, garlic powder and pepper.
Cover and bring to boil.
Reduce heat and simmer 1 1/2 hours or until beans are tender.
Add remaining ingredients and simmer uncovered 30 minutes. Stir occasionally.

title: hawaiian delight sandwiches
directions: Cook bacon and set aside.
On the bottom slice of the bun (bread), place a slice of well drained pineapple.
Top with bacon strips and then cheese strip.
Place under broiler until cheese melts.

title: barbecue smokies
directions: Mix in cooking pot. Boil low-medium heat. Wait until it boils. Enjoy!

title: steak or what
directions: Pat ground beef evenly into a 9 x 12-inch pan.
Spread potatoes and onions and peas evenly over it.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Mix soups and spread evenly on top.
Cover with aluminum foil and bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.
(Can use peas or cooked sliced carrots.)

title: banana-nut bread
directions: Cream sugar and oleo; add eggs.
Mix well.
Add rest of ingredients.
Mix well and beat.
Heat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour 4 No. 2 cans or 1 loaf pan.
Fill cans half full.
Bake for 1 hour.
Let stand in cans 5 minutes, then remove so that breads won't get soggy.

title: impossible pie
directions: Beat all ingredients in blender for 3 to 4 minutes.
Pour in a greased and floured 10-inch pie pan.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: crab soup
directions: Heat all, except crab meat and sherry, then add crab meat. Never boil.
Before serving, add 1/4 cup or more sherry.

title: leona's nut caramels(margaret wagner)
directions: Put sugar, syrup, whipping cream and butter in pot; stir until boils.
Then add half and half.
Place immediately in buttered pan.
Refrigerate.

title: old fashion molasses cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Roll out on floured board and cut.
Bake at approximately 350°.

title: cool whip pineapple cake
directions: Prepare and cook cake mix as directed on the box.
It should be cooked in three 8-inch round pans.
Combine cool whip and vanilla pudding and mix well.
Fold in pineapple.
After cake cools, ice cake with cool whip icing.
Make sure it is between each layer and around the sides.
Store in the refrigerator.

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix well and bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Bake in large casserole dish.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Mix sugar and peanut butter together until crumbly.
Put this into the baked pie shell or graham cracker crust (saving a little to put on top).
Make pudding and pour into pie over peanut butter mixture and chill in refrigerator.
Top with Cool Whip.
Sprinkle remaining sugar mixture on top.

title: half moon cookies(with butter frosting)
directions: In a mixing bowl, combine shortening, sugar and eggs.
Mix well until a smooth consistency results.
Then add flour, baking soda, baking powder, salt, milk and vanilla.
Drop tablespoons of batter on cookie sheet and bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes. When cool, spread half the cookie with butter frosting (white) and the other half with chocolate frosting.

title: oatmeal valentine cookies
directions: Sift flour, baking powder and salt; mix with butter, sugar, milk, egg and vanilla.
Beat until smooth.
Stir in oats.
Roll 1/8 inch thick, cut and decorate.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet at in 375° oven for 15 to 18 minutes, until light brown.

title: honey mustard chicken
directions: Mix the first 3 ingredients together; brush on top of chicken. Broil or grill 8 to 10 minutes.
Turn and brush other side. Continue for 8 to 10 minutes until tender.
Very good served with rice.

title: spaghetti sauce
directions: Cook and stir meat, onion and pepper until meat is brown and onion is tender.
Stir in remaining ingredients except spaghetti and cheese.
Cover and simmer on low heat; stir often.
Cook spaghetti and pour sauce over it.
Top with cheese.
Serve with salad and crusty rolls or French or Italian bread.

title: asparagus casserole
directions: Combine cracker crumbs and oleo.
Place 3/4 crumbs in bottom of dish.
Place asparagus on top of crumbs.
Make cheese sauce using last 4 ingredients.
Pour over asparagus.
Top with rest of cracker crumbs.
Sprinkle on almonds.
Bake 12 minutes in 450° oven.

title: granny's macaroni and cheese
directions: Beat eggs together; add little milk and mix.
Add rest of milk if needed.
Cook macaroni as directed; rinse with hot water to remove starch.
Add grated cheese, eggs, pimento and butter; mix and then pour over macaroni.
Stir/fold into macaroni, then pour into pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: savory southern chicken pot pie
directions: Brown sausage in saucepan; drain on paper towel.
In same saucepan, melt margarine. Blend in flour, salt and pepper.
Stir in chicken broth and milk. Cook until thickened. Add chicken, sausage and peas.
Pour in a casserole dish. Top with pastry.

title: my crock-pot bean dip
directions: Combine all ingredients in crock-pot.
Cook on low temperature for 2 hours.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: communion bread
directions: Mix
to
form dough.
Knead and roll to 1/4-inch thickness. Score
in
small squares after placing on baking pan to make breaking
apart
easier.
Bake
at low temperature until medium brown.

title: banana-spice cookies
directions: Beat the margarine or butter with an electric mixer on medium to high speed for 30 minutes.
Add about half of the flour, the sugar, eggs, baking powder, vanilla, cinnamon, baking soda and cloves; beat until thoroughly combined.
Beat in remaining flour. Beat in bananas; stir in nuts.
Drop by rounded teaspoonfuls 2-inches apart onto a greased cookie sheet.
Bake in a 375° oven for 8 to 10 minutes or until edges are lightly browned.
Cool cookies on rack and frost with butter frosting (optional).
Makes 60 cookies.

title: ragu beef over rice
directions: In medium size saucepan, brown ground beef along with onion and green pepper.
Turn heat to low and add spaghetti sauce. Cover and simmer for 15 minutes.
Prepare Minute rice as directed. Pour beef mixture over rice in individual servings.
Serve with a salad and some breadsticks.
Serves 4 to 5.

title: quick lasagne(serves 6 to 8)
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
In large skillet, brown meat; stir frequently.
Stir in onion soup mix, tomato sauce and water.
Cover and simmer 15 minutes, stirring occasionally.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Mix Velveeta with soup and chilies and heat. The cheese will melt without sticking. Add remaining ingredients. Pour into sprayed 13 x 9-inch dish. Cover with foil and cook until heated thoroughly, approximately 10 minutes at 450°. Serve immediately. Serves 6. Only 4 Weight Watchers points per serving.
